/* Frozen public snapshot: 4,000 signatories, oldest to newest. */
window.STATIC_SIGNATURES=[{"name":"Caterina Scaramelli","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Benjamin Siegel","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kate Lemmon","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emmanuel Toledo","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Peter Cheung","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kara Mostowski","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Anne Trainer","zip":"02130","message":"Safer roads and more extensive public transit is needed more now than ever."},{"name":"Jennifer Waddell","zip":"02130","message":"If you've paused these safety measures to further your political career, as people have mentioned, shame on you."},{"name":"Kristin Battis","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Micaela Coady","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Matt Warfield","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Anne Griepenburg","zip":"02121","message":"Every traffic death is preventable and we must take action now to fulfill the promise of Vision Zero. No more deaths."},{"name":"Caroline Peters","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Deborah Bernard","zip":"02130"},{"name":"David Ganzi","zip":"02130","message":"Mayor Wu, Boston needs your leadership to improve our streets."},{"name":"Mary E. Cirbus","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Yesika Williams","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Elizabeth (Beth) Cooney","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Simona G Lang","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Dylan Keating","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Alec Donowitz","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Elizabeth Coughlan","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Melissa Wolter-Gustafson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Erik Then","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Sara Schnitzer","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Anastasia Ekman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Magdalena Madrzyk","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Leslie Walstrom","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Leigh Kalbacker","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Naomi Sobel","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Arjun Mudan","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Jason Cortlund","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Maggie Roth","zip":"02130","message":"We are heartbroken."},{"name":"Adam Roberts","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Maddie Holden","zip":"02130"},{"name":"John Saylor","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Henry Hanson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"March Penn","zip":"02130","message":"Also abolish concurrent crossing in Boston please. It is not safe to have cars turning at the same time that pedestrians get the walk signal."},{"name":"Joshua Kern","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Laura Frye-Levine","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ankit Kumar","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Adam B Burrows","zip":"02130","message":"We cannot continue to allow bicycle and pedestrian safety to be held hostage by loud voices who oppose any changes to automobile-dominant transportation infrastructure."},{"name":"Katie Fargnoli","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Nicholas Triano","zip":"01845"},{"name":"Margaret McCulloch","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Karen Book","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Emily Drevets","zip":"02130","message":"No more deaths to traffic violence!!"},{"name":"Sydney Hardin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Scott Englander","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Ruthann Cheryl Thomas","zip":"02131","message":"My heart aches for the loss of Louisa Gag's life. I bike to work along that route (from Roslindale to Kendall Square) and have had a few close calls at the intersection of Tremont near Roxbury Crossing. Please restore funding and continue projects to build cycling infrastructure that keeps cyclists like Louisa safe.\n\nThank you, and holding space for your own grief,\n~Ruthann Thomas, Roslindale MA"},{"name":"Anthony Lacina","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Enid Eckstein","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Samantha Bottom-Tanzer","zip":"02130","message":"As a member of this community, resident of Jamaica Plain, and resident physician who commutes daily to MGH by foot, bike, or T, I depend on safe and timely ways to reach the hospital so I can care for other members of the Boston community. It is a constant topic of discussion among my family and friends how dangerous these streets are for pedestrians and cyclists. My thoughts are with Louisa."},{"name":"Sophia Samaha","zip":"02130","message":"I used to bike this intersection every single day. I am devastated at this avoidable tragedy. No one should have to die on a commute to work"},{"name":"Travis Marshall","zip":"02131","message":"A city for people needs streets for people. Bostonians deserve streets that serve everyone, designed to be safe for everyone."},{"name":"Joseph Von Holten","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Sarah Slavick","zip":"02130","message":"I’ve been sorely disappointed in the stalling of bicycle infrastructure. You were elected with a mandate and have not been following it lately."},{"name":"Jennifer Bruni","zip":"02445","message":"NOT ONE MORE!!!!!"},{"name":"Dasha Mikic","zip":"02130","message":"I don’t want to feel afraid of coming home to my baby ever again…just because I love to cycle"},{"name":"Zoe Fleischmann","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Reuven Steinberg","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jack Dougherty","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Kirsten Levandowski","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Kevin Block-Schwenk","zip":"02135","message":"I suppored you politically due to your support of a Green New Deal and better cycling infrastructure and really hope you keep moving forward with all that."},{"name":"Scott Kilcoyne","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Gabrielle Leavitt","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Tina Holland","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Gabriella Spitzer","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Katya Podsiadlo","zip":"02130","message":"My husband bicycles on a daily basis to work as a city librarian. Please make our streets safe with improvements for bicycles immediately."},{"name":"Irena Acic","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Dawn Belkin Martinez","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kristin Peterson","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Nicholas Gardner","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Adam Rodman","zip":"02119","message":"I am a physician in Longwood and bike past the intersection where Ms. Gag was killed every single day. I was incredibly heartened a few years back during planning sessions for redoing Columbus at Roxbury Crossing, as well as for slow streets. But years later, nothing has changed. I am incredibly disappointed, and more pedestrians and cyclists will die unless the city does something."},{"name":"Molly Phelps","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Gabriela Amore","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Michael Hogan","zip":"02148","message":"While I live in Malden, I commute by bicycle into the city, mere blocks from where Louisa was killed yesterday morning. Please take these deaths seriously and do what can be done to prevent another."},{"name":"Tim Lepczyk","zip":"02131","message":"Enforce traffic laws as well. Driving, walking and biking in Boston shouldn’t be so dangerous."},{"name":"Andrea Carusona Bruno","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Miles Howard","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Camilla alexius","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kelly O","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Alex Alex","zip":"02125","message":". . .  What else to say that hasn’t been said and documented in public format?"},{"name":"Josh R","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Sarah Block","zip":"02138","message":"Boston is part of my daily commute. Please take action immediately. Western ave flexposts are gone. Please return them."},{"name":"Sammy Nave","zip":"02131","message":"Please please please push these forward. As parents of young children it's one of the reasons we voted and advocated for you. I want to be able to walk my kids to Sarah Robert's without fearing for their safety. No more preventable deaths!"},{"name":"Caitlin Kullberg","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Dan Merrow","zip":"02130","message":"Your staff has been telling you this would happen for 18 months.  Louisa told you it would happen.  I told you it would happen.  Your Chief of Streets and his Deputy told you it would happen and you fired them because of it.  This is your fault and you cannot correct it.  Start by firing Nick Gove and releasing your Streets Cabinet to let them do their jobs so it doesnt happen again."},{"name":"Matthew Rice","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Darryll Fernald","zip":"02130"},{"name":"David Hofer","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Nina Garfinkle","zip":"02116","message":"I recently moved to Amsterdam after fighting for safe streets with LivableStreets and WalkBoston (and Louisa!) for 20 years. Change is not happening fast enough and I didn’t want to die."},{"name":"Angela Markle","zip":"02130","message":"Its long past time to put the safety of city residents first. Unpause safe streets projects now!"},{"name":"Allison D Kornstein","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Jennifer Cuadra","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Caitlin Outterson","zip":"02143"},{"name":"ORen Pilinger","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Maria  Cesca","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Christina Spangler","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Heidi Fessenden","zip":"02119","message":"Please, Mayor Wu, we cannot have any more fatalities! I can’t understand the way you have pivoted on bike lanes and safe streets, and I am a huge fan of yours. My children walk in this city, and I bike. I am scared for all of us!"},{"name":"Kaitlin Robinson","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Kevin McGaffigan","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Rebecca Klanchesser","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jackson Rutecki","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Zachary Yaro","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Patricia Connors","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Emily Jacobsen","zip":"02445","message":"I am not a resident of Boston. So if you think someone with a Boston zip will be more influential, use their name. People dying preventable violent deaths has to stop."},{"name":"Jacob Hanson","zip":"02130","message":"Literally you need to quit this selfish shift before you alienate your whole base."},{"name":"Trevyn Langsford","zip":"02130","message":"Do your job."},{"name":"Shailah Stewart","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Boris Perlovsky","zip":"02445","message":"How many more bicycle riders need to lose their lives before you (and other city leaders) improve our streets?"},{"name":"Kathleen McDonough","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Piero Falci","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Gray Leiper","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Diana Doty","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Claire Clay","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sarah Filman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kathryn DiMaria","zip":"02131","message":"I’m terrified to let my family bike in this city and we consider moving out of the city often even through we love it because of the safety of our street (Hyde Park Ave). Please make this a priority"},{"name":"Murray Adelman Hershkowitz","zip":"02130","message":"Louisa was a friend to me and so many folks, and would earnestly listen to all of our negative feedback on the infrastructure that ultimately killed her, and would do everything in her power to make those concerns heard.\n\nThis is an outrageous slap in the face to what she worked towards on this administrations behalf and we must all come together and demand the changes necessary"},{"name":"Rose Gottlieb","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Cullen Deimer","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Deb Allen","zip":"02131","message":"Please help us we need you to take action to keep bikers safe!"},{"name":"Dan Gottlieb","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Andrew Gibson","zip":"02134","message":"Hi Mayor Wu, I am a big fan of your’s generally. On street safety though, you have a been a huge disappointment (especially last year or so). I hope you reconsider your admin’s direction on street safety. Every death is preventable on our streets in my opinion."},{"name":"Ruby Vail","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Marcos Rodriguez","zip":"02130","message":"The 180 on safe streets projects and your complete lack of transparency for this shift was unthinkable before the election."},{"name":"Shira Weiss","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Bentley Meyer","zip":"01230"},{"name":"Amy Dorfman","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Andrew Szendrey","zip":"02141","message":"It could have been any one of us."},{"name":"Patrick O'Neil","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Miguel Schoonover Duran","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Darren Huang","zip":"02134","message":"Start delivering on the policy platform that you campaigned on. The status quo that you choose to uphold is killing people, even your own staff."},{"name":"Chris Foran","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Jon Ramos","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Kevin ONeall","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Henry Relph","zip":"02131","message":"Extremely disappointed by your inaction, mayor. You will need to earn my support back in your future endeavors by being a true champion on safe streets for all (mainly cyclist and pedestrians), not just kowtowing to drivers and their interests."},{"name":"Carrie Blazina","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Jordan Browne","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Julia Ebert","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Chris Vaughan","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Robin Halperin","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Diane Choih","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Vincent Soubbotin","zip":"02145","message":"Delays in favor of cars are literally killing us. Safe streets are not something we can afford to delay"},{"name":"Olivia Dumaine","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Hank Layfield","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Itamar Turner-Trauring","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Maura Burke","zip":"02458"},{"name":"Tristan Roubenoff","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Mark Smith","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Kimone Williamson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Katherine Roach","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Mitch Montgomery","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Mary Delaware","zip":"02131","message":"Hi Mayor Wu, Mary here. When I first moved to Boston in '21, I biked everywhere: work, the library, the grocery store and even first dates. Once I witnessed a bike accident on Washington near Target. As I stopped to see if he was ok, the driver was yelled at him. This incident, combined with others more tragic, made me stop cycling. It’s a shame b/c cycling is the best! Make our streets safe NOW."},{"name":"Phoebe Bean","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Danielle Mooney","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Sam Allon","zip":"02138","message":"Josh Kraft lost, yet in 2026 you govern as if he had won. We want Mayor Michelle Wu back! Not Mayor Michelle Kraft."},{"name":"Rush Sanghrajka","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Leah Grodstein","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Victoria Garcia","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Emma Simmons","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Charles Denison","zip":"02118","message":"Street safety should not be a political issue to be tossed around like a football. It involves real people and real human lives. Inaction will only result in more injury and more deaths."},{"name":"Pamela Snider","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Sophia R","zip":"02120","message":"As a witness to this horrific event and someone working in the transportation sphere who knows people deeply affected by this tragedy, we can no longer be complacent. Doing nothing is a choice, and it’s costing lives."},{"name":"Liam Sullivan","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Andrew Dykman","zip":"02111"},{"name":"Eva Breitenbach","zip":"02143"},{"name":"David Guertin","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Prapti Verma","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Rachel Bernstein","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Sam Maron","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Brian Antonio","zip":"02492","message":"This was entirely preventable. Please move forward with these initiatives before more lives are lost on your watch."},{"name":"Libby Mooers","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jonathan Manos","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Danna Solomon","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Liliana Justice","zip":"02144","message":"Mayor Wu, I am devastated. Please take action now. There is no reason to have this many traffic deaths in a modern, forward-thinking city. I went to BC and want to stay here, but I want a city that moves forwards, not back."},{"name":"Susanna Bohme","zip":"02121"},{"name":"Erin Packard","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Susan Elsbree","zip":"02130","message":"Please go back you commitment to bike lanes and safe street. The problems that arose that makes you stop, we’re about the lack of thought, execution and lack of implementation experiments of your team- not of the idea."},{"name":"Sidney Hare","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Matthew Lyon","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Debra Vinci","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Stephen Ringlee","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Diana Cowan","zip":"01970","message":"While my family lives outside the city, we travel and commute in and through Boston. Thanks for your attention to this important safety issue"},{"name":"Cassidy Salus","zip":"02186","message":"I was hit by a car near this intersection around 10 years ago, at the intersection of tremont/columbus. I was lucky to walk away either way minor injuries.  But it could have been avoided."},{"name":"Karl Schmeckpeper","zip":"02142"},{"name":"Caitlin Connolly","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Theresa V","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Maria DaRocha","zip":"02119","message":"I’m afraid to even consider riding with my child on the back of my bike. Please do something so we can all be safe."},{"name":"David DaRocha","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Hilary Allen","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Molly Gagnon","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Madeline Higgins","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Asa Reed","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Misha Hill","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Eve Boltax","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Evan Zinner","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Kirkland Ahrens","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Katya Dreyer-Oren","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Brian McFadden","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Anne Pellenq","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Aleksandra Burger-Roy","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Liam Axon","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Samantha Nelson","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Carly Merritt","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Louise Robbins","zip":"02130","message":"Louisa Gag was a sterling person and passionate advocate for safe streets; to honor her memory, the least you can do is agree to the actions listed in this letter."},{"name":"Dustin Rogers","zip":"02111"},{"name":"Sophia Pinto Thomas","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Rosa Herrero","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kyle Cucinotta","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Bana Abubakar","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Michael Pinkham","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Dana Ostberg","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Shane Dunn","zip":"02119","message":"Mayor Wu,\n\nI have lived in Roxbury for 7 years, Boston for close to 20. The hardest I have worked as a neighborhood advocate and community leader in my neighborhood association has been on streets-related issues — on a basic one-way street no less! And biking daily — on my own or with my kids on our bike — is terrifying. The area where Louisa died is notorious for awful vehicular behavior."},{"name":"Carmen Rondash","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Greg Buckland","zip":"02131","message":"Mayor Wu:\n\nSafer streets CAN NOT WAIT.\n\nNo more deaths on our streets.\n\nKraft made reversing street safety central to his campaign and you trounced him. Why on earth would you pause/slow roll safer streets after that?\n\nYou have a mandate for safer streets. Use it, or we will replace you with someone who will.\n\nNo more platitudes. Action. Now.\n\nWith Respect and also Fury,\nGreg Buckland, Roslindale"},{"name":"Kazuhiro Akamatsu","zip":"01854"},{"name":"Goldman Sackler","zip":"02120","message":"Enough is enough. Traffic calming measures need to be implements city wide. Starting with accident hot spots. Mayor Wu has dropped the ball after reelection on the promise to make transit safer for pedestrians and cyclists. Humans> Cars"},{"name":"Sharon Britton","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sabri Bilsel","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Vivian Girard","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Daniela Petuchowski","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Tiffany Cogell","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Caroline Bean","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jonathan Krones","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Debra Graves","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emily Kruse","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Nathan Weinberg","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Miranda Dotson","zip":"02130","message":"Rest in power Louisa. You should be here. Mayor Wu, do not let her death pass without a safety overhaul of Boston’s streets."},{"name":"Jade Eliasson","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Susan Winning","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Anne Ennis","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Zachary Bodnar","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Christopher Catalfamo","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Montell Khaldi","zip":"02130","message":"I’m not mad, just disappointed."},{"name":"Alexander Angotti","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Steven Ramirez","zip":"02130","message":"Prioritize roads to work for the residents of the city."},{"name":"Sarah Wachter","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Josh Tingley","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Lindsey Tucker","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Christopher Kelsey","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Alicia Fessenden","zip":"02119"},{"name":"James Zhen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Brian Fizer","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Molly McGinty","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Claire Barker","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Julianna Brody-Fialkin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Erica Desautels","zip":"02130","message":"These are the important funding projects that actually create a better Boston for all of us on a daily basis. It should not have taken this tragedy to make an impact!"},{"name":"Alianora Reilly","zip":"02130","message":"Louisa was my friend. She helped me find a safer route to work. She warned me about the dangers of the unprotected lanes. Your inaction cost her everything."},{"name":"Lewis celestin","zip":"02130","message":"Stop funding the police, stop defunding youth jobs, FUND SAFETY FOR ALL OUR COMMUTERS, FAMILY, SIBLINGS,FRIENDS,Neighbors"},{"name":"Nikki Lee","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Cheryl Ierna","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Joshua Keegan","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Zoe Peters","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Mayya Bozhilova","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Julian Nowogrodzki","zip":"02155","message":"I bike every day. That could have been me. It could have been me and my 8-year-old, who rides in our cargo bike. It could have been my husband. We cannot rely on individual drivers to protect us, that’s just not how the human brain works. Our city roads and streets need to be designed to protect us."},{"name":"James Reddick","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Michael Serpa","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Janelle Crowley","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Courtney Swartz","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Matthew Tschiegg","zip":"02131","message":"Please build more physically separated and protected cycling infrastructure. Our lives depend on it. Our lives are worth more than car throughput and parking availability."},{"name":"Steven Berry","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Leslie Cohen","zip":"02139","message":"Louisa Gag is the daughter of friends of mine. She is the second person in my life — the first being my beloved friend Jinny Chalmers, former Young Achievers school principal, killed in November 2920 —  to be killed riding a bike on the streets of Boston.  These tragedies are unspeakable and unnecessary, causing lifelong grief and unfathomable loss.  Please do all you can to make our streets safe."},{"name":"Tim Russell","zip":"02140"},{"name":"William Price","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Abraham Laxague","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Rebecca Ginzburg","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Grainne Buchanan","zip":"01970"},{"name":"Theresa Donohoe","zip":"02453"},{"name":"Mary Butcher","zip":"02132","message":"Safe streets cannot wait. Every day delay is another day closer to another tragedy such as this one. I don’t want the next death to be a parent with their child on their bike."},{"name":"James Gerity","zip":"02127","message":"Stop the U-turn, take action on the dangerous streets where cars kill our neighbors, our coworkers, our loved ones. You have a clear mandate, we are waiting for you to act."},{"name":"Thomas Thuene","zip":"02131","message":"Louise's death is devastating. Don't let her die in vain"},{"name":"Zakary Ganhadeiro","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Christine Ventura","zip":"02131","message":"I appreciate all that you’ve done, but the time has come for us to do more and make Boston the most bicycle and pedestrian friendly city in the world."},{"name":"Correna Cohen","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Angela E. Kelly","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Ethan Matthews","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Dan Rubin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Olivia Mobayed","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Yi Ming Wu","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Laura Smeaton","zip":"02131"},{"name":"John Thrasher","zip":"01752","message":"I used to ride into the city constantly. But these days I no longer feel safe w/DRIVER FIRST menality that your city continues to push upon residents, commuters, and fellow Massachusettsan(Bay-Stater). \n\nHow many more innocent citizens of this great state must be injured, and sadly recently again killed, before the motor vehicle isn't the primary means of travel through the state?"},{"name":"Valachovic Kristen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Victoria Kelly","zip":"02130","message":"Please be a leader and not just a politician. Residents voted for you to get things done and make our city safer, not pander to the whims of centrists that you court to for your next campaign."},{"name":"Lauren Glenister","zip":"02131","message":"Stop killing cyclists and focusing on vehicles.  This city must be safe to travel without a car"},{"name":"Maddie DeClerck","zip":"02130","message":"I am a transportation engineer who works in the public sector and a daily bike commuter with two kids on their own set of wheels now. Biking is our identity, it’s our passion, and it’s every one of our greatest fears is that we live through the death of a great friend/ family member or one of our like Louisa was. We will demand more, we will show up and we are more intent then ever."},{"name":"Ben Allen","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Jane Akiba","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Shelby Johnson","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Veronica Clavijo Jordan","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Maria T Maffei","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Lauren Galinsky","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Allison McDonough","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Mallory Sin","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Hillary Koch","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Corey Mullins","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jack Stropko","zip":"02130","message":"This is another senseless death from road violence. The city indirectly has blood on its hands, and it has let itself and the people of Boston down. Mayor Wu was given a mandate to fix our dangerous, stressful, chaotic streets, and she has run out of excuses."},{"name":"Catherine Niedzwiecki","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Helen Raizen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kaly Connolly","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Matthew Mersky","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jack McGill","zip":"02145"},{"name":"James Glenister","zip":"02131","message":"As a cyclist in Boston I have the same goal as everyone else traveling through the city: arrive alive. \n\nThe mayor has decided, despite running on the promise of safer streets and better cycling infrastructure against a famously bike hating candidate, she does not need to deliver on those promises and make it harder for those of us who bike to achieve that goal. \n\nEnough is enough."},{"name":"Lars Andresen","zip":"02119","message":"This is particularly disappointing as you ran your campaign on street/bike safety. Now you are doing exactly what your opponent, Kraft, said he would do, and \"put a pause\" on bike infrastructure. Do not let the perfect stand in the way of the good. We need good bike infrastructure now, and can work on perfecting it later."},{"name":"Virginia Berman","zip":"02131","message":"We are grieving and we know Louisa would want this."},{"name":"Tanner Muro","zip":"02131","message":"The number of times that our lives are endangered while commuting is simply unacceptable. \n\nI consider it a good day when during my morning or afternoon commute I only see one traffic law broken by drivers or a close call for me from someone who is not paying attention. And that is each way. \n\nI shouldn’t have to risk my life to get to work. No one should. Something must be done."},{"name":"Zachary Sager","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Graham Moitoso","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emma Chinitz","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Bathsheba Grossman","zip":"02143","message":"What is wrong with you? Always more space, time, oil, pollution, blood, lives for cars cannot be the future. Why are you giving it to them? Stop now.\nKeep this up and you are not a mayor for people."},{"name":"Katie Metzger","zip":"02130","message":"We appreciate all you've done for the city of Boston. Please do everything in your power to continue the movement of making the streets safer for us all."},{"name":"Amy Light","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Lisa Beatman","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Susan Sheffler","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Josh Fairchild","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Rachel Wyon","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jenny Duquette Norcott","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Wolf Hamel","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Clara Kerwin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Alexander Shankland","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Marcela Moreno","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Shannon Mooney","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Heather Mumford","zip":"02130"},{"name":"G Charron","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Susan Viola","zip":"02130","message":"The safety of our streets is a quality of life issue and a basic right of every pedestrian. Fix this issue now!"},{"name":"Derek Nye","zip":"02121","message":"Please act. Keep me alive to come home to my daughter and wife, whether I bike, walk, run, or drive."},{"name":"Lisa Wall","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Lisa Goddard","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Andrea Patiño C","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Oscar Lee","zip":"02169"},{"name":"Matthew Ruggiero","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Annisha Borah","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kerry Jo Green","zip":"02131","message":"I would be signing this letter as a cyclist, if I felt like I could safely cycle in this city. But since I don't, I'm signing this as a pedestrian, a driver, and a human being who has seen the damage that can be done on our streets when safety is ignored."},{"name":"Rand Wilson","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Sarah Allen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Rukmini Reddy","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Nathan Eckstrom","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Caryl Haddock","zip":"02128","message":"If I’d wanted a pause on protected bike lanes, I’d’ve voted for Kraft. I trusted you to prioritize safety but you haven’t."},{"name":"Cooper","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Laura Castañón","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Sandra Huckleberry","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emma Itri","zip":"02109"},{"name":"Claire Pacacha Borger","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Reza J","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Riccardo Arcodia","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Ariel Friedman","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Giuseppe Barbesino","zip":"02421"},{"name":"Alexandra Keenan Wolff","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Miguel Carrillo","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Danielle Williams","zip":"02130","message":"I've been so impressed with what you have done for Boston in your last 4+ years as mayor. My husband and son commute regularly on a bike together, and I implore you to make sure your next focus is on making the streets of Boston friendly and safe for everyone"},{"name":"Maren Tober","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Lucy Harackiewicz","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Grace Burke","zip":"02130"},{"name":"George Butcher","zip":"02132","message":"I walk, bike, drive and ride around this city and have done since 2019. We know what is needed. The risks of taking the imperfect action(s) are far out weighed by the harm of the status quo."},{"name":"Cristian Suarez","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Sandy Shea","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Christian Keefer-Moomaw","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Evelyn  Ortiz","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kristina Kaufmann","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Heather Johnson","zip":"02130","message":"In addition to the above, it is clear to anyone spending time in Boston as a cyclist, pedestrian or driver that traffic enforcement is at an appallingly low level - and has been for several years now. I regularly observe many near misses that could be avoided if the streets were actually policed properly and drivers did not have a free pass to run reds, etc. It’s a complete embarrassment."},{"name":"Sue Downing","zip":"02476","message":"Although I do not live within the city itself, I regularly cycle through Boston. I am a senior citizen and lifelong nondriver dependent upon my eBike for mobility and access, for mental and physical health, for every day commutes and errands, and for community rides. I bike. I vote."},{"name":"Eliott Wiener","zip":"02131","message":"A good mayor would make Vision Zero a top priority and not delay safety improvements. Improvements that are well understood and widely implemented in other cities both near and far. Copy what other cities, and other mayors, have already done. Road capacity is not more important than protecting lives. There will always be complainers; you should ignore them and do the right thing."},{"name":"Amelia Anthony","zip":"02127","message":"Please don’t let these senseless deaths continue! It’s time that you take action and do what we elected you to do."},{"name":"Christina Knapp","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sara Fogarty","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Violette Ballecer","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Chessin Gertler","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jacqueline Presedo","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Tanya Ross","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Daniel Tucker","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Colleen Sullivan","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Josh Jones","zip":"02472","message":"I trusted you. I met you at a going away party for a friend of mine. You seemed so happy about bikes and what they could do for the city. But then you took it all back. Why?"},{"name":"Alicia A","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Sasha Martin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Britta Seifert","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Matthew Cole","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Vero González","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Nathan Bennett","zip":"02130","message":"I see far too many ghost bikes in the side of streets. people drive like crazy because the police don't enforce the traffic rules. the only thing that gets enforced is parking tickets and expired tags."},{"name":"Eric Nieminen","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Roisin Foley","zip":"02130","message":"I have known Louisa since the first grade at the Trotter school, and worked alongside her in transportation circles as an adult. Her death is beyond heartbreaking. She loved this city and its people so much and she deserved better. Please don’t let another person die to appease naysayers who prioritize cars over human lives."},{"name":"Craig Woodmansee","zip":"02458"},{"name":"David Gutierrez","zip":"02135","message":"Mayor Wu is a disappointed."},{"name":"Kaitlyn Shrestha","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Daniel Kvistad","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Mary Tenenbaum","zip":"02132"},{"name":"David Paul Harrington","zip":"02130","message":"One more death that was preventable with safer, clearly marked streets and traffic enforcement"},{"name":"Cary Weiss","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Matthew Nardone","zip":"02130"},{"name":"William maciolek","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Abbie S","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Benjamin Silverman","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Eva Capova","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Allison Demas","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emily Bowe","zip":"02130"},{"name":"James Ivey","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Claire Gibson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Pandora Hess","zip":"02115","message":"Signing this a day after my baby girl and I were almost mown down by a car while legally crossing at a pedestrian light in Longwood. One of many such incidents. Enough is enough."},{"name":"Caesar G","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Maya Margolis","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Corrigan Luckey","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Sitar Terrass-Shah","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kara Oberg","zip":"02176"},{"name":"Natalie Shure","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Arnaud Frouin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emily Haberlack","zip":"02119"},{"name":"austin Perea","zip":"11233"},{"name":"Kirstie Tirandazi","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Sarah deSimas","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jordan Zinner","zip":"02131","message":"I want to live in a world where my daughter can safely get to school and have her parents arrive home alive. This infrastructure is unacceptable. No more studies, and just results."},{"name":"Santiago Aurelio Mota","zip":"02904"},{"name":"Izzy Essman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"LCA","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Danniely Staback","zip":"02904"},{"name":"Tim Morrissey","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Jaqueline Bezerra","zip":"02149"},{"name":"Jeffrey Parks","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Chris Borger","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sophia Franco","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Jesse Vengrove","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Elvira Mora","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Jennifer Gillen","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Lise sheehan","zip":"02110","message":"Please improve cycling safety citywide. Atlantic Ave especially."},{"name":"Ethan Yao","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Blair Pershyn","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Beverly Arsem","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Mark P","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Zev Pogrebin","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Thomas O’Malley","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Gwyneth Helie","zip":"02130","message":"I’m a friend of Glenn Ingraham, who tragically lost his life almost two years ago on Hyde Park Ave. This recent loss hits hard. Please, please."},{"name":"Matthew Tribby","zip":"02446"},{"name":"catherine Kemmett","zip":"02453"},{"name":"KC Anderson","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Daniel Monaco","zip":"02134","message":"I watched Louisa’s friends weep today at her vigil. On my way home from that vigil, I was almost struck twice by distracted drivers while “sharing the road”. Mayor Wu, please consider the lives of the people in your city. This death is not the first this year and it certainly won’t be the last if you do not act swiftly to implement infrastructure that physically separates bikes from vehicles."},{"name":"Scott Jones","zip":"02130","message":"Please I'm begging you for the safety of me and my children, TAKE ACTION on Hyde Park Ave! We are Woodbourne residents. There are IMMEDIATE safety improvements we can make NOW. I've attended several community meetings hosted by your staff. I've let my voice be heard at every opportunity. Improve now, then make things perfect later. PLEASE!"},{"name":"Keanna Smigliani","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Dan Cahoon","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Daniel Arsem-O'malley","zip":"02135","message":"Keep my many cyclist friends safe!!"},{"name":"Zack DeClerck","zip":"02130","message":"Dr. Mayor Wu, Our busy life is on foot, bike, and pub. transit.  Our kids love being able to bike to elementary school in Roxbury, and even downtown on the weekends (which has gotten harder with the recent removal of protected bike lanes). Louisa was a friend of ours. We're devastated. Drivers' behavior is out of control, and there's little evidence that City leadership is serious about safety."},{"name":"Colin Kanter","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Joanie Parker","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Clemens Alt","zip":"02062","message":"I was hit by a truck in 2021 on my commute into and through Boston and got away with 5 broken ribs but my life intact. Enough is enough. Action on actually protecting people who chose a different mode of transport than a car is long overdue. Act now."},{"name":"Brett Rado","zip":"02114","message":"Justice for Louisa! She, like many other advocates in Boston, worked tirelessly to secure a better future for our city. I am deeply saddened that the city’s political apathy toward safe streets has cost this community another remarkable human life. It is my sincere hope that this administration learns from this and treats the matter of traffic violence with the urgency and seriousness it deserves."},{"name":"Carly Martin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Chris McIntosh","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Izarys Rivera","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Kristina Woodard","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Amy Linsky","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Clare Fitzgerald","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Houda Chergui","zip":"02131","message":"Having been doored before in Jamaica Plain while cycling, I know how unsafe it is to be a biker in Boston. Please protect our bike lanes and our community."},{"name":"Nicole Santiago","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Chris Yu Jang","zip":"02460"},{"name":"Sean Lambert","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Maggie Spruck","zip":"02121"},{"name":"Nate Kaufman","zip":"02116","message":"Please. Stop stalling safety projects for political reasons. Prevent further injury and death. Take safety seriously again."},{"name":"Erin Farley","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Jo","zip":"02149","message":"I bike from Everett to Charlestown and can't count the number of close calls I've had on Alford and Rutherford Streets. My husband bikes to the parcel 12 building & was hit and had his ankle broken by a careless driver. I dread him riding into Boston because your administration has rolled back the safe bike lines that he used to rely on. Please do something before more people are hurt or killed."},{"name":"Abigail Caruso","zip":"02132","message":"I’m sorry for your loss as well, Mayor Wu."},{"name":"Elias Karikas","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Lucas Orwig","zip":"02119","message":"I commute by bike regularly from Roxbury into the Seaport. Biking is faster and healthier than any other travel option. On almost every trip I am forced out of the bike lane by cars parked illegally. I'd like to be able to continue biking without having to worry about my safety so often. When bikers are safer drivers and pedestrians are safer too.Please help us all get home to our families safely!"},{"name":"Rachel Whooten","zip":"02144","message":"As someone who is both a mother and a pediatrician- I rely on biking to get my kids around - it is the only way I can efficiently and economically get around a city where parking, traffic, and public transportation have their unique challenges. I implore you to do more to make our streets safer!!"},{"name":"Matt Bowman","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Nicholas Chieffo","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Avery Marcus","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Michaela Thompson","zip":"02130","message":"There are barely words to express my disgust. Shame on you for letting this happen. It's very clear to anyone paying attention that you're already preparing for your next political move up the ladder, but you're our mayor right now, and you 're accountable to your constituents. Do. Your. Job."},{"name":"Benjamin Grey","zip":"02135"},{"name":"David Hawley","zip":"02143","message":"Even fresh paint on the most exposed bike lanes would make a huge difference."},{"name":"Emily Bloomenthal","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Louise Johnson","zip":"02130","message":"Please stop this killing"},{"name":"Adrienne Langlois","zip":"01970"},{"name":"Emma Soucy","zip":"02130","message":"I feel that Mayor Wu has abandoned her base by sacrificing her core campaign issues and our lives to selfish politicking and advancement of her own career. She frankly doesn't deserve any more votes from any of us until she does what she purportedly set out to do as mayor and prioritizes the people in this city rather than her own political and reputational machinations."},{"name":"Aman Shankardass","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Amara Good","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Lucie Torrey","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Aisha Farley","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ryan Bateman","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Sarah Minkin","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Sean Kolczynski","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Alan Wright","zip":"02131","message":"Car driving, with average of 1.1 passengers per car & avg 3.5 miles, not only kills & injures people but also is destroying Earth. It is largest source of unnecessary CO2 emissions. Louisa understood this & devoted herself so that everyone could have a better future. Requiring car ownership to participate in economy is a social injustice. Congestion pricing w $ going to public transit is solution."},{"name":"Jonathan Foster-Moore","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Kathryn Riley","zip":"02130","message":"I am often a pedestrian and sometimes a driver.  It’s bad out there, Mayor Wu."},{"name":"Bekka Wright /Bikeyface","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Barnabas furth","zip":"02186"},{"name":"Gina Palino","zip":"90803","message":"Hello Mayor,\n\nThough I am no longer a Boston resident, I was a classmate of Louisa’s and still visit the city to see family and friends. This petition is well thought out and specific. I urge you to make these changes. Best, Gina Palino. Boston Latin School class of 2008"},{"name":"Christine Varriale","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Deborah Perry","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Megan Saunders","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Angela Gile","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Pichet P","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Frank LaNasa","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Mae Tobin-Hochstadt","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Melissa Quinones","zip":"02131","message":"Im so sad and sorry for this loss."},{"name":"Alena Zhirova","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Laura Honeywood","zip":"02132","message":"Oof.\nI bike to work every week - so does my wife who works in your office and our son who is 8. \nThis is so frightening - especially to those of us trying to make the whole world safer by cutting pollution. \nThanks for all you do. Hope you get enough support to justify prioritizing this."},{"name":"Joseph Hess","zip":"02115","message":"It’s a daily hazard. Do your job and fix it."},{"name":"Lena Rogow","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Tom E","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Virginia marcotte","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Anne Rose Dearing","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jana Pickard-Richardson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Olivia Huang","zip":"02130","message":"Biking is undeniably how I live in Boston. It's the best way to be in the city and explore it; I love biking as transportation and want everyone to share in it.  But I can't in good faith recommend it to others knowing it requires too much bravery. There are too many things to look out for in terms of safety and road rules (official and unofficial), biking Boston is not beginner friendly at all."},{"name":"Carrie McGuire","zip":"02474","message":"Do more now to make streets safer for bikers and walkers who work, live and visit the city. There are so many dangerous intersections where cars are given go ahead to turn into streets with walk signals. Enough!"},{"name":"Charlotte Rogg","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Jeanne Yeh","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Henry Cohen","zip":"02131","message":"Be strong and be bold, save lives. Be on the right side of history and make your mark on the city."},{"name":"Katherine Buckland","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Nancy Ryan","zip":"02130","message":"I am devastated at losing Louisa and also totally spooked and scared about biking in this city. I bike commuted by Roxbury Crossing in the aftermath of this accident. Please take the action you should’ve taken years ago to prevent this."},{"name":"Anna Daniels","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Madi Wachman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Danya Sherman","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Michael Rogove","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Dennis Byrne","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Dylan Landfear","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Sarah Anders","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Slater Clay","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Samuel Osborn","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Ben Cohen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Robert stevens","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Elizabeth Duane","zip":"02130","message":"I've been struck by a car while on a bike in boston nearly two years ago. My life and my career were nearly ended, but I lived. And I came back to Boston because I love and believe in this city. Please, do right by us."},{"name":"Danielle Barmash","zip":"02130"},{"name":"MaryGrace Menner","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ariana V Olson","zip":"02139","message":"Mayor Wu,\n\nI did not Louisa personally, but I am a member of the cycling advocacy community and know many people who did, and she was so loved and respected. Tonight, I attended a vigil at the site of her killing. We stood by the intersection you paused safety improvements on. I wish you'd been there to feel the consequences of your decision. Please do better, quickly."},{"name":"Ali Yuliya","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Heather Govern","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Eileen Bolinsky","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Zoe Marsiglia","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Justin Lindner","zip":"02131","message":"Please stop stalling and make our streets safer"},{"name":"Lily Pratt","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Lani Weil","zip":"02143","message":"Listen to voices of those who care about all our citizens, not just those with privilege."},{"name":"Erin K. Stabile","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Lia Marcoux","zip":"02144","message":"I'm sorry for your loss. It sounds like Louisa Gag was a really wonderful person."},{"name":"Grace Bachman","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Kaydee Vraspier","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Julia Leach","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Mikayla lewis","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Sam S","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Annie Shapiro","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Cristina Cuji","zip":"02119","message":"Please do not let perfect be the enemy of good when it comes to reviewing street safety projects. If we truly want a city where motor vehicles are not the only way to get around, we need to ensure cyclists and pedestrians can reach home alive. Some residents will inevitably be annoyed with having to slow down, share with cyclists etc., but if they save a life, they are well worth it."},{"name":"Nikunj Khetan","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Amy Cantor","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Karti Subramanian","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Alexander Shames","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Patrick Norton","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Leila Simon Hayes","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ariel Hecht","zip":"02210"},{"name":"Jose da Silva","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Karen Marmon","zip":"02143"},{"name":"John Perich","zip":"02163"},{"name":"Evangeline Furth","zip":"02131","message":"I live and teach in Roslindale — I think your kids, Mayor Wu, go to the elementary school at the end of my street. I know you care about this issue as much as I do, but I also know you can do more. I’m a biker, and I’m becoming a scared biker. Please fight for us"},{"name":"Colleen H Moore","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Charlie Creagh","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Alexandra Diamond","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Joanna Karbel","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jason Hitt","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Isabelle Despins","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Walter Thavarajah","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Leann Canty","zip":"02130","message":"Please, let’s take action so there is not another senseless tragedy."},{"name":"Sean McKenna","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Jessamin Yu","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Liz Kehler","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Holly Hansen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jackie Peterson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"MK Moskowitz","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Catherine Pilsmaker","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Daniel Vernick","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Daniel Finley","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Adam Zhu","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Jennifer Uhrhane","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Elinor Karlsson","zip":"02139"},{"name":"William Wallace","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Paige Boehmcke","zip":"02130","message":"My home on Hyde Park Ave was hit by a truck traveling 50 mph. How many more crashes are acceptable before the City decides our lives are worth protecting? After four studies and years of broken promises, nothing has changed. Stop studying. Fix Hyde Park Ave before another person dies."},{"name":"Kylie Burnham","zip":"02130","message":"Biking is my main way of getting around this city. Nearly every day, I encounter a dangerous situation that a safer street project could remedy. As a resident of Boston, I hope to see this taken seriously by my elected officials before more avoidable tragedy."},{"name":"Sina Mansouri","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Deniz Ceviz","zip":"02467"},{"name":"Lauren C","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Gabriella Romano","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Jerry Zhou","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Edward Alexander","zip":"02130","message":"Boston has a real opportunity to lead the way on street safety in america"},{"name":"Kara Stoever","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Aaron Greiner","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Vasil Pendavinji","zip":"02453"},{"name":"Sara O'Brien","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Samantha Diamond","zip":"11385"},{"name":"Allan Lewis","zip":"02110"},{"name":"Eli Ehrlich","zip":"02215","message":"I want to be able to safely ride my bike to school every day."},{"name":"Keihly Moore","zip":"02130"},{"name":"James Billman","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Theodore Heinrich","zip":"02130","message":"Safe bicycling makes my life - our lives in the city better. Please fund safe bike lanes. Deprioritize cars in favor of public transit.\n\nMBTA For the Win"},{"name":"Chiara Ma","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Hope Duke","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Evan Moorman","zip":"02121"},{"name":"Amy Littlefield","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Fiona Barnett","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Alison Hamlin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Elizabeth Hartford","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ryan Burke","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Robert M Fagan","zip":"01730","message":"ACT, please, all five of the above. Now."},{"name":"Malia French","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emily Fogg","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Cameron Turchetti","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Pooyan Tirandazi","zip":"02128"},{"name":"George Jakob Beierlein","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Hayden Seager","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Saul Tannenbaum","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Hilary Detmold","zip":"02121"},{"name":"Kevin Outterson","zip":"02215","message":"I cross the BU bridge every day. Some of Comm Ave is safe on the BU campus, but much of it is not."},{"name":"Sarah Horsley","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ryan Snider","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Kate Nyhan","zip":"02446","message":"I'm not a Boston resident but I ride my bike in Allston, the Back Bay, Beacon Hill, downtown and the waterfront for healthcare, civic participation, shopping, and fun. Stop waiting for perfect consensus to happen and start leading. If people wanted platitudes and particulate matter from more cars, they could have supported Kraft."},{"name":"Jesse Keane","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Laura Grattan","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Arielle Trager","zip":"02453"},{"name":"Hilary Poriss","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Char Ames","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Sarah Clapham","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Blair Nodelman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Paul yoo","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Mia S","zip":"02493"},{"name":"Paulie Peña","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Julia Hansen","zip":"02467","message":"Please honor Louisa by making our streets safer, starting now!"},{"name":"Matthew Jarrell","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Timothy Reardon","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Katie LaScaleia","zip":"02128"},{"name":"John Savoia","zip":"02130","message":"Not one more."},{"name":"Andrew Balmer","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Carley Ruemmele","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Cyrus Miceli","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Tatiana Mowry","zip":"02171"},{"name":"Nat Hamlin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Cait Donovan","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kristin Hamman","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Audrey White","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sofia Fleming","zip":"02143","message":"I’m an EMT who consistently sees patients, families and bystanders who are impacted by roadway injuries. In the summer we see so many bicyclist who are injured by motor vehicles. In EMS, we respond to a tragedy.  A true solution prevents these injuries before they happen. That is what the city has the power to do, to create infrastructure which saves patients from pain and  communities from loss."},{"name":"Russell Preston","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Valerie Sizhe Li","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Marshall Bushnell","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Nancy Lessin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Elizabeth","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Joel Pettigrew","zip":"02131","message":"Mayor Wu, Boston Citizens are more important than your soundbites on MSNBC. No more using Roslindale Sq as your victory backdrop until you’ve made it a pedestrian safe place"},{"name":"Liticia Avery","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Jesse Welty","zip":"02130","message":"Our household voted you into a second term based on your support of safer streets in Term 1. With the mandate you received in your re-election, we are surprised and saddened to see this about-face in policy. Simply put, we feel betrayed. This is a chance to earn back our vote and our trust. Your move, Madame Mayor."},{"name":"Morgan Tondreault","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Kiera Penpeci","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Henry Shales","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Meira Soloff","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Lisa Hiserodt","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Sean Hooley","zip":"02155","message":"Other cities are moving forward to make the streets safer for all users, in Boston under Wu we are moving backward, left behind."},{"name":"Amanda Major","zip":"01027"},{"name":"Philip Sequeira","zip":"02130","message":"Please"},{"name":"Brian Le","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Annabelle Marko","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Lauren Sava","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Edward Faulkner","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Stephanie Golas","zip":"02131","message":"Enough is enough, we demand safe streets for our children, families and neighbors."},{"name":"Molly Morley","zip":"02130","message":"You won your second term with over 93% of the vote. You have a mandate. Use it to make our streets safer instead of trying to appease to every single person. Endless studies and consultations are not making our streets safer and you will never win everyone over to your side. But right now you’re losing your base because of your indecision on street safety."},{"name":"Sara Putnam","zip":"01906"},{"name":"Sarah Kaputa","zip":"02115","message":"Im a student who bikes to work and school every day.  Daily I deal wirh angry drivers who cut me off and dont follow the rules of the road.  Protect us protect the kids protect the bikes protect the pedestrians."},{"name":"Bobby Olsen","zip":"01095"},{"name":"Speed Elliott Estebo","zip":"02114","message":"Fund protected (by concrete - not paint, zicla zebras, or flex posts) bike lanes now to save lives and avoid preventable killings, like the killing of Louisa."},{"name":"Anne Kazarnovsky","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Kevin Bogle","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Cianna Navarro","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Susan Trotz","zip":"02130","message":"I bike and do not feel it is safe to travel in  bike lanes on the road. I will only bike on dedicated bike lanes off-road."},{"name":"Brianna Sullivan","zip":"02155","message":"It’s too late for Louisa. Please act before it’s too late for others."},{"name":"G. Tucker","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Lindsay Partin","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Wade Campbell","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Franklin Ollivierre","zip":"02120","message":"The people of Boston have overwhelming supported you because of your bold visions for improving street safety for cyclists and pedestrians. Unfortunately, it has been clear that you have been influenced by voices who do not care about improving the quality of life in Boston for your political gain. It has very been disappointing to witness over the past couple of years.  Please do better!!"},{"name":"Iolando Spinola","zip":"02301"},{"name":"Sarah Wolozin","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Dr. Ari Belathar","zip":"02130","message":"The argument for and against safe streets has four sides: those fighting to protect parking spaces, the media framing tragedies like this one as “inevitable accidents,” you protecting your political ambitions, and advocates, like Louisa, fighting to protect the safety of all road users. Do the right thing!"},{"name":"Leo Byers","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Rick Pinchera","zip":"02131","message":"I helped the Wu campaign by collecting signatures and rallying to get the vote out. This is where my enthusiasm wavers - we need advocates to make real change on the issue of pedestrian and cyclist safety. We hosted the World Cup and the Tall Ships. It’s past time we did something about preventable resident deaths."},{"name":"Adrienne Rosenblatt","zip":"02118"},{"name":"J Carroll","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jack Eccles","zip":"02113"},{"name":"Dorothy Fennell","zip":"02130","message":"Now is a time to deeply reflect and rethink what we need for a “families” first policy, how we move through our communities is and specifically transportation is fundamental to those policies , it’s time to put families first and make our streets safe, no matter what vehicle you are in or on"},{"name":"Bryce Willey","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Giulia Fleishman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Seth Davis","zip":"02130","message":"Do it for my kids and wife who travel by bike, on foot and on transit together or independently every day"},{"name":"Olivia Hull","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Martha Hrdy","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Rev Martha Niebanck","zip":"02131","message":"Please address unsafe conditions for bike riders."},{"name":"Catherine Whitney","zip":"02760"},{"name":"Theo Belmont","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Hilary Law","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Miles Van Denburg","zip":"02130","message":"I know you have others to answer to and the portion of people who bike in Boston is a sliver of your voting base but this was an avoidable death. An easily avoidable death. And right now - you could cement your name as the person who saved lives."},{"name":"Xiomara Lorenzo","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Chase Duffin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Mindy Fried","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Lauren HEFFERON","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Remy Morrison","zip":"02472","message":"You need to live up to your promises."},{"name":"Olivia Hamlin","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Margaux Leonard","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Lauren","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Grace Riordan","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Paul Rhodes III","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Nahlia Yefet","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Elise Largesse","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Emma Rose Rainville","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Matthew Proctor","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Amrit Pilo","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Chris O'Neill","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Ryan Kelso","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Robbie Havdala","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Katherine L","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Mel Ea","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Vio T","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Nicholas Zamboldi","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Elizabeth Jo-Anne Wyndham","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Carrie Callahan","zip":"02452"},{"name":"Madeline Webster","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Jared Gottdiener","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Mike O’Brien","zip":"02130","message":"We all have horror stories riding and walking around Boston. Hyde Park Ave has one straightaway where excessive speeding takes place, the least you could do is speed trap at these zones. But enough is enough, bikes over cars, people can drive 20 mph if they love their cars so much."},{"name":"Johanna Hunt","zip":"02120"},{"name":"James Adam Thorsell","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Vijay Fisch","zip":"02215","message":"Please, as a Bostonian who bikes go work every day, it could not be more important to me to live in a safe community for cyclists."},{"name":"Emma Cayen","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Nurus Chowdhury","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Nicole Nordeste","zip":"02118","message":"I rode a bike in Boston for 6 years and got hit once per year even tho I followed all the laws. I had lights and I wore a helmet. I used hand signals and stopped for signs and lights. Boston needs to increase its safety measures for cyclists."},{"name":"Devika Mujgule","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Wil Thomason","zip":"02141"},{"name":"William Lewis","zip":"02131","message":"I have stopped cycling in the city because I don’t feel safe doing so. I wish the infrastructure was safer to protect everyone on the roads."},{"name":"Catherine Oconnor","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Sarah Wides","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Maia Erslev","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Jeffrey Kaufman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Mike Condon","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Jennifer Licht","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Mariele Ventrice","zip":"02131","message":"Please take action to make streets safe for everyone. Your words are not enough."},{"name":"Sophia Neirman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kong","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Samantha Paulsen","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Kate DeBeul","zip":"02111","message":"We shouldn’t have to beg for safe streets for ALL."},{"name":"Elizabeth Rose","zip":"01833","message":"My daughter, age 35, who lives in Allston, rides her bicycle to and from work in Brookline and Somerville many days. I fear for her safety if the streets aren’t made safer for all pedestrians and bicyclists."},{"name":"Austen Boodell","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Rachel Pac","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Josh Levinger","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Josie Swift","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Dinah Satinsky","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Madalen Bigsby-Licht","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Nadia Bell","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Ellery Klein","zip":"02155","message":"As someone from Medford, I was excited to see real leadership on this issue coming from Boston. And have felt betrayed as it has been rescinded. Now friends of mine that knew Louisa are grieving.\n\nI was almost killed on my bike recently by a pickup truck driver that was texting and driving and turning left at high speeds- on my son’s high school graduation day. We deserve better than this."},{"name":"Gerry Manacsa","zip":"02130","message":"I've been appreciative of the quick progress on street safety made in the early years of your first administration. I feel personally safer as a cyclist, pedestrian, and drive due to those street improvements. I hope that we can begin to move forward again and avoid senseless tragedies like the one that befell Louisa and her loved ones."},{"name":"Matthew Reece","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Ashley Yung","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Dana Skelly","zip":"02126"},{"name":"Lillian Worth","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Alisha Werry","zip":"02120","message":"As a resident of Mission Hill who commutes on Tremont and Parker almost daily, it breaks my heart and frightens me to hear what happened to Louisa. Loss of life at this intersection was almost inevitable given the unsafe cycling confirms here, which stretch across almost all of Tremont and Parker, as well as most of Huntington Ave. We deserve to feel safe in our streets and neighborhoods."},{"name":"Bruce Rockwell","zip":"01118"},{"name":"Elizabeth Sohn","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Darrah Bowden","zip":"02145","message":"My heart breaks for Louisa’s loved ones and close colleagues. She has really made the ultimate sacrifice. Bicycle advocates know all too well that a preventable death is what it takes to get the safety improvements we’ve been calling for. Why elected officials are willing to experience this painful lesson again and again is beyond me. Can Louisa’s death be the last one?"},{"name":"Eileen M Velez","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Andrew D. Murray","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Marcia Peters","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Diane S. Wisniewski","zip":"01902"},{"name":"Edmund Charles Burr III","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Olivia Ensalata","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sung Hoon Jung","zip":"02151"},{"name":"Marjorie Charney","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Adam Klauber","zip":"02130","message":"Our neighbor Cambridge has shown us it is possible to elevate street safety and economic vibrancy."},{"name":"Brandon Sullivan","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Rikki Tan","zip":"02143","message":"Please also stop selling out and over-investing in law enforcement and militarizing Boston. Clearly that money should be redirected to safer streets, public housing, climate relief, and improving social/educational infrastructure for communities in need."},{"name":"Tammi Chen","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Mitchell DiPanni","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Rob B","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Susan Spilecki","zip":"02124","message":"I like that you take the T with other riders to know how slow it can be. I like that you walk in the Pride parade, so you know how bad some of our downtown streets are. Now you really need to work for the commuters who are risking their lives to get to and from work"},{"name":"John David Rudie Jr","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Shandi Foulger","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Christopher Bailey","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Dianna Bronchuk Duran","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Corey Purcell","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Kate Hanks","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Bjorn Sparrman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Liam Morley","zip":"02130","message":"I’ve lived in Boston for several years now, and I dread taking my bike out. I’ve been hit by drivers not paying attention, I’ve been boxed in by police cars that stopped to talk to each other, I’ve narrowly avoided car doors that open into bike lanes. And I’ve watched you walk back bicycle safety on the streets I live on. Please be a force for change, make sure this doesn’t happen again."},{"name":"Christina Lau","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Jillian Harrington","zip":"02120","message":"Enough is enough."},{"name":"Matt Kaye","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Mia Scholes","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Parth Kabra","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Alexander Otten","zip":"02135","message":"I had a lot of faith in you in the previous term when I moved into the city. Your improvements made me confident enough to try city biking for the first time. Now you’ve backtracked on your street safety promises and one of those unfulfilled promises has gotten someone killed. This city deserves better and I and my community will remember next election when we choose who leads us."},{"name":"Sarah Freeman","zip":"02130","message":"Please put safety improvements back on track."},{"name":"Joanna Ware","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sarah Jansen","zip":"02143","message":"I used to admire your political work. But why did you surrender a project for our individual and collective survival to conservative voters? \nWe cannot go on letting dangerous and polluting cars shape what our cities are like. We cannot go on letting  drivers decide where we can move and congregate safely and sustainably. We want to live."},{"name":"Natalie Ng","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Theo Guilfoy","zip":"02128","message":"Get police out of their cars and onto the streets."},{"name":"Rayne Skillin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kyle Chernoff","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Simar Singh","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kalpa S.","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Jacob Brodeur","zip":"01507"},{"name":"Lens Webb","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Eric Chappell","zip":"02452","message":"Mayor Wu, please stop backsliding here. My life and safety are at risk because I work, walk, and ride in Boston.\nI'm angry and sad your colleague died, and I hope you feel responsibility for your stalled corrections that could mitigate further losses like Louisa's."},{"name":"Sarthak Shaha","zip":"02150"},{"name":"Malcolm Ragan","zip":"02128"},{"name":"KAM","zip":"03301"},{"name":"Lynnae Terrill","zip":"02119","message":"You were elected with a mandate—and handily defeated a wealthy man who made his opposition to bike lanes a central tenet of his campaign. PLEASE GOVERN ACCORDING TO THE WILL OF THE PEOPLE WHO SENT YOU BACK TO CITY HALL. You are charged as mayor to protect and care for Boston’s residents. Please do so, by enacting these measures immediately!"},{"name":"Maya Gelbard","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Michael H","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kate Grosslein","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kate Rooney","zip":"02120","message":"Cycling is how I get to class, to work, to home. The people of Boston have a right to live safely, freely, in community without fear. We carry a heavy heart for those who are, or were, victims of a system that has a clear solution. Achieve that solution now:  enough is enough."},{"name":"Jayne Goethe","zip":"02144","message":"Please let’s make Boston the premier cycling and pedestrian-prioritized major city in North America. The Netherlands course-corrected in the 1970s from a car-dominant society. We can do this now—too late for Louisa, but not for the rest of us. Mayor—please ACT NOW! Please no more preventable traffic violence in Boston."},{"name":"Hsin Huei Chen","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Sefira Bell-Masterson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kathleen Harris","zip":"02170","message":"Thank you for caring Mayor Wu. I live in Quincy MA but grew up in West Roxbury. Thanks for knowing that protected bike lanes save lives."},{"name":"Makayla Hilberman","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Marie-Laure Grimaldi-Marvel","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Hillary Till","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Cory Williams","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Kyle Costello","zip":"02130","message":"Too much nonsense for too long, Mayor Wu. Blood is on your hands!"},{"name":"Deacon S Marvel","zip":"02130","message":"Dear Mayor Wu,\nIt is imperative that you make Bike safety a top priority in the remainder of your term.\nThank you,\nDeacon Marvel"},{"name":"Tomas Persson","zip":"02474"},{"name":"James Jenkins","zip":"02130","message":"Sick of this"},{"name":"Abigail Kruegle","zip":"02359"},{"name":"Arpit Jain","zip":"02210","message":"Please please please heed our voices"},{"name":"Alison Safford","zip":"02130","message":"Let us lead in this area too. It is really simple. Bodies before machines."},{"name":"Valerie Poulos","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Michael Winston","zip":"02119","message":"I unfortunately saw the aftermath of the incident, at which another cyclist operating his bicycle safely was almost hit by the crime scene truck arriving to the scene driving opposite traffic."},{"name":"Andee Krasner","zip":"02130","message":"We know you are committed to making our City safer for everyone. We hope you will move quickly to improve street safety for walkers and cyclists."},{"name":"Lukas Kruegle","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Daniel Massimino","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Emma Yudelevitch","zip":"02138","message":"I work in Downtown Crossing and I want to feel safe walking and biking to work. Louisa was part of my book club and will be missed."},{"name":"Mike DiMaio","zip":"02118","message":"It is heartbreaking for Louisa’s life to be cut so short on the type of dangerous roadway she worked so hard to improve. Rather than further Louisa’s work to make streets like Tremont safer, the City has removed nearly all existing bike lane protection and ceased nearly all improvements. The dangers on our streets are terrifying, and the work needed is obvious. Please prioritize street safety."},{"name":"Kristel Hunt","zip":"10710"},{"name":"Eleanor Auerbach","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Simon Gerzina","zip":"01915"},{"name":"Claire Sygiel","zip":"01082"},{"name":"Kristin Dwan","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Terrence Harris-Hughes","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Marc Jean-Louis","zip":"02121"},{"name":"Joseph Mullin","zip":"02118","message":"Boston’s record on transit safety is abysmal. So sad a young person and advocate for progress has died as a result of the mayor’s gross negligence. It’s past time to take the safety of all residents and visitors seriously. Please fix this mess ASAP."},{"name":"Ellie Dominguez","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Julia hopkins","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kyle Graesser","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Lindsay Allen","zip":"01338"},{"name":"Devin Nonnenman","zip":"02144","message":"I door knocked  for you when I lived in Boston, and one of the standouts of the start of your service as mayor was seeing you bike with constituents to work. Vision Zero needs to be re-prioritized."},{"name":"Andy Fox","zip":"10710"},{"name":"Caitlin Smits","zip":"02138"},{"name":"John Feidelson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Megan Swyter","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Kameron Kane","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sharon McGrath","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Sutton Kiplinger","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jessica Carless","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Elizabeth Vertina","zip":"02140","message":"I used to live in Jamaica Plain and ride my bike to work and home. I now live in Cambridge. I have been hit by cars on 2 different occasions where I had a green light and they turned right into me as I crossed the intersection. One collision gave me a concussion that took me a year to recover from. Yes I wore a helmet. These safety initiatives aren’t just for fun. People’s lives are at stake."},{"name":"Alex Frieden","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Benjamin Bovell-Ammon","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Adam Shutes","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Ken Sazama","zip":"02130","message":"This is embarrassing! Why did you change so much on your policy bikes? Stop costing the lives of our residence in Boston."},{"name":"Sean Donaghy","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Amanda Henson","zip":"04105","message":"Dear Mayor Wu, my twin sons work, live, and cycle regularly in Boston and I worry about their safety all the time. As a student at BU in the early 80s, I was impacted by the death of a student riding her bike. Sadly, Louisa’s death was not an anomaly - rather  it is an all too frequent reality. Please prioritize pedestrian and bike safety so this type of tragedy never happens again. Thank you,"},{"name":"Blake Stover","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Pilar G","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Natalie Karlsson","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Greg Tobin","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Nathan Kastner","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Cassie Toby","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Claudia Robaina Winston","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Anne Kaufman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Hannah Hudson","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Sophia Herscu","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Daniel Patterson","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Jennifer Wyman","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Sylvia Lustig","zip":"02474","message":"Please, please take action and do not just say words. It is becoming more terrifying to bike in this city, but it is a critical mode of transit that we rely on. This death hits very close to home."},{"name":"Michael Orff","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Joseph Liu","zip":"02467","message":"I lived one block down at 1500 Tremont Street for 5 years. During this time I commuted with my bike and carried it up and down the stairs every day from my 3rd fl apt.\n\nEverytime I rode on Tremont Street I was especially aware of the dangers of distracted driving mixed with congested traffic, business deliveries, double parking, and the emergency response vehicles. This was PREVENTABLE"},{"name":"Christina Michaud","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Will Oliver","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Rebecca Froom","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Amanda Lapham","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ferit Albukrek","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Justin Kunimune","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Julia Danahy","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Aaron Chiou","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Jess Liborio","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Julia Himmelberger","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Timothy Traverse","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Neelabh Sharma","zip":"02467"},{"name":"Elizabeth Skaggs","zip":"02121","message":"If you actually cared about Louisa -and the loads of people you're meant to protect murdered by pampered, negligent drivers in this city- you'd act to protect people outside of cars.\nDo something more than just platitudes, act like a real mayor and make Boston better, AKA, inconvenience the damn drivers. \nClearly lives are at stake, and not just the ones that hurt your poor feelings personally."},{"name":"Silas Kotnour","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Leonardo Ruiz Sanchez","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Emily Gleitman","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Nat Talbot","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Olivia Iannini","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Sean Colsen","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Riva Pearson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Morgan Younkin","zip":"02122","message":"My family depends on you, mayor Wu, to make it possible for me to get home each day safety. Right now my wife is begging me to stop biking because things are demonstrably not safe and Louisa Gag, and experienced cyclist and advocate, is dead. It could have been me. \n\nPlease\nInvestigate and hold accountable the driver responsible for this\nRestart safer streets construction \nEnforce traffic laws"},{"name":"Jessica Ernst","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Kristin Johnson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Fable Scarborough","zip":"02155","message":"Delaying projects that make the city more equitable and livable keeps resulting in the injury and death of cyclists. I'm tired of living in a city where there's always more money for cops and developers, while every infrastructure project that could make this city safer and more liveable is met with delays and austerity. This tragedy could've been prevented, and we are heartbroken and furious."},{"name":"Rosy Hosking","zip":"02131","message":"Please please improve our streets for my children and yours, and for their children and all the future children of Boston."},{"name":"Andrew Papia","zip":"02125","message":"My son rides his bike to school on this route. Make the streets safe for him and all children in the city!"},{"name":"Brian Guarnotta","zip":"02130","message":"Yes you have done some great thing for cyclists, thank you, but let's do more."},{"name":"Lauren Kee","zip":"02459"},{"name":"Schuyler Pratt","zip":"02129","message":"This tragedy shines light on the lack of bike lane safety in our city. While there has been implementation of new bike lanes over the past few years, it does not seem there is consistency throughout the city. We need to do better. - Schuyler Pratt, cyclist from Charlestown, MA"},{"name":"Delaney Dameron","zip":"02210"},{"name":"Erin Markee","zip":"02130"},{"name":"John Wegner","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Leslie Euston","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Rachel Campbell Hipson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Anna Yugova","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Madeline Augustine","zip":"02108"},{"name":"Bryce Kieren Healy","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emma Batson","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Florence Ma","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Amanda Rychel","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Adrian","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Kathleen Meditz","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sky Rose","zip":"02143","message":"Her death was preventable."},{"name":"Colin Stergios","zip":"02145","message":"I work every day to make streets safer for biking. You should be, too."},{"name":"Matthew Swain Smith","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Mary Beth Ellis","zip":"01810","message":"My daughter Sidney was killed In preventable traffic violence. This movement can’t wait every day risks another senseless death - demand safer streets and safer vehicles now."},{"name":"Timothy Newell","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kaylee Gentry","zip":"01230"},{"name":"Cooper Evello","zip":"02131","message":"Please"},{"name":"Daniel Germain","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Stephen Mahood","zip":"02119","message":"I bike down this path on the regular and among many crossings the tremont one is dangerous and needs a better plan. In addition to others such as raised intersections to more discipline to drivers."},{"name":"Maty Cropley","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Bryson King","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Katie Cook","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Michael Gomez","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Lauren Peterson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Nikolas Shashok","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Camryn Given","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kate Paladin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ligia Fragoso","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Nathan Watts","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Michael Soha","zip":"02119","message":"Every stalled project raises the likelihood of another Louisa. If Louisa couldn’t bike safe in our city, nobody can. We need action now!"},{"name":"Mitchell Dalvi Rosen","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Colin Whooten","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Andrew Giannino-Curtis","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Eben Haines","zip":"02210","message":"Every day I have at least one near miss from a speeding driver staring at their phone, whether on a bike or in a crosswalk. Every new speedometer the city has placed on the side of the road is constantly flashing “slow down”, missing bollards have turned bike lanes back into parking spots. How many more people we love have to die, because you’re afraid to impinge upon the convenience of drivers?"},{"name":"Sibi Ramachandran","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Eliza Passell","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Amanda Cegielski","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Jacob null","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kevin Smith","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Derek DuPont","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Jennifer McCloskey","zip":"02131","message":"Will my child be next? You know we all bike to school, to school with your kids. We shouldn’t be afraid to do so. Please take real action."},{"name":"Robert Couture","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Emily Patel","zip":"02420"},{"name":"Lexi Feldman","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Brian Aldrich","zip":"02478","message":"Please work to get our police to begin enforcing the laws we already have on the books. Anyone spending more than 5 minutes watching traffic in Boston will observe dozens of violations, most dangerous. You can watch all day and not see an officer take action. I've been told by a BPD officer that right on red through a pedestrian signal at 20mph with no stop was \"OK\". That's not OK and it never was"},{"name":"Barry Jaspan","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Rachel LaFlamme","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Liam Powers","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Julie Taberman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Carina Gold","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Daniella LeBlanc","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sydney Solages","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Neal Chaudhuri","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Terri-Lynn McCormick, Esq.","zip":"02115","message":"I donated, canvassed and voted for you because you promised us safe streets. You have not delivered and have even backtracked. Cyclists and pedestrians aren't killing drivers. They are killing us. \nRadical change is needed now. No more baby steps."},{"name":"Phillip Soucy","zip":"02155","message":"How many more? Louisa's death was preventable. So many countries have demonstrated how to protect their pedestrians and cyclists from incredibly lethal cars. We can and need to do better, or accept deaths like that her's are the cost of delaying. How many more deaths will you accept to protect a few minutes on someone's commute?"},{"name":"Harry Bullivant","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Adam Slomovitz","zip":"02143"},{"name":"William C Cole-French","zip":"02125","message":"Mayor Wu - Where are you?"},{"name":"Jonas Herbst","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Katie Wells","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jeff Byrnes","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Callum Murphy","zip":"01801"},{"name":"Rebecca G","zip":"02453"},{"name":"Lila Smith","zip":"02143","message":"As a daily bicycle commuter into Boston, it’s shocking to see the difference in how much car traffic is prioritized over pedestrians/cyclists once you cross over the bridge from Cambridge"},{"name":"Guillermo Vargas","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Richard Van","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Daniel Jensen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Chris Armstrong","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ruan Oliveira","zip":"02130","message":"Deeply disappointed in your leadership. I had higher hopes for people from our generation, Mayor Wu."},{"name":"Samantha Brecht","zip":"02130","message":"I am a nurse, and cared for another pedestrian who was run over and dragged by an SUV just this week. By the time she entered my care she was on her 6th surgery. These are the streets I cross with my 2 small children under age 5. Luisa was on the very same bike commute my now pregnant wife takes to work. Our daycare provider has had 2 cars totaled when they were PARKED on Hyde park ave THIS YEAR."},{"name":"Kyle Ennis","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Lauren Cole-Osborn","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Cassidy Chang","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Matt Ball","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Kevin Torres","zip":"02720","message":"We should not be under the mercy of 2 ton death machines and their creators."},{"name":"Matt Baynes","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Olivia Carpenter","zip":"14850"},{"name":"Jamie Burke","zip":"02472","message":"Your political cowardice led to Louisa’s completely preventable death. Miles and miles of bike lanes have been left unprotected—lanes I travel each day to work or with my son, which are just paint or have missing bollards with seemingly no repair in sight. We deserve to get around safely and know our loved ones are coming home. Step up or end up with more blood on your hands."},{"name":"Katherine Franz","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sophie Arnstein","zip":"02467"},{"name":"Spencer Friedman","zip":"02135","message":"Everyone should have the right to feel equally safe in Boston streets"},{"name":"Avery Houston","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Patricia Cartwright","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Jeremy Szteiter","zip":"02131"},{"name":"William L Elsbree","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Andrew McFarland","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Joseph Delle Donne","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Anika Rabenhorst","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Patrick Cleary","zip":"02478"},{"name":"Paige McKissock","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emily Stein","zip":"02155","message":"A beautiful light was just extinguished, senselessly, traumatically, and painfully. These deaths are all preventable. Please act now."},{"name":"Theo McGrath","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Lindsay Warner","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sasha Zeidenberg","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emily Pease","zip":"02131","message":"Please make our streets safe before more of our neighbors are killed!"},{"name":"Kmnuge","zip":"02359","message":"My children live in Boston. I’m writing to support keeping them safe as they try to ease the gridlock of cars in town. They fear riding on the streets. There are so many models of great infrastructure around the world supporting cyclists and pedestrians. The result of these changes would make our city a much more pleasant place in so many ways."},{"name":"Molly McGovern","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Zach Ryan","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Aidan Boni","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Tina Chan","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Kate S","zip":"02130","message":"Louisa should still be here"},{"name":"Brooke Ashleigh","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Kate Nash","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Erica Lu","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Matthew Kohler","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Spencer Phillips","zip":"02111"},{"name":"John Ventura","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Adrian Vanegas","zip":"02120","message":"I live feet away from where Louisa was killed. The sight was terrifying and heartbreaking. I pray for her the family and loved ones, and that our Boston administration makes changes to prevent such tragedies."},{"name":"Sadie Luehman","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Anna Littlehale","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Carrie Schultz","zip":"01982"},{"name":"Andrew Glaude","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Eric Herot","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Josh Hoxie","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Seb Kryspin","zip":"02139","message":"You can make change happen. Please, do it. I don't want anyone else to die."},{"name":"Kayla Monks","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Santiago  Lopez","zip":"02143","message":"Streets in Somerville are full of holes and incredibly dangerous for cyclists, plus crime is spiking so much everywhere in Boston."},{"name":"Dougie Szeto","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Anne Holstein","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emma Richards","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Elaine McCauley Meehan","zip":"02135","message":"Louisa's death was preventable. We need separate bike paths that aren't sharing space with F250 trucks. We need bike paths that are raised and set back from the street. It will be better for automobile drivers and pedestrians. PLEASE, do not let Louisa's life work die with her. Boston is made for people to be outside and moving around. Do the right thing, and honor Louisa Gag by making us safer."},{"name":"Deepti Kannan","zip":"02143","message":"I used to commute by bike in Cambridge but now that I work in Seaport, I stopped biking on the Boston side of the river because of the poor quality of roads, the lack of bike lanes, and the ruthlessness of Boston drivers. We need more bike lanes and bike safety measures!"},{"name":"Matthew Dezii","zip":"02135","message":"My friend is gone. We can no longer say, “I don’t know how this happened,” because we do know. Safety improvements have been nonexistent for almost 2 years. We can make this a safe city for those biking and walking. All you have to do is build it. Please please please, I can’t lose another friend and community member to vehicular violence."},{"name":"Melody Spencer","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Cassie Dezii","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Elizabeth Allington Southerland","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Theresa DeLucia","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Liza Birch","zip":"02907"},{"name":"Fiona McQuade","zip":"02125","message":"I have been hit five times on my bicycle. I no longer bike commute because as a parent I know Boston's streets are not safe for my child. The BPD makes the choice to not enforce the bike lanes--I have asked numerous times. I insist the BPD must aggressively enforce the bike lane and ticket the drivers who park in it daily. Doing so, would help the city budget and make the streets safer."},{"name":"Karyn Donahue","zip":"02131","message":"Please do not cave to the pressure from the minority voice of residents who are antagonistic towards bike lanes and sharing the roads with bicycles. The future will include bicycles as a normalized means of transportation around the world. You can keep Boston at the forefront of this trend. Thank you!"},{"name":"Adam Mazo","zip":"02130","message":"We need safer streets so that all people can live!"},{"name":"Lawrence E","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Will Rhatigan","zip":"02144","message":"You have the power to save lives—and to end them if you don’t act. Please unpause street safety projects before someone else you know is hurt."},{"name":"John Coiner","zip":"02474"},{"name":"James Cordero","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Alea Stokes","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Libby James","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Ryan McClain","zip":"02186"},{"name":"Rachel Landers","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Lucia Ahearne","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Dory Klein","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Eliza Sparkes","zip":"02126"},{"name":"Kayla Santana","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Nicola Roux","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Matthias Iris Remillard","zip":"02144","message":"If you do nothing, Louisa's death will mean nothing. What will actually get you to act?"},{"name":"Juju Robinson","zip":"30009","message":"My adult kids ride their bikes daily (no car) and a friend of mine tragically lost her life near Cambridge a few years ago - struck by a box car. Do better Wu"},{"name":"Paul Morgan","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Kirpal Demian","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Dan Totten","zip":"02139","message":"Do your job."},{"name":"Amy Shen","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Katharine Nash","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Chelsea Kryspin","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Fen Portmann Katz","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Travis Johnston","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Maegan Hurley","zip":"02121","message":"I used to commute to work every day from Somerville to the North End by bike. Then I moved to Dorchester in 2022. I continued to commute by bike for about one year. But close call after close call made me realize how incredibly dangerous it is to ride a bike on the Boston streets. I loved riding my bike. But I wasn't willing to risk my life anymore. Please make the streets safer for everyone."},{"name":"Lucy Nadeau","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jo Melita","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Sara Muspratt","zip":"02132","message":"Mayor Wu,\nThis unnecessary death of an unusually dedicated employee is terrible. You have an opportunity to make sure her work is carried on. Please, please, seize it."},{"name":"Carmel Levy","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jason Chin","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Lucas Good","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Ellie Medal","zip":"02143"},{"name":"John Kryspin","zip":"01887"},{"name":"Brice Green","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Rachel Graham","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Sydney Adreon","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Nathaniel Dvorkin","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Gloria Huangpu","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Diana Marsh","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Anne-Marie Barron","zip":"02186"},{"name":"Amy Flax","zip":"02138","message":"The time is now. Protect all people. I am a senior and love to get around on a bike. It feels so\nScary !"},{"name":"Perri Sheinbaum","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Gaia Di Bernardini","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Jazmin Cole","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Dorothy Farrell","zip":"02130","message":"I voted for you twice.  Believed in you. Now you must earn my trust. Please do the right thing and make our streets save in Louisa’s name and her hope for a better Boston"},{"name":"Dawn Oates","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Keith Marcotte","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Audrey Chu","zip":"02130"},{"name":"David Robinson","zip":"02130","message":"Mayor Wu, \n\nI bike this corridor to work each day from JP to the South End that Louisa was killed. As a new parent of a newborn who I plan to bring on my bike I am scared about this daily commute. Please take action on safe streets now to prevent any more needless deaths.\n\n-David"},{"name":"Lauren Higgins","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Justine Portmann Katz","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Claire Geruson","zip":"02135","message":"My three-year-old and I bike to work and into school every day together. We are always wearing our helmets and always in the bike lanes, please help us stay safe."},{"name":"Alison Stokes Gottlieb","zip":"02130","message":"I knew Louisa's family well. Also this intersection. This tragic! We need action."},{"name":"Michael Sheridan","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Grace Coffelt","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Rebecca Wallach","zip":"02467"},{"name":"Ann Frantel","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jordan Huynh","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Max K","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Lauren Ockene","zip":"02130","message":"It is time to quit pandering  to noisy and drivers and their myopia. Protected bicycle lanes and traffic calming create a city that is safer for cyclist, pedestrians, and everyone.\n\nLouisa should not be dead.\n\nNo one else should die because our streets are not safe and because leaders listen more to anger and selfishness than data and facts  about public safety and the health of our communities.."},{"name":"Aliza Barnett","zip":"02130","message":"You said you wanted to fight for fast and free public transportation when Zohran was campaigning on that platform, but since your race, you haven't taken action. You say you want climate action in this city, but you've cut public works and haven't improved biking infrastructure. Improving city infrastructure and ensuring safety is central to your campaign promises. Please do better."},{"name":"Marcogianni Tromp","zip":"02113"},{"name":"Paul Flores","zip":"02141","message":"Please add protected bike infrastructure to the rest of Cambridge Street from the Longfellow Bridge to City Hall. This is a high volume bike commute route to downtown and the people who use it deserve safety and protection from dangerous drivers."},{"name":"Rocky Prull","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Orion Keierleber","zip":"02144","message":"Mayor Wu, my community voted for you because you campinged on a platform of making streets safer for people outside cars. Now you have stalled those projects, and people are dying. The blood of your constituency is on your hands."},{"name":"Maggie L.","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Donald M Neill","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Mark Duhaime","zip":"02130","message":"There are so many new intersections, mph restrictions, and newly drawn lanes to help with traffic patterns, but none of that is effective without proper enforcement. I’m not usually in support of more policing, but traffic enforcement, with officers at major intersections and along sensitive passages, would help everyone slow down and follow the rules for us all to be safer."},{"name":"Tom Love","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Kristen Ammons","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Kienan Blatchley-Martins","zip":"02446","message":"The level of reckless driving is astounding and police officers do nothing to stop it when it happens right in front of them. Infrastructure is sorely needed to fix what law enforcement won't, to ensure the lack of common sense exhibited in a remarkable number of drivers does not continue to kill our city's residents."},{"name":"Rey Tucker","zip":"02144","message":"Boston is easily the most dangerous city in the area. I avoid going there as much as possible because of the horrible lack of basic street safety. Tell this to your businesses when they ask why they're struggling."},{"name":"Jonathan Maitland Lauderdale","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Andrew Mayer","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Anya Guyer","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Marty Alani","zip":"02139","message":"I'm a Cambridge resident, but I rely on my bike to get all over the city, including the intersection where Louisa was killed. I often don't feel safe crossing the river into Boston because the infrastructure for bike safety is noticeably much worse than in Cambridge. Infrastructure improvements will help connect the Boston area by bike and make everyone safer."},{"name":"Mackenzie McCree","zip":"02743","message":"The loss of community members and pedestrian safety is inevitable without proper care for citizens well being. Please make our tax dollars invest in your average day Bostonians, not the rich and wealthy."},{"name":"Ace Leggett","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Joshua Decosta","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Hagar Shirman","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Jess Montgomery","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Anna P","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Nikhil Phatak","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Molly Jones","zip":"02130","message":"It's time to step up and show you care about the safety of our neighbors!"},{"name":"Zoe birnhak","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Matthew Hogan","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Lily Burger","zip":"02131","message":"We must make the streets safer for cyclists. This is not an option. Too many have died. As someone who commutes via public transportation because I cannot afford a car and live in this city, I myself am too scared to bike in Boston because we do not protect our cyclists enough. Cars should not rule the road. We must create more bike lanes and we must ENFORCE and RESPECT existing bike lanes."},{"name":"Adam Driscoll","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Erin Sutton","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Vinny Fieg","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Elizabeth Fieg","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Halle Chernin","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Kat Eshel","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Grace Julien","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Michael Plante","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Lileana Sethares","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Rachael DeCruz","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Isaac Klickstein","zip":"02113"},{"name":"Shawn Macmillan","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Edward Edwards","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Sara Wasserman","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Shannon Beatty","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Jane Ebersole","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Ivy Saltsman","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Jasmine Feng","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Joanna Tam","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Andrew Levine","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Nadege Le Goff","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Frederique Bienfait","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Aleksandra Jakubowski","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jeanette Beaute","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Jake DeGrace","zip":"02114"},{"name":"David J Reed","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Anna Kelley","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Gabbe Roseman","zip":"02118","message":"Biking and walking encourages a love for Boston through slow observation and community engagement. Let me love Boston safely."},{"name":"Jennifer Brundage","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Meg Galbreath","zip":"01028"},{"name":"Ray Porfilio","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Nathaniel Gabriel","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Jonathan Goldenberg","zip":"02131","message":"I live on Hyde Park Ave, a half mile from forest hills. A four lane road with parking on both sides without a bus or bike lane. A road, without a needed redesign, that has killed my neighbors and will kill again without a redesign. I should not fear for my life when I bike. Not one more preventable death."},{"name":"Liz Duda","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Brian Savage","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Jennifer Cheng","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Gabriel Bamforth","zip":"02135","message":"While demands 4 and 5 of this letter may not be reasonable nor feasible, I believe demands 1,2, and 3 are important for solving Boston's traffic issues and keeping everyone safe."},{"name":"Camila Diehl","zip":"02118","message":"In memory of Louisa"},{"name":"Taylor Cain","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Julian Vallen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Hanna Russell","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Seena M","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Josiah Siegel","zip":"02460"},{"name":"Seth Gadbois","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jennifer Chen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ryan Bryla","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Olivia Pietz","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Mary Vidal","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Emily Bahnsen","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Nicole Miller","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Evan Tschirhart","zip":"02130","message":"Beyond the above I would beg you to do more to ensure that traffic laws are followed in Bost. The number of cars that speed, or ignore red lights and zoom through an intersection, or drive aggressively to pass on narrow roads, has increased exponentially in the last 5 years. In addition to the structural and design issues that make streets safer we need to return to a culture of safe driving."},{"name":"Feyga Saksonov","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Nicolas Amato","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Quinton Celuzza","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Noah Crane","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Danielle Caisse","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Josh McLinden","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Josué Pérez Campos","zip":"02139","message":"I, as many commuters that go into downtown everyday, have witness the deterioration of your safe streets stance into an empty promise. The cancellation of ongoing safe street projects and the null enforcement of traffic laws makes your administration not dissimilar to Kraft’s car-centric campaign. This was preventable, how many more deaths are acceptable for you?"},{"name":"Daisy Chiu","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Charles T. James","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Drew Nelson, Community Pedal Power","zip":"02118","message":"Every day, Cambridge and Somerville are pulling me closer. The way I see it, Mayor Wu has two options: 1. Recommit to Vision Zero. 2. Lose every single truly progressive voter in this city to other cities fighting the good fight"},{"name":"Yashwant Kathirvel","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Zafira Smith","zip":"02120","message":"Cars have never and will never be productive to the quality of life anywhere. Especially not in this city. Prioritizing them bas never made sense."},{"name":"Sean Harris","zip":"01609"},{"name":"Jaime Kvaternik","zip":"02139","message":"As someone who’s been hit by a car once and avoided many near collisions, as well as seen hits or collisions by careless drivers, I wish Mayor Wu understands the severity of this incident and unblocks the road safety projects. I’d even go further to suggest investing in red light cameras/speed cameras to prevent rash, illegal driving behavior since cops don’t seem to always want to stop it."},{"name":"Teresa Harvey","zip":"01095"},{"name":"Eyob Solomon","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Miranda Briseño","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Mark Belzowski","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Mathew Hearl","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Robert G Stone","zip":"02130","message":"Aggressively and publicly prosecute dangerous driving. It’s sickening when “Boston driving” is used as a punchline when deaths like this occur"},{"name":"Maric Kramer","zip":"02478"},{"name":"Julia Martin","zip":"02478"},{"name":"Charlotte Bosworth-Miao","zip":"02138"},{"name":"David Carr Anderson","zip":"01890","message":"I have commuted by bike into Boston from Winchester every weekday, year-round since the Winter of 2015, when the trains stopped. Boston biking has improved since then but has recently stalled. As you know, Louisa was a far more skilled and conscientious rider than most, and the public roadways are not safe enough for her, or me, or you.  Let's work together to get that improvement back on-track."},{"name":"Tobias Roberts","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Margarita Montgomery","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Mona M","zip":"01238"},{"name":"Theresa Strachila","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sydney Rajchel","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Whitney O’Brien","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Koai Solano Ortiz","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Colin Boisvert","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Andrew Scott White","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Gabe Besecker","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Dylan Cleverly","zip":"02108"},{"name":"Audrina Warren","zip":"02128","message":"Smarter infrastructure is possible. I'd love to live in a city that understands how reckless policies and the dire state of the climate are connected. More work needs to be done to make a future where humans can live and move safely. So many groups have been doing incredible amounts of research on the actions that need to be taken immediately. Listen to them. Take Action Now."},{"name":"Indigo Longo","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Jilene Chua","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Julia Tuttle","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Brandon Cardley","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Hunter McLaren","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Sophie Ghitman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jennifer leblanc","zip":"02134","message":"How many lives need to be destroyed before people realize that making bike lanes NEEDS to be a priority. Safer lanes increase the public’s comfort biking, and will make our city more green and less polluted by gas and traffic. But we need to listen to the people who are highlighting the dangers and the areas that need improvement. Mayor Wu needs to show up."},{"name":"David Liu","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Elizabeth Feigenbaum","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Susanna Kemp","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Cecilia Menchetti","zip":"02130","message":"After living in Boston for 8 years, reckless drivers and the completely senseless tragedy they cause have me seriously considering moving out of the city. It doesn't have to be this way."},{"name":"Annie Cardley","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Madeline Kemp","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Derek McIntire","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Tor Olsson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Anne Boylan","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ryan Murphy","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Sean Cardwell","zip":"02135","message":"Please help protect us as we try to just live in this wonderful city."},{"name":"Kim Craig","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Joyce Quach","zip":"02140","message":"Please, Mayor Wu. We need change. We need to prevent further cyclist deaths. My friend’s friend passed away due to an accident."},{"name":"Cole N Townsend","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Catherine Armistead","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Roos","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Jessica wygoda","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Elizabeth Garfield","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Jacob Van Dine","zip":"02188"},{"name":"Adin Kugelmass","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Ally Milano","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Justina Cheng","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Gavin Sullivan","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Ariel Nelson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Finn Doyle","zip":"01890"},{"name":"Emily Lavy","zip":"02478"},{"name":"Nancy Sableski","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kassandra Silva","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Lilith Garcia","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Lilly gifford","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Lyric Jackson","zip":"02110"},{"name":"Nathaniel Brown","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Sarah Doyle","zip":"01890"},{"name":"Rickie Harvey","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Andrew Iliff","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Suzanne Birdsell","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Beth Derr","zip":"02130","message":"As a cyclist commuter, some streets on my commute have become much safer (the north/south-running section of Tremont, Congress St by post office square) - but there are still too many unprotected streets, segments of my route where I feel exposed and at risk. You have the power to change that. Don't let there be another Louisa."},{"name":"Ted Hansen","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Michael Weidenbruch","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Barrett Su","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jean Nolan","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Samuel Greenblatt","zip":"02130","message":"I specifically spoke to you at your recent Curtis Hall event. How many people have to die before Boston decides to actually make safe streets a priority? The time is now!"},{"name":"Miranda Briseño","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Nick Remillard","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Jorge Delgado","zip":"02458"},{"name":"Camilla Elvis","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Cecy Sweeney","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Paul Watkins","zip":"02130"},{"name":"MaryKate Murphy","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Yanira Santos","zip":"02130"},{"name":"S. Scharn","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Helen Horigan","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Melissa Teng","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Elaine Anderson","zip":"01890","message":"Please, please protect us!"},{"name":"William Huba","zip":"02482"},{"name":"Erica Mattison MPA, JD","zip":"02026"},{"name":"Drew S","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Brian Jordan","zip":"02130","message":"I have seen what this mayor can do when she puts her mind to it because I work in housing. She has done a lot for this city and had a strong start to her first term on transportation. I have also seen my neighbors lose faith in her commitment to street safety in Boston. I have not. Nonetheless, the mayor needs to act or these kinds of tragedies will keep happening. Prove me right."},{"name":"Jonathan Beesen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kenet Bickley","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Katarzyna Spitalniak","zip":"02169"},{"name":"Rawan AbuShanab","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Chloe/Clover Brown","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Marko Vučetić","zip":"02130","message":"You suck so much at your job. I am voting for literally any other Democrat next cycle. Maybe even a Republican because at least those people have the decency to be honest about how little they care about me."},{"name":"Mark Reczek","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Aisling Carlson","zip":"02138","message":"This should not be optional."},{"name":"Mary Brady","zip":"02130","message":"I’m the mom of cyclists who have biked across the United States with no accidents, but one was hit while walking her bike across the sidewalk at Green St next to the T station, and the other while biking down Pond St by a car turning left. \nCars hitting bicyclists should not be assumed as inevitable for my children, grandchildren, nor yours."},{"name":"Amory Sivertson","zip":"02169"},{"name":"Thomas Collet","zip":"02140","message":"I currently avoid trips into Boston, for example, for shopping because it is too dangerous to ride my bike in the city."},{"name":"Gina Kaufmann","zip":"02138","message":"I ride my bike when I can to reduce my reliance on cars and parking spots, which I do not believe in getting hung up on. I live in a city, not a suburb, for a reason. But I often feel unsafe and choose a car, and that feeling only grows with deaths like these. Please help greater Boston make community-minded decisions without fear."},{"name":"Victor Koran","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Janet Cheung","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Dan Bisers","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Robert Orthman","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Brad Mello","zip":"02916"},{"name":"Lilliana Lopera-Jimenez","zip":"02130","message":"Please make the streets safer. My brother is a biker"},{"name":"Matt DelSordo","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Lauren Arkema","zip":"02130","message":"The news of this meaningful person’s death is devastating and it seems so especially wrong she was lost in this very way. If there is any (and it’s clear there is) chance you can ensure a tragedy like this doesn’t ever happen again, then please take action. I know very dear people on this petition that have called out for so long… You must be heartbroken and grieving too… It’s time. No more."},{"name":"Elise Turner","zip":"02120","message":"lock in girl like please"},{"name":"Megan Mello","zip":"02916"},{"name":"Michele Choi","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Michael Vanseveren","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Mimi Clemens","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Ebelechiyem A Okafor","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Joseph Evans","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Ariella Ruth Goldberg","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Joel Checo","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Nilin Blann-Holley","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Amr Salem","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Ray-ray Carmona Farrales","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Lindsey Adams","zip":"02139","message":"I bike to work every day. As a graduate student I spend time in labs across Boston and Cambridge. Biking into the Longwood Medical Area continues to terrify me, because I risk my life to get to work."},{"name":"Emily Manning-Mingle","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Steven Ayr","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Anna Clemens","zip":"02215","message":"I am disappointed in how your lack of leadership has resulted in more dangerous streets in this city. Your choice to step back from street improvements has only made our city less safe and devalued modes other than driving. Your refusal to say “no” to drivers and community groups in the wrong has resulted in deaths like this one. Louisa did so much for Boston. She was a light, remember her."},{"name":"Lexy Lattimore","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Josh Tycko","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Lo Makechnie","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Clara Short","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Alex Kautz","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Elizabeth Rose","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Ryan Brenner","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Adam Oberstadt-Petrik","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Sarah Hastings","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Kiera Oconnor","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Nathan Wentworth","zip":"02143","message":"I live in Somerville but work in Boston and commute by bike every day, the difference between biking in Somerville/Cambridge and Boston is unreal. Prioritizing \"consensus\" from car drivers will only cause more pedestrian and cyclist deaths."},{"name":"Catherine Abel","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Kathryn Aucella","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Max Schlecht","zip":"02142"},{"name":"Andrew Korts","zip":"02155","message":"The shockwaves felt through a community when something so tragic happens are painfully real, unforgettable, and scary. It leaves people with an irreparable gap in their life that nothing can fix. Please don’t allow your streets to be the sites for more of these tragic events especially when you have such passionate, motivated, intelligent people working to fix them."},{"name":"Xinyi Looi","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Raiden Hung","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Jim Gurzenski","zip":"01106"},{"name":"Ashley Wells","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Taylor A Robart","zip":"02145","message":"FIX SHIT NOW\nDO NOT WAIT\nWAITING IS COMMITTING TO KILLING MORE PEOPLE\nENOUGH IS ENOUGH"},{"name":"David Brenner","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Olivia Golden","zip":"02130","message":"I am a cyclist, pedestrian, and former classmate of Louisa Gag at Tufts. Louisa was the type of person who exuded kindness and passion. Her death is a huge loss for the city as a whole. Sadly, you can’t go back and make improvements to save Louisa, but I urge you to  honor her memory and prevent further deaths by unpausing bike infrastructure projects that will make Boston safer for everyone!"},{"name":"Morgan Kelley","zip":"02191"},{"name":"René Reyes","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Michelle Caine","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Eleanor Hanno","zip":"02636"},{"name":"Nikolas Varga","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Sarah Brady","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Thomas Hanno","zip":"02136","message":"This tragedy was preventable. We elected you because we believed you would make real improvements to street design and street safety."},{"name":"Ryan Nicoll","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Mary McGaffigan","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Monica Cohen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sangyeol Lee","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Ethan Rathbun","zip":"02130","message":"Everyone would be much happier in safe bike lanes than being stuck in traffic."},{"name":"Veronica Reyes-Lara","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Amy Bolotin","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Benjamin Rider","zip":"01460","message":"How many have to die Mayor Wu?"},{"name":"Skylar Gering","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Rachel Lynch","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jonathan Lee","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Cale Moore","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Samuel Benenson","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Emma Om","zip":"02110"},{"name":"Kris Hanrahan","zip":"02131","message":"I have a family member in city planning and while I love so many of the Wu administration policies, watching the reorganization of DOT has been really hard. I know the sweeping changes your administration has advocated for require an overhaul of systems that are redundant and ineffective, but the gutting of DOT has lost this city the skilled professionals we need to make the streets safer."},{"name":"Aaron Levine","zip":"02141","message":"Please do the right thing!"},{"name":"Paul Cirillo","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Joseph Frank","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Drew Homan","zip":"01970","message":"People are dying and the trends in pedestrian and cyclist deaths and injuries speak for themselves.  Please show that you care about something besides corporate profit."},{"name":"Bennett Simon","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Alissa B Guertin","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Tara Tam","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Charles Tannert-Lerner","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Takanori Underwood","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Stephen Fang","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Laney Strange","zip":"02122"},{"name":"michelle Adams","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Yael Stern","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Zayir Malik","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Andrew Gallagher","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Dan Axmacher","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Olivia Parsons","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Alison Smizer","zip":"02451"},{"name":"Kelly Lyons","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Katie Calandriello","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Sydney Mountain","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Leila Freitag","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Russell Weiss-Irwin","zip":"02122","message":"Please, Mayor Wu— don’t wait for another death."},{"name":"Jessica Famularo","zip":"01770"},{"name":"Nicholas Long","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Adrienne F","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Ahmed Darwish","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Jean Jonah","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Alex Kenney","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Jane Ichord","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Minsoo Thigpen","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Caitlin Allen-Connelly","zip":"02215","message":"No more lives, please. While we cannot prevent all accidents, we can do so much more. Let’s honor Louisa and those who have perished before her. Please refund critical streets projects."},{"name":"Ethan Ansel-Kelly","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Quang Ha","zip":"02478"},{"name":"Mira Brown","zip":"02130","message":"I am also a retired BPS employee. And I have campaign for you and believe in your leadership and the potential of your being our mayor. I know the reality of administering is always harder than visiting an adequacy, but I do believe that you’ve gotten a little afraid of the nay-sayers who have not not yet been able to widen their understanding of their own self interest as current car drivers."},{"name":"Maya Perlmann","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Nerline Moise","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Gabriel Ocker","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Joe Delorto","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Sadie Blanco","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jennifer Roberts Keddy","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Michael Gallagher","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Michael LaScaleia","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Eleni Macrakis","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Amy Chu","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Evan Valentine","zip":"02130","message":"If you approve more road safety projects, we will lose less lives like our Luisa ❤️"},{"name":"Jarrod Homer","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Alix Hackett","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Joshua Edwards","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Daniel Carleton","zip":"02132","message":"I have been hit by a motorist while bike commuting and chased out of crosswalks while walking. So I originally voted for you primarily due to your support for safer streets. \nNow the backsliding by your administration feels like a betrayal. Progress needs to resume because the status quo is unacceptable, with people's lives at risk daily."},{"name":"Elise Rio","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Jennifer W. Tucker","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Michael Leukam","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Andrew Fagan","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Conner Tomasello","zip":"02134","message":"I want to believe in Mayor Wu and her agenda, but the lack of urgency around safe streets over the past year have me looking for other options. Please follow through with your promises and honor Louisa’s memory by continuing her work."},{"name":"Robert Leigh","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Andrew Fischer","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Nicholas Mehrle","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Deirdre Crommie","zip":"02144","message":"My 26 year old daughter bike commutes in Boston & is in Luisa’s bike riding community. She rides the Bostrial and fundraises for bicycle infrastructure and safety in Boston. Incomplete work was a contributor in Luisa’s death. Please get this work done. No more waiting. No more killing."},{"name":"Shiqi Huang","zip":"02119","message":"Pls make improvements to Roxbury. It's dangerous here a middle school kid on bike got hit and taken to the ambulance in front of my house. Please taking this seriously."},{"name":"David Bryan Glascock","zip":"02131","message":"This kind of tragedy should NEVER have happened. In addition to the 5 steps in this petition, overhaul the traffic enforcement components of the Police Dept. There are nearly as many traffic-related deaths in Boston as there are murders.  a comparable amount of resources should be dedicated to solving traffic deaths. Start with red light running enforcement and prosecute fully!-Retired city worker"},{"name":"Zosia Stafford","zip":"02144","message":"This death of one of our community is horrific and tragic. The fact that it could have been prevented is even more so. When flex posts were removed in the city, we said it would only lead to deaths.We must now use our grief to motivate action. Regardless of specific crash location, visible bike infrastructure in the city creates an environment where drivers are more aware and respectful of bikers."},{"name":"Jackie Tam","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Jamie Spoeri","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Allie Thorn Bresee","zip":"02134","message":"This is about preventing individual deaths from traffic incidents as well as about ending the choke-hold cars have on this city, polluting our air and destroying our climate for the future. We need traffic and transit development that prioritizes the safety and health of our city ahead of convenience for drivers."},{"name":"Sam Haiken","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Will Thiel","zip":"02130","message":"Every morning, I have to weigh anew the public and personal benefits of cycling against the undeniable negligence of being a parent on a bike in Boston. Riding a bike should not be an act of defiance - it should be an obvious choice for the public good. But this morning, in particular, I pedaled not because it was wise or safe, but because it must be, and you must not accept otherwise."},{"name":"Charlie Miller","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Michael Hipson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sophie Waldman","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Whitman davis","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Matthew Ireland","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Laura Gray","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Kate Allen","zip":"02215","message":"I'm not a cyclist, but a distance runner, and have found many intersections in the city to be terrifying to cross be it running or walking. I have multiple friends who bike often and am often worried for their own safety. I was excited to vote for you to avoid what Kraft wanted to do wrt bike infrastructure but have been extremely disappointed and embarrassed by the lack of progress."},{"name":"Robert Mohr","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Nate Brunacini","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Lauren Young","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Omauri Byron-Edwards","zip":"02126"},{"name":"Sam Veth","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Gregory Colby","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Courtney Walsh","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Melita Schmeckpeper","zip":"02446","message":"My family members and I commute through Boston by bike or on foot.  We all deserve to be safe during our daily journeys. Please take responsibility for creating safer streets for all, promptly and comprehensively.  We can't afford to stall any longer and risk more members of our community being killed. Thank you."},{"name":"Patrick Zuercher","zip":"02113"},{"name":"Darija Meier","zip":"02210","message":"Please make bike safety a priority. If we have more bikers on the road, it will ultimately result in less cars on the road and less traffic but we can’t expect people to ride their bike if it’s unsafe. Use Copenhagen as an example."},{"name":"Gabriel Deacon","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Cheryl Devitt","zip":"02131","message":"Honestly, the city needs to get this resolved NOW. How many other people need to die? There are comments on social media from neighbors cheering about the death of a cyclist. There are attitudes and infrastructure that NEED to be addressed and CHANGED. Not years down the line. Think about more about the Bostonians here, less about the rich  interlopers that developers want here."},{"name":"Ross Hoch","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Sabrina Goldsmith","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Arthur Oliveira","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Abbi Holt","zip":"02130","message":"I voted for you because you supported cycling infrastructure. I ride to my work as a teacher every day. I can not stress how much this impacts my life. Protected bike lanes, not lines of paint!"},{"name":"Matthew Hersey","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Ana Sofia Tort","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Maxwell Gitlen","zip":"02130","message":"Dear Mayor Wu, \n\nWe, your constituents, supported your campaign against Kraft and re-elected you in resounding numbers, in a race that hinged in part on arguments about your safe streets initiatives. Since your re election, there is a sense that you have turned your back on us, and these commitments. I have believed  that you are a leader of principle - please demonstrate that brave leadership."},{"name":"Katharine Cooney","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Christopher Schmitt","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Max Meinhold","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Tim Barry","zip":"02139","message":"I do not want to speculate too much, but the bike lane on Tremont street is unsafe: it is 3 feet wide and flanked on either side by a lane of parked cars and traffic. A strip of paint on the side of the road is not infrastructure and does not make anyone safer. I ask that you not only expand the bike network but also carefully consider the design of bike lanes before installing them."},{"name":"Michael Wohlgemuth","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Rich Lieberman","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Kip Lim","zip":"02119","message":"I want to bike more, but I'm afraid to lose my life. It's disappointing to feel like I have to get to local places by car."},{"name":"Matthew LaPaglia","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Harneen Chernow","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Shruti D","zip":"01886"},{"name":"Griffin Thomas","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Joseph Meier","zip":"02210"},{"name":"Noah Stone","zip":"02478","message":"Dear Mayor Wu - I know you are a kind and responsible person, and I’m very sorry for your loss. I genuinely do not understand why so many street safety projects have been paused under your leadership. It’s for fear of backlash - I promise you that once these projects are implemented, that will go away. We CAN make this happen. Please choose to make the streets safer for me and for all."},{"name":"Chia-Chun Chung","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Cheryl Pavlik","zip":"02135","message":"You were our greatest hope. Please don’t disappoint us."},{"name":"Carmen Williams-Dwyer","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Anne Perkins","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Diana Lee","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Corene Steinert","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Eamon Donovan","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Miriam Leeser","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Bethany Ward","zip":"02130","message":"How many more of us need to be hit by cars before you act?"},{"name":"Ami Olson Campbell","zip":"02130","message":"In August my family is moving from Arlington to JP. I’ve been so excited to use our cargo bike to commute my son to school and run errands. Louisa’s death, more than any close call I have had or tragic death of another cyclist, has shaken me to completely alter our commuting plans. If this can happen to a lifelong city cyclist, it can certainly happen to me and my child. Paint is not protection."},{"name":"Meghan Hickey","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Wesley Sawyers","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Andrea Palencia","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Alana Parkes","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Chad Lee-Stronach","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Charlo Maurer","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Nick OToole","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Scott Luckman","zip":"07456"},{"name":"John A. Quatrale","zip":"02135","message":"Please prioritize safety for pedestrians and cyclists over motorcars."},{"name":"Paul Gregory","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Felix Flax","zip":"02459"},{"name":"Bobbi Sloan","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Francisco Rodriguez","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Moses Nakamura","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Rachel Ho","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Rowan Sloan","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Heather Concannon","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Rosa M","zip":"02130"},{"name":"James Shelton","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Giulia Norton","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Nancy Krieger","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kathryn Hall","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Robin Shen","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Elena Bertkau","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Breanne Barente","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Justin Mellette","zip":"02130","message":"Safer streets is why I voted for you over Kraft. Please support this"},{"name":"Carolyn Becker","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Hannah Sperry","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Chelsea Harmon","zip":"02122","message":"I would love to feel safe enough to bike around the city, but we need more bike infrastructure, support, and safety measures to make that possible. Blue bikes were recently added near me in Dorchester, which is a great step, but there aren’t bike lanes or safe areas to bike here yet. I worry about my spouse biking every day to work, and I want to know my city is getting safer for bikers."},{"name":"Leonard Liebeno","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Samantha Dickson","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Kristin Raven","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Lynn Drew","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Daniel Crocker","zip":"02130","message":"We must, once again, rely on our leaders to see our needs and to advance our protections and regulations, especially as longstanding traditions (eg a human driver at the wheeler) are changing. It falls again to Boston to show the world how to handle the new terrain. My expectations are high. Please meet them."},{"name":"Peter Gray","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Brian MacKenzie","zip":"02446","message":"I'm a former BTD worker, we did good work under \"car guy\" Walsh and was excited for it to continue and accelerate under the current administration. I've been horrified that instead we've stalled and reversed."},{"name":"Wesley R Drew","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Christian Dambolena","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Roberta Apfel","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Greg Marra","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Valerie Stone","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Julia McCoy","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Michael Frank","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emma Rugg","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Aasimah Navlakhi","zip":"02143","message":"We bike every day with our two kids across all of Somerville, Cambridge, Boston, and even Winchester. We encounter so much rage from drivers even as we follow every law and signal and are trying our best to be good stewards of this planet and teach our kids to be conscious of their footprint. You are in the position to negate that rage and promote that safety. Let’s do it. Tell me how I can help."},{"name":"Kelly Sheng","zip":"02111"},{"name":"Zachary Hollopeter","zip":"02128","message":"Hi Mayor WU, this is Zach Hollopeter from Eastie Dems. I came across this organized effort, and the asks here seem sound. I think highlighting the steps you are taking to address safety concerns at this time will draw a strong audience and support from those who are mourning this loss right now. Thank you for all you continue to do for our city. Sincerely, Zach Hollopeter."},{"name":"Connor Doherty","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Lynn Rubin","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Sherry Grossman","zip":"02130","message":"Work initiatives do take time, however, we are painfully reminded that the costs of inaction can be deadly. Let's move forward together!"},{"name":"Alex Eduardo","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Rose Shuker-Haines","zip":"02130","message":"I moved to Boston because it is one of the few places in the US where one can live without a car. Still, me and my pedestrian/cyclists friends have almost daily stories of aggressive drivers and near-accidents. Stories and experiences like these are unacceptable—we need safer road infrastructure now. l"},{"name":"Odie Lemmel","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Jeremy Gonzalez","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Galen Ellis","zip":"02446","message":"Though this letter lays out the most fundamental need for the reforms specified, also consider the benefits to you that come with safer streets:\n-greater community support for you\n-more votes and taxable income from those who survive\n-a more desirable city to move to for those looking to put down roots\nPlease lead us to a better, safer Boston."},{"name":"Nicole Batrouny","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Maria Noguera","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Elisa Girard","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Thomas Worden","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Roger Gottlieb","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jasper Meyer","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Miah Ebels-Duggan","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Karen Petrucelly-Springer","zip":"02136"},{"name":"David lemmel","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Carlos A. Sainz Caccia","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Ziba cranmer","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Nat Santiago","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Madison Codding","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Daniel Huber","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Catherine DeJager","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Adam Essene","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Aaron Block","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Krishna Singh","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Fig Zimmerly","zip":"02130","message":"This is so tragic, I’ve seen so many close calls in my own neighborhood between cars and pedestrians/bicyclists. We need to do better at keeping people safe"},{"name":"Tyler Mckenzie","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Sara Mariani","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Adriana Messina","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Monica Coyle","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Patricia Stanton","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Ta’mar Thompson","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Deborah Filler","zip":"02445","message":"I bike regularly in Boston.  This should not require risking my life, when I am biking safely and according to all traffic rules.  The streets of Boston must be made safer for all cyclists."},{"name":"Karen Rheinlander","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Elisabeth Palacios","zip":"02142"},{"name":"Natacha Meyer","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Jeffrey Gray","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Alma Balonon-Rosen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Aneesa Sonawalla","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Eva Mitskevitch","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Zuri Walters","zip":"02747"},{"name":"Elizabeth chadis","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Anthony Yakely","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Hannah Goldberg","zip":"02144","message":"We shouldn’t wait until tragedy strikes."},{"name":"Rowena Lindsay","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Melissa Berlin","zip":"02138","message":"Louisa was my friend. I refuse to lose another."},{"name":"Elizabeth Good","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ren Klein","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Georgia Cosola","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emily Salomon","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Susan Audrey Hall","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kathleen Cahill","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Christopher Schmidt","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Anna Martineau","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Jade Ma","zip":"02140","message":"Louisa’s death was completely preventable and it is due to your inaction and deliberate disregard for cyclist and pedestrian safety that all of us face the danger of death every day just trying to get to work. Don’t let anyone else die please."},{"name":"Katherine L Hartmann","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Jenn Cartee","zip":"02124"},{"name":"James Magee","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Hannah Helfner","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ava Rizzico","zip":"02120","message":"Northeastern University students like me live all around Mission Hill, and narrowly avoid accidents around that intersection every day. Please add protected bike lanes to every main roadway to protect your students who can’t afford cars."},{"name":"Cheryl Rosenberg","zip":"02131","message":"Too many people have been killed by vehicles on our streets. In addition to more protected bike lanes and sidewalks, there should be harsh penalties for vehicle operators and better enforcement of traffic laws. Drivers habitually run red lights, speed, ignore stop signs at crosswalks, drive in bike lanes, and fail to allow pedestrians to cross in crosswalks, without any repurcussions."},{"name":"Harvey Halpern","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Sarah A","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Ben Reider","zip":"02460"},{"name":"Leah Pascarelli","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Julie Rosen","zip":"02131"},{"name":"David Rennert","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Miriam Komaromy","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Elizabeth Grab","zip":"02130","message":"I have nursed friends injured by cars and buses. I have nearly been killed myself once. My partner nearly didn't come home three times, once during a hate-crime while he was on a bike and Boston police watched from the curb. I've had to bear the burden of moving across neighbourhoods in Boston for a place safe enough to exist as a pedestrian, biker, and transit-user. Do your job. Stop killing us."},{"name":"Gabi Mazursky","zip":"02120"},{"name":"April Smith","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Breanne Mullen","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Michael Brown","zip":"29611"},{"name":"John Pelletier","zip":"02460"},{"name":"Irena Manukian","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Noah Harper","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Ruth Caplan","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Rudy Lautner","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Hannah McKinney","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Graham Cruise","zip":"01886"},{"name":"Shay Orent","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Pfifer Chastain","zip":"02138","message":"My closest friends cycle consistently throughout the city- on some of the streets that are supposed to be the safest. They should not be risking their lives by going to work, the store, running errands, or visiting friends. Boston does very well at many things, and it should continue that legacy through safer streets."},{"name":"Sophie McLaughlin","zip":"94102","message":"I commuted to work by bike in Boston for years and never saw any improvement to street safety. It’s way past time to start taking it seriously."},{"name":"Elisabeth Graham","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Forrest Hsu","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Maura McDonald-Brown","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Ryan Margossian","zip":"02451","message":"Any traffic death is too many. This is a solvable problem that too many people have decided is the cost of doing business. Please do not add your name to that legacy by the time your career in politics is over."},{"name":"Diana Brown","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Nhi Hoang Nguyen","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Jennifer Adams","zip":"02109"},{"name":"Noah Colbert","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Zoii Barnes-Scott","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Jared Katsiane","zip":"02118"},{"name":"David Taus","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Ann Abrams","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Torey H","zip":"02119","message":"When I lived in the city, biking to work was my greatest joy, my mental health support, my physical activity, and my sense of pride. I was also terrified and infuriated daily by unsafe streets, and heartbroken by news of accidents and deaths. Boston was just named the most dangerous place to drive in the country. Let’s improve safety for all."},{"name":"Sam Segal","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Joseph Connolly","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Maggie Rand","zip":"01930"},{"name":"Meaghan Connors","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Jonathan Liem","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Khadijah Bhatti","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Reggi Alkiewicz","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Rachel Nagin","zip":"02126"},{"name":"Jacqui Becker","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Erin Murphy","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Elizabeth Luce","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Geri Medina","zip":"94609"},{"name":"Kinsey Bellerose","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Trista Blanchard","zip":"02184"},{"name":"Chris R","zip":"02132"},{"name":"James Davis","zip":"02119","message":"Aggressive driving is making Boston unbearable. It leaves commuters stressed, skyrockets our insurance rates, and most importantly takes lives. Boston Police need to do their jobs by respecting traffic laws among their own ranks and pulling aggressive drivers over for wellness checks."},{"name":"Ben Wetherill","zip":"02132","message":"It is past time to get a new Chief of Streets."},{"name":"Molly Heyman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jane Leo","zip":"02139","message":"I'm really proud of the work you do! This is an issue we can't ignore any longer."},{"name":"Lisa Liang Philpotts","zip":"02143","message":"I am a RN at Boston hospital. I cycle to work daily to get to work on time and get home to my parents, spouse, and young children. Please prioritize pedestrian & cyclist safety. Not 1 more death, not 1 more body with shattered bones coming into the ED from crashes that could have been prevented with safer infrastructure. My sincere condolences for the loss of your coworker & friend, Mayor Wu."},{"name":"Nancy Mazonson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Brook Levine-Adler","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Isabella Pfeiffer","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Stephen Brady","zip":"02144","message":"While I no longer live in the city, last week my company moved offices to Boston so I am commuting in again. I would like to not die. I truly do not understand the mayor's retrenchment here. Kraft tried to run on a bike backlash and she blew him out of the water in the preliminary. I was one of Wu's earliest fans, and I counted on her being better than Marty \"You have to understand...\" Walsh."},{"name":"Christopher Coombes","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Kurt Broderick","zip":"02459","message":"I know politics from WDC make it scary to push pro bike policies, but we need you to be strong here, please"},{"name":"James Donahue","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Jason Turgeon","zip":"02119","message":"I voted for you twice but won't make that mistake again. You sold out the people of Boston. Every time I get on my bike - the fastest, most affordable, most climate friendly way to get around Boston - I have to worry whether I'll come home to my kids. And that's on you."},{"name":"cate Mingoya","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Nancy Horowitz","zip":"02131"},{"name":"William Cordes","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Aoife Cannon","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Isabel Kaplan","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Mimi Silverstein","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kim Caldwell","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Amanda Lowitz","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Natalie Testa","zip":"02081"},{"name":"Laura Soria","zip":"02139","message":"The fact that we have the tools and knowledge to prevent deaths like Louisa’s and yet they still occur is a failure on the folks who are in office. Expand the bike network. It will protect cyclists, and also make pedestrians safer as well. The more alternative routes and methods of transit, the less folks will rely on cars, which will make driving better for anyone who has no other choice."},{"name":"Barbara Moran","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Rebecca Leu","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Carson Guillemin","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Amanda Ghilardi","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Maddy Popkin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jordan Hurlbut","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Justine DeCotis","zip":"02210"},{"name":"Ellen McCarthy","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Melissa Van Veldhuizen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sam Dreyfus-Brown","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Adrian Vanegas","zip":"02120","message":"I live feet away from where Louisa was killed. The sight was terrifying and heartbreaking. I pray for her family and loved ones, and that Boston's administration takes action to prevent such tragedies."},{"name":"Ella","zip":"02120","message":"Please make our streets safer. Cyclists deserve to be able to ride without fear of losing their lives."},{"name":"Keene Abbott","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Anne McHugh","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Stephanie Golden","zip":"01701","message":"Visiting Amsterdam showed me that true cyclist integration in traffic is possible. As a tourist, I felt more comfortable on a rented bike than in my own city. The time is NOW"},{"name":"Sophia Shimer","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Bianca Ortiz","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Serenity Y","zip":"02302"},{"name":"Abigail Fay","zip":"03054"},{"name":"Joshua Wilson","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Tom Petrino","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Robert Cooper","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Zachary Pepper-Cunningham","zip":"01776"},{"name":"Becky Wasserman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Katarina Torres Radisic","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Marcie hogan","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Amrita Suresh","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Mary Battenfeld","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jen Lesar","zip":"02130"},{"name":"David Kirk","zip":"02111"},{"name":"Lenny Somervell","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Philip Wasson","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Ori Cantwell","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Geoffrey Smith","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Bevin Amira","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jeff Berlin","zip":"02176"},{"name":"Tiffany Jeng","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Mariama Congo","zip":"01503","message":"I grew up in Boston and still love my city.  Please help make it better by making it safer!  Please help fix the T and make it so more people can leave their cars at home and T, bike, or walk safely."},{"name":"Rose Frank","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Jeremy Menchik","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Gabriel Distler","zip":"02134","message":"What happened to Louisa was horrible and unnecessary. We need safe streets for all Bostonians including cyclists."},{"name":"Hilary Menegaz Weitzner","zip":"05301"},{"name":"Adam Kessel","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Audrey Seraphin","zip":"02134","message":"I never want to get the call Louisa’s family got this week. I will not support your administration any longer. I have been an employee, an admirer, a volunteer and a dedicated constituent of yours for many years, enough is enough. You need to keep my beloved Bostonians safe - nothing else matters as much,"},{"name":"William Dean","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Paul Basken","zip":"02152","message":"Stop all public subsidization of private personal motor vehicles, all of it, or explain why that mode deserves any public assistance and promotion."},{"name":"Audrey Jensen","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Ian Dulin","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Mallika Sabharwal","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Leann Kosior","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Charlotte Badler","zip":"02121"},{"name":"Malana Krongelb","zip":"02128","message":"You have lost my vote, and I hope and pray you will do the work to win it back. Act worthy of Boston, and worthy of yourself."},{"name":"Lynette Sullivan","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Gleb Bahmutov","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Miriam Farb","zip":"01030"},{"name":"Eric Kernfeld","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Ren Birnholz","zip":"02134","message":"I bike in this city every day and don’t feel safe regularly. I fear for my life to get to work."},{"name":"Blake Heyman","zip":"02111"},{"name":"Haley Higginbotham","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Emily Moy","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Mark McGregor","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Michael Mambrino","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Grace McGregor","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Zain Ahmed","zip":"01581"},{"name":"Nathan David Obeng-Amoako","zip":"02115","message":"When will enough be enough?"},{"name":"James Iorio","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Max Huang-Debow","zip":"02130"},{"name":"John Ratliff","zip":"02128","message":"Expanding/ improving public transit is another critical part ok f confronting this issue."},{"name":"Nina Wolff Landau","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jennifer Kimball","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Megan Foley","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Tony Rahme","zip":"02151"},{"name":"Jonathan Viola","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Francis Bonelli","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Barry Schwartz","zip":"02130","message":"There are increasing numbers of “ghost bikes” (where cyclists were killed riding their bikes). Many cities in Europe, cyclists are so plentiful they travel without fear of being mowed down by cars! Increasing safety for cyclists will encourage more people to cycle rather than use their car-resulting in less pollution, fewer cars on the road, fewer traffic accidents, and happier people."},{"name":"Hero Williams","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Kun Song","zip":"02492"},{"name":"Samuel Fischer","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Mark Finklestein","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Max","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Lynn Waskelis","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Pam Steel","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Taufiq Dhanani","zip":"02125","message":"I've been a long time supporter of Mayor Wu's original campaign and want to see that mayor in charge to make Boston a safe and world class city that exceeds any and all expectations. The previous year's backtracking on safe infrastructure does not help us achieve this goal and the community is paying for it. We should not be here, there shouldn't have to be this letter, we can be better!"},{"name":"Benjamin R Losordo","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Adam Odzer","zip":"02141","message":"Committing into Boston is a harrowinf experience and it is truly absurd how far ahead Cambridge bike infrastructure is. Boston should be a leader in livable cities, not actively moving backwards and becoming so opaque its impossible to tel thr status of projects that have been proven time and time to save lives."},{"name":"Jane Petro","zip":"02130","message":"There is plenty of evidence showing what areas of the city are dangerous.  Let’s reduce deaths by correcting  these dangerous intersections. And let’s expand bike paths wherever possible!!!!!"},{"name":"Hannah Limov","zip":"02130","message":"I recently started biking again to both add exercise into my life & improve my mental heath. One of the joys is getting to explore this beautiful city. One of the challenges is how much I fear for my life if I am not on a greenway. I am Jewish, & when someone dies we say “May their memory be for a blessing.” May Louisa’s death & memory incite you to do what is right— please make our streets safer."},{"name":"Daniel L Kleinman","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Darci Hanna","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Sophie Lee","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Aseem Deodhar","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Eric Massak","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Kyle Worcester-Moore","zip":"02143","message":"I ride or take transit into Boston on a weekly basis. But the very deadly risks of coming into Boston are all too tangible. Friends and I often decide to avoid Boston for this very reason and go to more bicycle and walking friendly towns. If it needs to be said another way, SMALL BUSINESSES are LOOSING CUSTOMERS who would otherwise come to Boston and spend because of the safety issue."},{"name":"Cam Gordon","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Joshua Teixeira","zip":"01749"},{"name":"Rachel Berkowitz","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Erik Van Zandt","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Derek Lichter","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Timothy Lee","zip":"02421"},{"name":"Melissa Labbe","zip":"02130","message":"We need safe streets and climate friendly transit. Please make good on your promises to improve road safety in Boston. People's lives depend on it."},{"name":"Kim Gilmore","zip":"02124"},{"name":"John McGinley","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Riv Thrope","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Arjun Adamson","zip":"02130","message":"Earlier this week I was nearly hit by a car. It was trying to catch a light and passed me on my right, driving through the bike lane on Cambridge street. Infrastructure is critical, paint is not enough to stop people from driving dangerously."},{"name":"Sarah Leidel","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Dana D","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Elizabeth Torres","zip":"02134","message":"It’s too important. Please"},{"name":"Jaya Aiyer","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Julie Leavitt","zip":"02464"},{"name":"Lily Peirce","zip":"02135","message":"Louisa’s death was preventable. Simply stop prioritizing cars over people. Listen to your constituents and prioritize proper traffic enforcement and safe bike/pedestrian infrastructure."},{"name":"Nia Maywar","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Aria Pearlman Morales","zip":"02116","message":"Drivers are frequently violating the spaces the city built to protect cyclists. Not only do we need infrastructure, we need BPD to enforce laws surrounding that infrastructure. The safety officers need to enforce consequences for not respecting biker safety instead of oftentimes actively participating in keeping them unsafe (parking in bike lanes, etc)"},{"name":"Paul Losordo","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Anya Flood Taylor","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Noa Baron","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Sam Daitzman","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Brandon Jones","zip":"02171","message":"You campaigned on doing what is right, not what is politically safe. Stay true to those initial promises."},{"name":"Riley Applebaum","zip":"02134","message":"Safe infrastructure makes a city livable and attractive and affordable. Please prioritize your residents and our safety"},{"name":"Andrew C Berg","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Avery Richards","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Daniel Calvo","zip":"02215","message":"I would like to stay in the city I was born in, but not if it means risking my life commuting to work on a bike or as a pedestrian"},{"name":"Julia Chernushevich","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Sam Ratliff","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Simenesh Semine","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Joshua Hoy","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Saffron Kaplan","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Mark MacGilchrist","zip":"02130","message":"I ride my bike daily through Boston and past where Louisa was killed.  Our streets can and should be safer"},{"name":"Joyce Huang","zip":"02170","message":"As a Boston native born and raised, Louisa's efforts to increase cycling safety and accessibility led me to ride my first bike at the age of 23. I had never ridden a bike before and the number of affordable blue bikes felt like my world opened up - the wind on my face felt freeing. I was even able to experience crashing safely in bike lanes on my first few attempts. Enough is enough."},{"name":"Barbara Parmenter","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Ken Geiser","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Elena Snow Evrard","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Robin Goodfellow Malamud","zip":"02121"},{"name":"Paul Grata","zip":"02476","message":"I'd love to take up biking here in Boston, but I'm from Miami - a place locals openly acknowledge biking as being a death wish. Stories like this, the close calls I've had as a pedestrian and the comparative safety Europe offered to bikers, keeps me from pursuing this desire. \nPeople don't need to speed to work. The speed limit is already laughably low. We're just missing the infrastructure."},{"name":"Dan Olds","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Cecilia Villero","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Shannon Ma","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Rebecca Chapman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Isabel Barbi","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Curtis Van Slyck","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Bill Arduser","zip":"01096","message":"Please work harder to improve our safety!"},{"name":"Dorothy Pazin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Nora Paul-Schultz","zip":"02130"},{"name":"A.khanna","zip":"02120","message":"Seattle has some great infrastructure why can’t we"},{"name":"Jackson Wild","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Jenna Schlags","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Beste Noyan","zip":"02134","message":"As a cyclist and commuter in Boston this was devastating news, even more so after learning a friend knew her… do better."},{"name":"Catherine Halpin","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Jane zy","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Jerry Lin","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Gabriella Knab","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Christopher Caporusso","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Eric Shoag","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Alyssa Tilhou","zip":"02119","message":"In a city that can affordably house its residents at the necessary density, cars must be a luxury, not a necessity. We must make safe, climate-friendly, and affordable modes of transportation that accommodate high density — pedestrian, bicycle, and communal transit — the foundation of our transportation system, not the bonus layers."},{"name":"Lesley Michalowsky","zip":"02481","message":"Please take care of the pedestrians and cyclists who are making the effort to reduce the impact on climate change, and have chosen not to use cars! We have to keep them safe!"},{"name":"Michael Daitzman","zip":"02481","message":"I commute into Boston.  Every time you slow walk a project it has an effect."},{"name":"Ida Assefa","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Judy Flam","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Jenna Williams","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sophia Caporusso","zip":"11366","message":"Dear Mayor Wu, \nAlthough I am not a Boston resident myself, I have six family members who are, and I am deeply concerned for their safety on these streets. Act now to prevent more deaths, because family and friends are watching. Thank you, \nSophia Caporusso"},{"name":"Vanessa Liang","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Mary Erickson","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Mary C. Burns","zip":"02135","message":"Bike lanes help pedestrians, too. It forced cars to slow down but we need the infrastructure to physically protect both cyclists and pedestrians.This city was NOT built for cars, it was built for other forms of transportation. You were elected to diversify transportation and we are seeing the tragic consequences of this decision. Now is the time."},{"name":"Eliana Feygin","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Nicole Mushero","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Coco Muir","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Madeline Hale","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Morgan Remillard","zip":"02130","message":"Please act now. Here on Hyde Park Avenue we just had a car come flying up onto the sidewalk and try to drive through the ground floor of our building while taking down a tree and entire street lamp. The sidewalk and even indoors are not safe from the distracted drivers that go 20+ above the speed limit. How many more people have to be killed before you actually do something that protects us?"},{"name":"Harold Schaut","zip":"02118","message":"Mayor Wu, please continue the safer streets plan you outlined in your first and re-election campaigns. I voted for you to have a safer city to walk and bike in, not for cars to have a free for all. I appreciate the work that has been done on the bike lanes on Tremont street, but we need more protected continuously connected bike lanes and pedestrian only streets. Thank you."},{"name":"Susan Tang","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Kirsten Randle","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Amy Ingles","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Naomi Corlette","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Basil Sheehan","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Andrew Farnitano","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Julie Bui","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Judith Grant","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Amy Buinicky","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Stephen Sirisky","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Corey Runkel","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Matthew McNierney","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Stephanie Chace","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Daniel Steele","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Taylor Stivali","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Briana Rossi","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Molly Hurd","zip":"02176","message":"My husband and I both commute into Boston for work. He rides a blue  bike across the city. I walk. Every day I remind him to bring his helmet, to be safe rather than quick, and to please, please come home to me again. I ask you the same: please, keep us safe. Make sure we come home to our loved ones again. Louisa was trying to do that for us, and she deserved so much better from her city."},{"name":"Marilyn Stern","zip":"02130","message":"We know there are many hard decisions that you have to make- please consider this change!"},{"name":"Catya Kurban","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Kendra Melanson","zip":"01244"},{"name":"Joris De Schutter","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Karyna Yen","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Tyler Torres","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Alison Wendlandt","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jonah Lefkoff","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Sam Klugherz","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Sitara Zoberi","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ji Woo Pak","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emily Unger","zip":"02145","message":"I am a primary care doctor and commute by bike, T, and car depending on the day. I have cared for multiple patients who have been injured by cars, including children. Please make our streets safer!"},{"name":"Gabrielle Caporusso","zip":"11366"},{"name":"Erynn Flanagan","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emma Callen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Stefanie Shull","zip":"02130","message":"I don’t have an inside perspective on why all these safe streets projects have been delayed for so long. From the outside it looks like West Roxbury’s desire to do their grocery runs two minutes faster in cars is being prioritized over the broader benefits of infrastructure changes that support modal shift: reducing fossil fuel use, improving air quality and public health, and saving lives."},{"name":"Leticia De Bortoli","zip":"01248"},{"name":"Ron Newman","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Bryan Sadowski","zip":"02131","message":"This admin won its primary against a challenger specifically running against safe city infrastructure. The voters have spoken, you won handily, time to act accordingly."},{"name":"Max Katz-Christy","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Josh Breeden","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Jill Dailey","zip":"02467"},{"name":"Rhonda Kay","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Saadia","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Matan BenYishay","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Stephanie Ash","zip":"02130","message":"My husband and I cycle to work every day. Mine is short in JP but even that is dangerous. He goes from JP to central square Cambridge. Every day I'm terrified that he won't come home. We are a world class city, we can and must do better. You're a cyclist yourself, you used to ride from Roslindale! You know how bad it is out there. Please restart the great work y'all were doing before. Thank you."},{"name":"Amanda Zimmerman","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Sam","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Rachel Pergamit","zip":"02130","message":"Mayor Wu, a huge part of my vocal support for you was from your support of bike lanes and transportation access. You rode to work, you saw commutes we took. \n\nI want to feel safe as I bike around Boston. I dont want to end every ride counting how many times I almost got hit. Louisa's death was preventable. \n\nYou  can make change to honor her memory."},{"name":"Ben S","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Heather Mick-Carito","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Elizabeth Costello","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Katie B","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Julie Ogletree","zip":"02131","message":"In honor of your relationship with Louisa and support of her work, please act"},{"name":"jay luker","zip":"02420"},{"name":"Kelsey O'Leary","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Stephanie Houten","zip":"02155"},{"name":"FJ Perfas","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Ryan Sugrue","zip":"02111"},{"name":"Abby Werner","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Isaac Hughes","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Xavier Fradera","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jamie E Stolper","zip":"02466","message":"I do not live in Boston, but drive in to the city several times a month for appts and meetings.  It is scary to observe cyclists and vehicular traffic and to watch out myself constantly for bicyclists when driving and turning. Also, my husband is an avid bicyclist and rides all over the Greater Boston area, sometimes to meet me.  I am always frightened when I know he is riding on city streets."},{"name":"Raj Kundu","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Isaac Gittelsohn","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Deborah Malkin","zip":"11231"},{"name":"Benjamin Mauer","zip":"02130","message":"I’ve lived in JP and commuted by bike to David Sq for years. I breathed a sigh of relief once I was over the Mass Ave bridge into Cambridge. Boston streets feel hostile to cyclists, and they are hostile, and deadly. Make our streets safer now, by design."},{"name":"Rachel Nolan","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Crystal Huff","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Sam D","zip":"02446"},{"name":"James Desmond","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Chen Cao","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Andrew Spofford","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Sally Wetzler","zip":"20451","message":"Please make the streets safe for ALL who use them."},{"name":"Matthew J Belyea","zip":"01247"},{"name":"Jessica Ormsby","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Becky Silverstein","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Julie Smith Galvin","zip":"01880","message":"As someone who bikes into Boston for work, we need to take action now!"},{"name":"Adam Leedy","zip":"02139","message":"Cycling to work/school in the Boston area is one of the most important liberties we have when the costs associated with driving and maintaining vehicles are sky high, when parking shortages have remained the standard, when traffic is unbearable, when roads are poorly maintained causing further damage to expensive vehicles. Protecting those that walk and bike and positively reinforce healthy habits"},{"name":"Maria Lyons","zip":"02122","message":"Please make the area around the intersection of Walnut Street and Water Street in Port Norfolk, safe for pedestrians and Bikers. Needs painted crosswalks and signs alerting motorists of bikes traveling along the Neponset Greenway Trail that runs through the neighborhood on City streets! We also need speed bumps on Walnut Street to slow down the cars going to all the facilities at the end of Port."},{"name":"Jacob N Oppenheim","zip":"02118","message":"It's time for the Charles St redesign in Beacon Hill.  Enough is enough."},{"name":"Rachel Sensenig","zip":"02155","message":"As someone who commutes into Boston twice a week for work, I witness firsthand the traffic and road safety problems on the city's streets. Pedestrians and cyclists are put into danger every day. I myself would consider biking into Boston, saving time on my commute, but I'm too afraid of how unsafe my commute would be once I enter the streets of downtown Boston. Do better."},{"name":"Liam Quinn","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Maia Materman","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Riya Aggarwal","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Andrew Haines","zip":"02130","message":"The enforcement of existing traffic laws would be a great start.  As a resident of 40 years by Forest Hills Station. I no longer see police giving tickets for moving violations. This was something common 20 years ago. The running of lights, passing school buses and blocking intersections goes without punishment and people die in my neighborhood every year. A police ticketing will improve behavior"},{"name":"Linnea Schultz","zip":"02135","message":"I am a Boston EMT and see so many people hit as cyclists and pedestrians etc. These people are the most vulnerable on our roads and need protection from cars."},{"name":"Ivy Basseches","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Bruce Ehrlich","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Benjamin Lappen","zip":"02114","message":"Stop appeasing conservatives who don't even vote for you anyway. Stop listening to Kamala Harris DNC consultants.  Stop walking back on your mandate.  Listen to your voters. Fight for safety. Fight for climate. Fight imperialism. Fight fossil fuels. Fight for our lives or we will unseat you."},{"name":"Ryleigh vaughan","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Joel Berger","zip":"02108"},{"name":"Kayla Myros","zip":"02131","message":"Dear Mayor Wu, \nI am heartbroken that Lousia, a dedicated advocate and public servant, died doing what she cared about. I'm scared, as a resident, recreational cyclist, pedestrian, and urban planner. How can we expect to go about our daily lives when they are, in fact, in peril by vehicles? There is so much beyond your control, but with your advocacy, I hope something can be done. With grace - KM"},{"name":"Elizabeth Tonogbanua","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Elizabeth Littell","zip":"02110"},{"name":"David Holzman","zip":"02131","message":"Please, please, please, Mayor Wu.  NOW is the time to act."},{"name":"Daphne Barrientos-Vega","zip":"02135"},{"name":"James mcgaffigan","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Hillary A Pearlman-Ledell","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Daniela Cardenas Roberts","zip":"02130","message":"May Wu, I have been so proud to call you my mayor. Please help us understand the paise on these projects. I have young kids like you. They bike bus to school. Please unpause and help to keep us safe."},{"name":"Andrew Roberts","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Melissa Kelly","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Ronan McNally","zip":"02135","message":"It’s so sad that this has happened. I have multiple friends that have told me stories of how they’ve been hit or clipped by cars while biking. Some who’ve stopped biking all together after that experience. My friends shouldn’t have to fear riding their bikes, and Louisa should still be here. I’m not an expert in how to make it better, but I trust you to find those that can and hope they do."},{"name":"Mitchell Heineman","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Jonathan Montague","zip":"02134","message":"I bike to work every day.  It is how I get to all my activities.  I don’t feel safe when I know that on most of the road in my commute, the only reason I don’t get killed is because a driver keeps their car pointed forward."},{"name":"Surabhi S","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Bahar Sharafi","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Leo Judge","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Gregory Dracoulis","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Dustin Michels","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Lauren McClain","zip":"02145","message":"The current status quo is a failure to protect the citizens of Boston, and blocking projects that make streets safer is unconscionable. Cars don’t vote, people do. Protect your citizens or lose their support."},{"name":"Quintin Silva","zip":"02446","message":"i ride my bike around the city as a primary way to get around. i can’t drive. i have to bike, train or get a ride."},{"name":"Kylie Arnold","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Nadia Tabbara","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Leah Costlow","zip":"48912","message":"I commuted by bicycle from Cambridge and Medford to Boston for 8 years and still travel around Boston regularly by bike and by foot. Progress in safety improvements has been too little and too slow. People shouldn’t have to die for the voices of advocates to finally break through, but we urge you to listen anyway."},{"name":"Eric Ambos","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Tom Moseley","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Stephen Daly","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Serena Sossi","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Dylan Terry","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Peter Shapiro","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Symone Dowling","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Somy Kim","zip":"02126"},{"name":"Kimberly Berberich","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Daniel Zube","zip":"02155","message":"Take action now for safer streets for bicyclists and pedestrians!"},{"name":"Ivanna Bergese","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Hayden Germanis","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Mamie Covell","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Thomas Grainger","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Chloe Strandwold","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Deb M.","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Anne Fabiny","zip":"02130","message":"PLEASE DO THIS!  One day your children will be in their 30s and you have the power to keep us all safe."},{"name":"Megan De Bortoli Zin","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Jacob Walsh","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Arielle Sabot","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Shira Tiffany","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Brendan Nicholas","zip":"02472","message":"This is an amazing city, but one that puts cyclists and pedestrians at too great of a risk of cars and trucks. As both a frequent driver and cyclists I urge you to swiftly protect cyclists with barriers between automobiles and bikes, and to generally make biking safer  in Boston."},{"name":"Peter Dearborn","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Denise Simon","zip":"02219"},{"name":"Michael Monaco","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Kate Hanlon (NA CAM)","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Walton Rea","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Courtney Imken","zip":"02130","message":"We deserve better! Louisa should be alive!"},{"name":"Caroline Pridmore","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Cheyenne Candlin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Steven Sarasin","zip":"02135","message":"Im don't even bike in the city but I want our bicyclists safe. I live in the city. This is one of the reasons I voted for you. Now you're wavering and people are dying. Do better."},{"name":"Kevin Tobin","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Nathan Hey","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jenna Brown","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ethan Berceli","zip":"02130","message":"Cities should be for the people who live in them, not the cars who drive through them."},{"name":"Jeremy Pouliot","zip":"02453","message":"I work in Boston and depend on safe streets to ride to and from work as I don’t live in the city. Mayor Wu, it’s time to wake up and prioritize people over cars."},{"name":"Tony Duong","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Dulce Gutierrez Calvo","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Anna Plunkett","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Olivia Wons","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Nadia Ureña","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Mariia Mikhova","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Llian Riedel","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Alden Dearborn","zip":"02132","message":"I intentionally live in a one car household. My husband is a bike commuter and he transports our 5- and 2-year-olds by bike daily. Boston is a safe city but it is not a safe enough city for cyclists. I have been hit by cars cycling (both times in bike lanes), my husband has been hit multiple times, our friends have been hit and one was killed. We need protected bike lanes NOW."},{"name":"Marissa Vogt","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Allison Reilly","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Samantha Schneider","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Nathan Sternenberg","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Sara Tomassetti","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emily Graham","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Jenessa Vogt","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Lauren Kleutsch","zip":"02476","message":"I am a teacher in the Boston Public Schools, and I commute by bicycle every day, with my children riding on the back until I drop them at daycare. The lack of infrastructure in the city is dangerous, frightening, and now, devastating for those who knew and cared about Louisa Gag."},{"name":"isabella basille","zip":"02481"},{"name":"Juliette Ho","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Collin Rydecki","zip":"02115"},{"name":"cole springate-combs","zip":"02143","message":"Why does every modest safety improvement need to be paid for in blood."},{"name":"Hannah Rabold","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Jeremy Robertson","zip":"02130","message":"Please direct the BPD to DO THEIR JOB and enforce existing traffic laws. Make it a priority. Calm the Boston drivers. (and collect some revenue along the way)"},{"name":"Shannon McMahon","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Michael Zeevi","zip":"02135","message":"Let’s make sure that this never happens again. Louisa was a wonderful human, colleague, and agent for change. May her memory be a blessing."},{"name":"Rita Droste","zip":"02130","message":"Please make the police enforcing the basic traffic laws. Drivers in cars are the problem. Please do better making the roads safe."},{"name":"Daisy Kettle","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Hope Shumaker","zip":"01938"},{"name":"Jeremy Serbee","zip":"02120"},{"name":"KNic Kharufeh","zip":"02199"},{"name":"Maiah Riedel","zip":"07450"},{"name":"Kelly Datko","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Amy Collier","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Mike Schofield","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Leo Chau","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Rachel Adam","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Lauren Shear","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Amelia Santiago","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Geneva Yang","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Abigail Bedell","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Marilyn Yohe","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Paul B Gustafson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Margaret Keithline","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Allen hao","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Eric Stone","zip":"02446","message":"Mayor Wu, I think you have now experienced first hand the very real impacts of stalled safety improvements on our city’s streets. As a Brookline Town Meeting Member pushing for more traffic calming and bicycle safety infrastructure locally, I urge you to immediately reconsider the numerous recent pauses to bicycle and pedestrian safety and busway improvements in Boston.\nRespectfully,\nEric"},{"name":"Nathan Chui","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Matthew Sommerfeld","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Kristin Russo","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Julie Smith-Bartoloni","zip":"02130","message":"Thank you in advance"},{"name":"Josh Kirschner","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Rachel Benedict","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Kathryn Ostrofsky","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Kanisorn Wongsrichanalai","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Susan Ellison","zip":"02482"},{"name":"Deborah Bernard","zip":"01906","message":"I believe you will help make improvements - signing in support. Thank you"},{"name":"Mark Balas","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Jessica LeBow","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Loren Stolow","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Nate Kemp","zip":"01742"},{"name":"Elissa Murphy","zip":"02131","message":"Beyond infrastructure we also need better enforcement.  Mopeds zoom down the southwest corridor path and through red lights with no accountability.  Cars pass park and park in bike lanes, they run red lights and stop signs, and race through small neighborhoods to beat traffic lights. Commuting feels like combat regardless of whether by bike, car or public transit and it feels worse by the week."},{"name":"Keith Magnus","zip":"01730"},{"name":"Lina M Canon","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Leah Holt","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Linda Nieman","zip":"01742"},{"name":"Bonnie Delaune","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jeff d cronin","zip":"02478"},{"name":"Kyle Denton","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Beth Rosenzweig","zip":"01741"},{"name":"David Halperin","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Kaija Schilde","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Dunbar Carpenter","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Aiyana Currie","zip":"01742","message":"I commute on my bike to and from Boston all year round. To save gas, to save the environment, to stay fit & provide thinking time. I have to add “not get killed” to my list every time."},{"name":"John T Mendelson","zip":"01773"},{"name":"Todd Brady","zip":"01741"},{"name":"Abigail Kelling","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Sarah Kilfoyle","zip":"02045"},{"name":"Yuko Okabe","zip":"02155"},{"name":"David Kroop","zip":"02446","message":"I get around the Boston area by bicycle, which is my main means of transportation.   A death like Louisa's is inexcusable and unacceptable, and it is hard to persuade others that they should try to get around by bicycle when they see that people on bicycle are getting killed on our streets."},{"name":"Rachel Bandi","zip":"01742"},{"name":"Josh Drevets-Larson","zip":"02130","message":"I was so excited to vote for you in November because of the work that you had done to make Boston safer and better for cyclists and pedestrians. I've been so disappointed, and honestly betrayed at how your administration has handled these projects this year. Please do better - if I'd wanted more pedestrian and cyclist deaths, I'd have voted for Kraft!"},{"name":"Tanner Demaggio","zip":"02134","message":"Ive commuted by bicycle in Boston for over 10 years. In this time I’ve been hit by cars, intentionally run off the road, and harassed by drivers almost daily. I was thrilled when Michelle Wu first ran with promises to make our street safer. It’s unacceptable that funding for projects have been cut, and people are STILL dying at the hands of drivers. Prioritize your residents and fulfill your word."},{"name":"Katrina Demulling","zip":"02906","message":"Our beloved Brookline MA librarian was killed cycling Fenway years ago. Its tragic to hear of another beloved community member killed while on their bike because the streets are still designed for speed rather than safety. Fund and build the bike lane network Boston deserves. For every loud anti-bike naysayer there are hundreds of quietly waiting constituents wondering why you fail to lead."},{"name":"Jared Poole","zip":"02703"},{"name":"John koh","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Karen Mackin","zip":"01720"},{"name":"Beth Tuck","zip":"02492","message":"Please make our roads safer for bikers - especially the spot from Museum Way past the Museum of Science to where Storrow Drive connects. Thank you."},{"name":"Jillian Howard","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Doris Lee","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Luigi Guatieri","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Addison Minott","zip":"02130","message":"Signing on behalf of myself, and 3 young children, who all ride bikes in Boston to get where we’re going. Sometimes we’re all in one bike, sometimes we’re on four separate bikes, but we always appreciate and welcome changes in our city which make our choice for transportation safer."},{"name":"Helen Schroeder","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Thom Dunn","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Fiona Wallace","zip":"02120"},{"name":"James Maher","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Sabrina Dorsainvil","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Julie Curti","zip":"02111"},{"name":"Masha Zilberman","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Courcelle Stark","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Gabrielle W","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Alex Rutfield","zip":"01803"},{"name":"Patrick Balogh","zip":"02453"},{"name":"Amy Sloper","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Rabbi Michael McCloskey","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Samantha Mallon","zip":"02130"},{"name":"shima tajbakhsh","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Elena Martinez","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Ken Carlson","zip":"02139","message":"I live in Cambridge but work in the Fenway. I am a safe streets advocate who knew and worked with Louisa. You should be ashamed of all the slow walking of safe streets projects you instigated  this last year. You were our hero but with your senseless inaction you have become just another pol who is more concerned about her political ambitions than for the safety of the people you serve."},{"name":"Sparsh Bansal","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Jennifer Reiner","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Linda Agnello","zip":"14586","message":"I'm not a resident of Boston. I'm a cyclist and this hit hard. This should never have happened."},{"name":"Louisa Winchell","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Bruce Goode","zip":"01788","message":"Please, this will make a difference and save lives."},{"name":"Georgina Lewis","zip":"02184"},{"name":"Grace Jansen","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Lily Mittnight","zip":"01867"},{"name":"Andrew Strassman","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Daniel A Kirschner","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Sylvia Smullin","zip":"02143","message":"I live in Somerville. I bike to and through Boston for business and social. I am a survivor of a collision with a vehicle. This is life and death. Please be a leader here."},{"name":"Leigh Meunier","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Leonard Schloer","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jan Preheim","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Ted Decker","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Susan McLucas","zip":"02144","message":"I run the Bicycle Riding School in Somerville and I want to be able to tell my students that they don't need to be afraid to ride on streets and cut pollution in our city.  But it's a real judgment call.  Let's make it as safe as we possibly can for new and experienced riders. (BicycleRidingSchool.org)"},{"name":"Noah Tuke","zip":"02148","message":"I believe we can build a city where no one is a victim of traffic violence. Building that city requires action and real change, words are not enough."},{"name":"Jennifer Katherine Meader","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Erika Anderson","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Jenny Chan","zip":"02110"},{"name":"Sarah Magee","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Lal Yatagan","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Erich Trieschman","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Armelle Duston","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Eric Klawiter","zip":"02446","message":"I bike to work in Boston everyday to my job as a doctor at MGH. Make our streets safe for everyone."},{"name":"Carlos Monsen","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Michelle G","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Charlotte Lellman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jack Tuke","zip":"02110","message":"I would really like to not die on my way to work"},{"name":"Sharon","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ethan Dupont","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Jodi Dwyer","zip":"02176","message":"I work at Brigham and Women’s and get off at Roxbury Crossing everyday to walk to work. I want safe sidewalks for walkers and safe bike lanes for cyclists."},{"name":"Mark Chase","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Karen Meyers","zip":"02445","message":"I was hit by a car while cycling near my home.  While I am glad I am alive, it took me almost a year to recover.  Please make our streets safer for cyclists!"},{"name":"Timothy Clark Peters","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Victoria Seguin","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Maxim Sheinin","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Robert DeBenedictis","zip":"02138","message":"How many more have to die?"},{"name":"Jeremy Redburn","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Clyve Lawrence","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Jason Brown","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Christopher Hug","zip":"02467","message":"I frequently cycled in Brookline, Boston and Cambridge on my way to work in biotech and healthcare.  Cycling has become much more dangerous due to distracted driving, cell phone use while driving, larger cars, increased traffic, delivery trucks and poor infrastructure combine. Far too many people have been injured and killed by this bad combination.  We can do better."},{"name":"Evan Forcucci","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Barbara Sisson","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Maija Robbins Gray","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Carice P Reddien","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Emma Rentcome","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Dan Flynn","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Michelle Murray","zip":"02119","message":"It breaks my heart that Louisa Gag is the latest unnecessarily tragically killed cyclist and it terrifies me because it happened in a location that I ride past twice daily on my commute to work in Cambridge.  No excuses: make our streets safe for cyclists and pedestrians!"},{"name":"Samuel Rabinowitz","zip":"02446","message":"As a 4-year resident, pedestrian, and cyclist of Boston, and 1-year resident of Brookline, I’ve seen too many bike lanes come and go. They should only be coming. You had some great momentum when you got in office - where’d it go? Why reverse it? Let’s protect people before they die, not after!"},{"name":"Thouis Jones","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Gregory Ouellette","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Taylor Braun-Jones","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Bradford Verter","zip":"02467"},{"name":"Nathanial Freitas","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Margot Babington","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Christopher Cassa","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Perry Grossman","zip":"02445","message":"I am sad to see the death of Ms. Gag.\n\nPlease work on safer streets.\nPerry Grossman\nBike Commuter from Brookline to BUMC."},{"name":"Amy M Li","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Maanav Ratan Prakash","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Tim Jones","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Michelle","zip":"02446","message":"There are so many possibilities for improvement and instead they are passed over. There is no reason that bike lanes should be next to the curb, not between parking spots and the street when streets are repaved. There is also next to no enforcement of drivers running red lights and driving over the speed limit."},{"name":"Ryan Devlin","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Alex Buckman","zip":"02135","message":"I don't want to be the next to die, but I could be if you decide not to make the streets safer."},{"name":"Madeline Marlett","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Steven Karan","zip":"02043","message":"Bike safety needs to be addressed throughout the city.  Protect the bike lanes. Also,  do something about motor bikes in bike lanes going too fast, or riding the wrong way, and the food delivery motor bikes need to be regulated and kept out of bike lanes."},{"name":"Lynore Del Sette","zip":"02382"},{"name":"Irene Posada","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Chang Ge","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Ida Kao","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Isaac Zerkle","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Ann Heleege","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Anthony Ishak","zip":"02446","message":"Many of us have had near misses in the past few years while biking safely in Boston. Please take immediate action to implement these simple strategies making it safer for all who traverse in Boston."},{"name":"Brooke Moss","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Em Weintraub","zip":"02445","message":"As someone who advocates for safer streets, works on public infrastructure, and bikes to work, I've been repeatedly forced to reckon with the truth that this could have been me. I often wonder what the headline would be if my life was cut short on my daily commute.\n\nI look forward to a future where I don't have to imagine my obituary in the Globe."},{"name":"Tristan Angieri","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Isaac Baker","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Maria Molteni","zip":"02210"},{"name":"Kelsey Tustin","zip":"02110"},{"name":"Shelby Young","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Sean Devlin","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Lisa Coviello-Foster","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Cardinal Robinson","zip":"02139","message":"Drivers always take up the bike lane! It feels unsafe. Boston could be like Amsterdam!!"},{"name":"Sophia Cotman","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Theresa Hansen","zip":"02155","message":"Louisa’s death is hitting hard with me. Please stop slow rolling the projects that help improve safety on our streets."},{"name":"Marlena Idrobo","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Lucie March","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Nika T","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Amelia Yu","zip":"02127","message":"I bike in constant fear of getting hit by a car."},{"name":"Hao Wu","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Alexandra Lahey-Seratt","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Joseph mitchko","zip":"02420"},{"name":"Elena Rippel","zip":"02446","message":"I regularly bike and walk through the streets of Boston. I don't have a car, so having safe, reliable bike and pedestrian infrastructure is incredibly important to me, and there are places I won't even bike because I don't feel safe. We need to prioritize safe streets to prevent more even deaths of our friends and neighbors."},{"name":"Nelson Huang","zip":"02111"},{"name":"Keally cieslik","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Laurel Mitton","zip":"02466"},{"name":"Maha Aslam","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Daniel Ball","zip":"01776"},{"name":"Amanda Bligh","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Marc Schultz","zip":"02446","message":"Thank you for all you do. We know how difficult it is to get anything done but hope this most recent tragedy will help create the awareness to move these critical safety efforts forward."},{"name":"Elias shirley","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Mark Schafer","zip":"02119","message":"I ride my bike around Boston nearly every day from my home in Roxbury, including to my job at UMass Boston in Dorchester. I don't want to be the next statistic."},{"name":"Rob Borgoño","zip":"02478"},{"name":"Alexander Kelly","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Draven Neil","zip":"02155"},{"name":"John Tagliamonte","zip":"02474","message":"We can prevent the deaths of cyclists in part through safer roadway infrastructure, in part by enforcement of laws for drivers, cyclists and pedestrians.  And at the state level through more comprehensive license and license renewal requirements for safely operating any and all powered vehicles from e-bikes to powered scooters, to motorcycles, cars and trucks. Please stop deaths on Boston’s roads."},{"name":"Adam Goldstein","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Aaron Cohen","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Megha Nair","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Beka Chezhia","zip":"02127","message":"Boston residents deserve to feel safe on our streets, whether they are walking, cycling, using public transit, or driving. Please prioritize safer street design, protected bike lanes and improved crosswalks. Thank you"},{"name":"George Osterweil","zip":"02144","message":"We need safe streets now - it shouldn't take yet another preventable death before we take decisive action to protect cyclists and pedestrians throughout our state. Mayor Wu must commit to putting the lives of her constituents and the people of Massachusetts ahead of the business owners and lobbies who oppose progress at the cost of more deaths."},{"name":"Alex Kimura","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Shauna Sperou","zip":"01752"},{"name":"Mingjia Chen","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Andy Feldman","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Alisa Plazonja","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Toby Sillman","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Sander Miller","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Emery Anderson-Merritt","zip":"02453"},{"name":"Ethan DeJesus","zip":"02122","message":"Tighten up son."},{"name":"Bettina Neuefeind","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Katie Foster","zip":"02155"},{"name":"SK","zip":"02155","message":"As someone who drives, bikes, and walks in this city, we need better street infrastructure for cyclists. When driving, I feel unsafe navigating the roads alongside my neighbors who primarily use biking, and when cycling myself, I also feel unsafe sharing the roads. With rising deaths and injuries, we must prioritize improving biking infrastructure in Boston and its neighboring communities."},{"name":"Amalya Megerman","zip":"02144","message":"I am a bicyclist who regularly commutes to Allston. Bicyclists and pedestrians should be able to commute and move through the city without worrying about their basic safety"},{"name":"Julia Hunt","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Nathan Partlan","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Philip Durbin","zip":"02446","message":"I'm a former resident of the Fenway, and I bike through Boston every day on my way to work. Please do what you can to make streets safer. I participated in the Friday evening ride for Louisa Gag, and it was powerful to see so many people come together in support. Please help."},{"name":"Caroline Lucas","zip":"11225"},{"name":"Gavin Lund","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Bettina Neuefeind","zip":"02446","message":"I know you as an LSC alumna, and a former student of my husband’s— moments ago, I biked home from MGH after spending the weekend there tending to my 19 year-old daughter after an erratic driver spontaneously U-turning cut her off and fractured her elbow, her foot, and covered her in road rash. Please stop the madness and support separate infrastructure for micro mobility. Be bold & save lives."},{"name":"Ray Zaslow","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Frank Friedman, MD","zip":"02446","message":"No more excuses!"},{"name":"James Hobin","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Aliza Schwartz","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kelsey Clausing","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Rebecca Koblish","zip":"02120"},{"name":"P Fountain","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Owen B.","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Heather Johnson","zip":"02130","message":"If you want more people to bike, you have to make it safe. I bike in this city, but I know plenty who don't for reasons just like what happened to Louisa. We can do so much better for our community."},{"name":"Stephanie Weyer","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Anna Jacobs","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Abigail Plone","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Jay Lam","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Gemma Bruce","zip":"02143"},{"name":"B Franklin","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Haleh Fotowat","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Tane Koh","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Jacob Bezner","zip":"02130","message":"May Louisa's memory be a blessing, and a call to action."},{"name":"Joselyn Gil","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Elizabeth Guerra","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Andrew Moore","zip":"02445","message":"I don't live in Boston, but I ride its streets all the time, including the length of Tremont where Louisa Gag lost her life. Please heed the admonitions in this letter before Boston streets claim another cycling victim. Thank you"},{"name":"Carolina F","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Gordon Allen","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Steve H","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Simon A Rakov","zip":"02445","message":"Mayor Wu, I am horrified by this death, and by this information around “slow walking” bicycle and pedestrian safety projects. After crushing Josh Kraft in the primary, you had and have no excuse not to push crucial safety projects forward. It feels like blood is on your hands here. As an admirer of yours, this disappoints me deeply. The Mayor Wu I believed in is better than this. Fix it. Now."},{"name":"Liza Gallandt","zip":"02130"},{"name":"daniel paydarfar","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Lauren Shappell","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Vivian Ye","zip":"02090"},{"name":"Serena Aimen","zip":"10014"},{"name":"John Bower Corcoran","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Heather K","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Beth Miller","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Jaz Twersky","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Eli Latto","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Flavia Costa","zip":"80002"},{"name":"Dillon Hammer","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Neal Lerner","zip":"02446"},{"name":"AJ S","zip":"01776","message":"i lost someone on an unsafe road situation a few year ago. we need road safety pls"},{"name":"Joseph Verespej","zip":"02128","message":"Lack of safety on our roads is a policy choice. Every time money is spent elsewhere or decisions are withheld, vulnerable road users stay at risk of becoming a statistic instead of a citizen. Boston claims to be a champion and progressive city, but the decisions being made instead show regression. Boston is better than this; it’s about time we show it."},{"name":"Rachel Gilbert","zip":"94609"},{"name":"Michael Yim","zip":"01581"},{"name":"John Bihn","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Ellen Bechtel","zip":"02135","message":"I bike on this street every day with my two kids, 4 and 2 years old, in my cargo bike. This could have been me, or all three of us. \n\nPlease, please, do not let “perfect” be the enemy of “done” and please move more quickly to unblock city street safety projects NOW."},{"name":"Jason Duong","zip":"02149"},{"name":"Elizabeth Cousins","zip":"02131","message":"I also urge you and City Council to enact a vehicle size surtax. Pickup truck drivers  in general are very aggressive drivers, and these oversized vehicles take so much road space that cyclists are further endangered by road space hogging."},{"name":"Eileen Callahan","zip":"02446","message":"Please prioritize safety for cyclists and pedestrians. A city that is bike and pedestrian friendly is more vibrant and livable."},{"name":"Lucas Pekkarinen","zip":"02135","message":"I think that the less our city is reliant on car based infrastructure the better. More areas with pedestrian and bike only transportation would do wonders for the sense of community that makes Boston so great. Everyone deserves a safe and secure method of travel and so long as people have cycle and commute with the fear of being hit by a death machine, that wish for a safe travel cannot be seen."},{"name":"Robert Penny","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Alexander Raab","zip":"02188"},{"name":"Esther Landesman","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Preston Mueller","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Kieran Winslow","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Bryan Meade","zip":"02188"},{"name":"Derek R","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Gabby Fernando-McKinley","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Emily Salinas Romero","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Sophie Cashen","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Jonathan C Lansey","zip":"02110","message":"Me and a few friends have been logging cars parked and bike lanes for the last month. I think I'm personally averaging about five every single day, this includes police and other vehicles employed by the city. There are a few hot spots that put us regularly in danger. Happy to share the data."},{"name":"Bec Sheinkopf","zip":"02906"},{"name":"Carl Larson","zip":"02130","message":"Remember when we used to #demandmore ?"},{"name":"Maaha Rafique","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Jason Stockmann","zip":"02141","message":"I do appreciate the good work your administration has done for the City of Boston and the support you've lent in the past to cyclists, transit riders, and pedestrians.  Please let the cycling advocacy community know what we can do to help support your administration in implementing safe infrastructure for all road users; we stand ready to help in any way possible."},{"name":"Alex Epstein","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Colin Bergmann","zip":"01035","message":"As a former resident of Fort Hill who cycled the exact street louisa lost her life countless times, I urge you to listen our voices and our desperate calls for transportation safety, choice, and equity"},{"name":"Courage Dzidula Kpodo","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Justin Jones","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Stephanie Li","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Norah Lazane Stone-Booth","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Cristopher Miranda","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Annie Cardinaux","zip":"02130","message":"As a Boston resident for over years, I voted for you because of your progressive transportation vision. Please take action towards safer streets for the majority of Boston residents who bike/walk/take public transport, many of whom do not even own or drive cars. No more needless deaths!"},{"name":"Aaron Chevalier","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Olya S","zip":"02451"},{"name":"Megan April Rodehorst","zip":"02155","message":"My brother rides his bike into the Seaport every day for work and I fear for his safety on a lot of those downtown streets. We need to do a better job of making this city accessible for all; not just for people with cars."},{"name":"Leonard Wholey","zip":"02446","message":"My family and I would greatly appreciate better bicycle facilities in Boston."},{"name":"Rian Flynn","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Todd MacFadden","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Miles Meth","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ketti Wilhelm","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Rachel Zoll","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Lily Hemminger","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Diana Christova","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Nathan Glen Phillips","zip":"02466"},{"name":"Kevin Buckley","zip":"02140","message":"Nothing should be a higher priority than reducing tragic deaths of all kinds on the streets of Boston. Every delay in implementing steps to make the streets safer for pedestrians and bicyclists works against that goal. Please work swiftly to make the streets safer now, reach consensus later."},{"name":"Grace Leung","zip":"02446","message":"Please eliminate “right turn on red” to all traffic signals and signs in the city. I grew up in Hong Kong, one of the most densely populated cities in the world. There is no such thing as “right turn on red” for cars in there. When pedestrians and bikes cross the street when the crossing signal is on, the intersection is always clear - NO turning vehicles. 100% of the time. No guessing required."},{"name":"Dalton Boyse","zip":"02120"},{"name":"eiric marro","zip":"03060","message":"“There is no joy in possession without sharing.”....Share the roads safely, there is enough for all"},{"name":"Susanna Hilfer","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Rachel Slade","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Gregory Wheeler","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Matthew Lawlor","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Charlotte Bowder","zip":"02145"},{"name":"John L Bowman","zip":"02446"},{"name":"nicholas del Sobral","zip":"01742","message":"Do you care more about these multi ton vehicles being able to go wherever they want whenever they want or do you care about cyclists and pedestrians not being hit by said vehicles?"},{"name":"sunita goyal","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Daniel Krulewitch","zip":"02116","message":"Let’s go!  No more blood on the streets."},{"name":"Rho Cherry","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Catherine Morley","zip":"01760"},{"name":"Ann-Marie Lawlor","zip":"02131"},{"name":"N Koenigsberg","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Aubrey Simonson","zip":"02145","message":"I bike from Somerville to Northeastern University and back most days. Most of that ride is separated bike paths, slow-traffic streets, and other infrastructure that feels genuinely safe. But the thing about a path is that the whole thing has to be safe. I generally don't travel deeper into the city than symphony, because beyond that it stops being safe."},{"name":"Jolita Seckute","zip":"02138","message":"Enough is enough."},{"name":"Brian Langley","zip":"02210"},{"name":"Dana Bullister","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Ian cooke","zip":"01720"},{"name":"Robert Seto","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Christina Lindberg","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Marcia C. Dana","zip":"01886"},{"name":"Tieszen, Lisa","zip":"02445","message":"Please, Mayor Wu, as you welcome people to our city, make it as safe as possible for those traveling by bike. We need your focused support publicly, financially, systemically, to make our streets even safer. Making our streets safe for all cyclists needs to be an immediate priority¡"},{"name":"Charlie Philbrook","zip":"02459"},{"name":"Joan Byron","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Cynthia Stillinger","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Jeff Speck","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Katelyn Lipton","zip":"02909"},{"name":"Elizabeth Zoob","zip":"02131","message":"PLEASE do what takes to make Louisa's tragic death the last one."},{"name":"Jill Myers","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Steve Miller","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Isabel Waitz","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Heather Weber","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Gabi Riedel","zip":"07450"},{"name":"Lilly Rama","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Kent Rodzwicz","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Ruchika Madan","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Lea Parsons","zip":"02118","message":"My husband is a cyclist who commutes to work on his bike.  He is also a trauma surgeon which allows him a front row seat to the dangers that face cyclists in the city of Boston.  When asked why he chooses to risk his life by biking to work, he explains that it is not only his fastest option but that it allows him to get some exercise and do his part to reduce the number of cars on the road."},{"name":"Connor Smith","zip":"02056"},{"name":"Sadie MacKinnon","zip":"02134"},{"name":"A Roberts","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Jacklyn Thibodeau","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Cypress Frankenfeld","zip":"02144","message":"I was hit by someone driving a taxi in Boston who made an illegal left turn at a dangerous intersection. They put me in the ICU level 5 with a broken wrist, broken elbow, and blood all down my back. I was paid the full amount that taxi insurance covers ($20,000k) which minus health costs and legal fees barely amounted to anything. I was scared to cross the street for months after that."},{"name":"Christopher Koch","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Charles Parsons","zip":"02118","message":"I cycle to work on Tremon to Longwood and I am a frontline healthcare worker.  Things have to change, Boston needs to change."},{"name":"Lydia Jefferson","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Gwen Teutsch","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Lise Capet","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Amanda Sindel-Keswick","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Amanda Zimmerman","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Jocelyn Sobieraj","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Margaret Baratz","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Beth Gilligan","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Xiang Luo","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Karen Shashoua","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Stephen Petrarca","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Ashley How","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Robert Lauer","zip":"02144","message":"Dear Mayor Wu,\nI'm sure you are dealing with a lot of pressures.\nBut, right now, please stop and think about wherat you want the city, where you want our streets to look like and feel like in 5 years, in 10 years, in 50 years. You have the power to not only make me and so many others feel safer, but also to actually save lives. That's huge. Please help all of us now!\nRobert"},{"name":"Isabel Glick","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Catherine Mesner","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Ekaterina Popova","zip":"02130","message":"Please, make our streets safe."},{"name":"Dominique Renon","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Jeff Hunt","zip":"01742"},{"name":"Matthew Devlin Devlin","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Owen Trites","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Stephen Mark Boor","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Donald Black","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Aidan Ahern","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Pia Brandt","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Robert Thomas","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Harry Mattison","zip":"02134","message":"Mayor Wu - we’ve known each other for a long time and I’ve been an enthusiastic supporter of your political career because I thought we both cared deeply about making a Green New Deal a reality in Boston. But it seems like something changed, and I hope it will change back so that your vision and energy and leadership can make Boston much safer, greener, and more livable."},{"name":"AJ Moran","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sarah Post","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Ariana Eiseman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Paulina Migalska","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Rebecca Herst","zip":"02130","message":"This heartbreaking tragedy was unnecessary. We were in Montreal when we heard the news. Being in a place that deeply prioritizes bike safety (even in a cold weather city!) made it so clear that these are political choices. We can make Boston safer."},{"name":"Jess Farrell","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Alexa Jakob","zip":"02144","message":"Safe streets cannot wait. It is unacceptable that people are dying on our streets, and all too sad that one of the key people working on making them safer died because of the Mayor’s inaction. Let’s honor Louisa’s legacy by making our streets safer."},{"name":"Gillian Webster","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Hamza Shahzad","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Danielle DeLuca","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Suzanne Karioki","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Zachary Moser","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Brendan Mueller","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Lawrence Lessig","zip":"02446","message":"Courage for right."},{"name":"Patricia L Maher","zip":"02446","message":"On my former relatively short commute to work from Brookline to Somerville I passed 4 ghost bikes every day. How can we accept this? We must make our streets safer with bike lanes and traffic slowing"},{"name":"Joshua Michel","zip":"02143","message":"As a life long resident of Massachusetts, I long had an interest in living in Boston. But Boston’s inability to provide basic safety for its pedestrians and cyclists drove me away. Now I don’t even consider it a safe place to visit by bike. There are far too many unsafe situations by bike between poor bike lanes implementation and network gaps. Do better: for yourself and all of us."},{"name":"Maureen Morrow","zip":"02878","message":"Our daughter is also a transportation planner and rides her bike to work many days."},{"name":"Haskell Werlin","zip":"02130","message":"My daughter Kyla was a classmate of Louisa's and was a founder of the bike club at BLS. We are deeply saddened by her unnecessary and untimely death that should never have happened. Please heed the message in this letter to improve transportation safety in Boston."},{"name":"Ana Rojas","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Stuart Luper","zip":"02113"},{"name":"Jakub Kaplan","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Shiran Dudy","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Amber Christoffersen","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Juan Fernando Lopera","zip":"02451"},{"name":"Naomi Spector","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Matthew Zalesak","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Eugene J. Arthur","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Abigail Malmud","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Nidhi Gulati","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Amanda Rosevear","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Bill Heinemann","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Manizeh Khan","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Gerald Autler","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Laura Segel","zip":"02492"},{"name":"Yvonne Robles","zip":"02131","message":"Please honor your bold campaign promises  that got you elected. Don’t make your constituents accept bureaucratic excuses."},{"name":"Brynn Leopold","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Christine Petersen","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Colin Haws","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Elaine Almquist","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Adam Katz","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Neal Lakdawala","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Amelia Fordyce","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Christy Pardew","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Roy Russell","zip":"02139","message":"Louisa's death, as devastating as it is for all of us, provides political cover for these needed improvements to our infrastructure. What a wonderful and fitting tribute to a dedicated public servant and loved member of our community. Don't waste it."},{"name":"Laura Borrelli","zip":"02155","message":"The roads are ALWAYS better with more bike and ped infrastructure that makes people feel safe."},{"name":"Charlene Abebe","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Jessica Smith","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Ian Kolesinskas","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Gary Shiffman","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Alyson R Fletcher","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Cara D.","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Julianna Michele Morfit","zip":"04210","message":"This affects everybody. I no longer live in Massachusetts but still believe that everyone has a right to safety travel around major cities, especially one with such prominence as Boston. What happens in Boston echoes around the country, and changes should be made to improve safety for citizens of both Boston and America."},{"name":"Ari Rubenstein","zip":"02145","message":"Devastating how preventable Louisa's death was. I was a Roxbury resident for ten years until 2024 (and proud Wu voter), and continue to commute to work in Downtown Crossing by bike from Somerville."},{"name":"Brielle Ervin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Alexander Lenail","zip":"02139"},{"name":"felix arroyo","zip":"02114","message":"I'm very sorry for your loss \nLuisa was a wonderful human being who I've had the privilege of knowing, and to watch what had happened is  a huge devastation to all who knew of Luisa and her life dedication  and to all who have met her.\nThis is a devastating reality  for all cyclist"},{"name":"Colin Smith","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Eric Brassell","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Laurence Slotnick","zip":"02474","message":"I live in Arlington and sometimes ride into Boston, as I did with my family this past weekend for SailBoston.  I co-founded LivableStreets in 2005, and I've cycled in many cities around North America over the years. My family knows thar Boston's cycling infrastructure could be so much better than it is, particularly since my wife commutes by bike to Kendall Sq for her job."},{"name":"Danielle Moscovitch","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Gerard Glover","zip":"02122","message":"I study bike of pedestrian planning one of our great public universities of UMass Boston. Every action taken causing movements on the streets is backwards from what the future is going to look like."},{"name":"Margaret Kent","zip":"02135","message":"Mayor Wu, we must take real steps to prevent another death, through robust protective infrastructure, slower motor vehicle speeds, and changes to our goods delivery system. We must no longer prioritize driver convenience by accepting fatal risks to people walking and biking. Please rise to meet this challenge, and truly honor Louisa's legacy."},{"name":"Jose Cotto","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Jessica Finch","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Verena Runstadler","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Rosemary McInnes","zip":"02130","message":"I have come close to being hit many times as a cyclist. I have known people who have been killed as cyclists. Please listen to these demands, Mayor Wu!"},{"name":"Matthew Fisher","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Michael Chon","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Casey Mitchell","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Naomi Durbin","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Jason McNeill","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Eliza Kollett","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Julie Davis","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Simon Singer","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Ellen McCrave","zip":"02135","message":"Ditto- enough is enough."},{"name":"Sydney Howland","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jeff Dieffenbach","zip":"02139"},{"name":"William McNeal","zip":"02135","message":"As a daily bike commuter I ask that you set aside politics and PRIORITIZE SAFETY."},{"name":"Harmony Boyd","zip":"02150","message":"The half-assed measures on bike lanes are going to leave a long shadow. Bikes are a sustainable method of transit in a way cars can't compete with especially in a city that can basically never be made anything other than tolerable for cars. The zebra bumps and flex poles are a money sink you need real separated lanes or people are gonna continue getting killed by fat trucks for no crime or harm.:("},{"name":"Ben Finch","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Jessica Lynch-foust","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Catherine Seaman","zip":"02445"},{"name":"LAUREN Greenberg","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Aoife Troxel","zip":"02144","message":"As someone who works in Downtown Boston, my bicycle commute often takes me past city hall. I want our streets to be safe for all, and I want to feel proud of the work the city is doing to protect vulnerable road users. Neither of those things is true right now."},{"name":"Jonathan Klein","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Alexis Runstadler","zip":"01907"},{"name":"Laura Kollett","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Kristin Pischel","zip":"02115","message":"Cyclists deserve safety! Help us help the planet!"},{"name":"R B","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Herminio Miranda","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Dominick Tribone","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Jackie Gong","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Atiea Kemp","zip":"02121"},{"name":"Kaitlyn Dhanaliwala","zip":"19128"},{"name":"Noah Peduzzi","zip":"02493"},{"name":"Claudia Henry","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Shannon Spellman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Michelle Moon","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Gina Pryciak","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Rachel Sorlien","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Funlola Coker","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Lamia Farah","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Max Heller","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Kevin M. Carragee","zip":"02135","message":"I have biked for decades in Boston. While biking infrastructure has improved, much more needs to be done, I have been hit by a car and have had many close calls given reckless driving. We need to do more to protect pedestrians and bicyclists on Boston streets."},{"name":"PIERO FALCI","zip":"02130","message":"Please, take a look at the Netherlands. Bring their experts to give us ideas of how and where improvements can be made."},{"name":"Nora Cullen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Mia Schwartz","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Samira Lopez","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Isabella Beaton","zip":"01876"},{"name":"Richard Freierman","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Alexander Miles Shoulders","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Jeremy Gregory","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Meredith Moran","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Anat Hochberg","zip":"02130"},{"name":"John Alessi","zip":"01230"},{"name":"DJ","zip":"01742"},{"name":"ERNEST C****K","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Abigail Ripin","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Erich Leas","zip":"02130","message":"Mayor, you ran your first campaign on a strong platform, including robust street improvements that were actually implemented. I do not know what caused you to draw back so sharply in this second term, but I hope this moment triggers a much needed course correction."},{"name":"Preston Gutelius","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Leeann Severson","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Jessica Strzempko","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Brian Crounse","zip":"01742"},{"name":"Michele Polese","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Marilyn Judge Vogt","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Eryn Rosenblum","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jean Zeiler","zip":"02026","message":"Keep pushing!"},{"name":"Steve Hollinger","zip":"02210","message":"Mayor Wu, it’s with a heavy heart that I’m signing this letter, understanding that your own heart has been deeply torn by this tragic loss. I believe at your very core, that you want so many of the same things that Louisa envisioned for Boston. I’m grateful for those that carry a torch for cyclists with passion, as Louisa did, working for a better Boston."},{"name":"Bram Lambrus","zip":"02111"},{"name":"Hannah McMeekin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Rylie Lagasse","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Jocelyn Ting","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Leonardo Toma","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Bryan Duceman-Plummer","zip":"02026"},{"name":"Kelley Coughlin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kim Martineau","zip":"02474","message":"Please make the streets safer. This was such a preventable  tragedy"},{"name":"Paul Schwarz","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sanjay Johnson","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Ben Bruno","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Leah Pruente","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Charles Xu","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Teehan McGinness","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Kelly Regan","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Mo Katz-Christy","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Christina McWilliams","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Emily Thibodeau","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Richard Murphy","zip":"02467"},{"name":"David Loutzenheiser","zip":"02493"},{"name":"Ruth Miller","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Ethan Contini-Field","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Michael Ghazarian","zip":"02453"},{"name":"Lucas Herringshaw","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Alberto Migliore","zip":"02445","message":"The safer biking in Boston, the more people will leave their cars home to bike, the less Boston will be congested."},{"name":"Sara cucinotta","zip":"02026"},{"name":"Tavor Baharav","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Sally DeNapoli","zip":"02130","message":"Please make our streets safer for all Bostonians."},{"name":"Adam Myerson","zip":"02124","message":"Safe streets were foundational to why I voted for Mayor Wu."},{"name":"Elizabeth Rocco","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Frances Bass","zip":"02026"},{"name":"Daniel Goldman","zip":"02465"},{"name":"Stephen Walter","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Agnes Portalewska","zip":"02026"},{"name":"Leina Xu","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Robert Russell","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Melanie Santos","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Adam Shyevitch","zip":"02465"},{"name":"Eileen Sonnett","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Hallie Trial","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Mark Goldberg","zip":"02421"},{"name":"Michael C. Piantedosi","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Ellen Freeman Roth","zip":"02493"},{"name":"Gardner Olson","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Dylan Duncan","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Oliver Breese","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Conor Carlucci","zip":"01742"},{"name":"luis galup","zip":"01776"},{"name":"Jeri Sykes","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Katherine Haenschen","zip":"02446","message":"I work at Northeastern and use BlueBikes to commute home to Brookline. I always feel like I’m risking death on part of my commute. Please make our streets safer for all vulnerable road users!"},{"name":"Amy Mahler","zip":"02124","message":"We deserve safer streets. Every commuter and resident should go about their day without fear of death from poorly designed streets. The Mayor has direct control over our street design - don’t let the vocal car commuting neighbors bully you into unsafe streets. You can exert your vision for a safe Boston. Louisa advocated for that vision and future, please honor her memory and make it happen."},{"name":"Catherine Santrock","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Scott Benowicz","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Azadeh Tajpour","zip":"02142"},{"name":"Nicholas.S","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Christopher Smith","zip":"02052"},{"name":"Adam Wagner","zip":"02478"},{"name":"Joanna Olson","zip":"02139"},{"name":"MATTHEW CASEY","zip":"01778"},{"name":"Julia Svoboda","zip":"02144"},{"name":"FILOMENA SCIBELLI","zip":"02149"},{"name":"Elliot Roy","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Arusha Hollister","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Alan Toda-Ambaras","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Juliet Adams","zip":"02139"},{"name":"John Anderson","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Natasha Kablaoui","zip":"02458"},{"name":"Matthew Neubacher","zip":"02135","message":"Fixing our streets goes hand in hand with *demanding a fully funded MBTA* with an abundance of planned projects to expand transit service. \nSafe streets and reliable frequent transit SAVE LIVES and PROTECT OUR CITY FROM RECESSION, a threat that grows more dire every day."},{"name":"Mel Stoler","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Jacob Verter","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Leonard A. Weiss","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Kelly Teitel","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Katie Grinnell","zip":"02130","message":"Summer reading assignment! Roadkill: Unveiling The True Cost of Our Toxic Relationship with Cars by Moore & Kay - I read it for a graduate class and got to speak with the authors and it echoes everything we already know. Streets designed for the safety of pedestrians and cyclists, plus public transit options make for a healthier, happier and more prosperous city. Invest in a better future now."},{"name":"Jenna Hoffstein","zip":"02026"},{"name":"Albert DeNapoli","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emily Condon","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Kate Schreiber","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Tanya Grancharova","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Alexander Fernandez","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Aaron Joe Parrish","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Benjamin Warwick","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Daniel Erker","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Seth Kroll","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kurt Steiner","zip":"02130","message":"Drivers are so, so entitled in this city. As both a driver and pedestrian, I know our “windshield bias” is tough to overcome. Enough is enough."},{"name":"James Ellis","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Kristina Georgadarellis","zip":"02026"},{"name":"Rebecca Cline","zip":"02130","message":"Mayor Wu, I urge you to prioritize safety over consensus. I have been cycling to work, from Jamaica Plain to Berklee College of Music, for 23 years and counting. This recent fatality involving a cyclist who was wholly dedicated to safety has given me great pause. I hope that you will demonstrate your strength by pushing these safety measures through despite any disapproval from constituents."},{"name":"Sneha Sriram","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Julie Balise","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Abigail Lela Gorra","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sarah Hale","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Thomas Gloria","zip":"02459","message":"Please make this a priority.  Our collective mobility benefits from mutual concern for safety."},{"name":"John Blasberg","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Kristina Schneider","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Matthew Ludwig","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Robert S Williamson","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Danielle Barney","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Erin Byrne Rousseau","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Larry Alford","zip":"02459"},{"name":"James Liebowitz","zip":"01760"},{"name":"Jacob Epstein","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Joshua Radack","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Jacob Hilker","zip":"01730"},{"name":"Jim Knizer","zip":"02143","message":"We shine a path forward towards Vision Zero, and the foundation of that work must happen for Boston. Let this be the turning point, let this extinguished light be the last. Boston shall be the beacon, we must lead the way. \n\nLet our city come together and show meaningful improvements, not lip service. I beg you, be the change - we need you out front, carrying the torch that takes us forward."},{"name":"Andy Yu","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Apollo Constantine","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Maya Mudgal","zip":"11238","message":"I was a colleague and friend of Louisa's at BTD from 2022-2025. Though I now live in New York, I was a Mission Hill resident for years and know firsthand how dangerous these streets are. Mayor Wu's inaction for the last 500 days is dangerous, disrespectful, and completely unacceptable."},{"name":"Jonathan King","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Kate Finnerty","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Nicholas Rising","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Benjamin Kaplan","zip":"02465"},{"name":"JULIANA CARVAJAL CASTRILLON","zip":"02494"},{"name":"Zain Ahmed","zip":"02142"},{"name":"August Roberts","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Erin O'Brien","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Jonathan Cooper Allen","zip":"02445","message":"I have volunteered at Bikes Not Bombs for over 35 years, and have helped to provide sustainable transportation all over the city as well as all over places needing it, from post Katrina New Orleans to Dieppsloot, South Africa."},{"name":"Jared Pass","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Steven J Gag","zip":"02131"},{"name":"LeighAnne Taylor","zip":"02476","message":"Justice for Louisa. Vision Zero."},{"name":"Eric Silman","zip":"02445","message":"These improvements will keep more young professionals in Boston because it is the kind of urban experience they want"},{"name":"Sidney Swearingen","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Kendra Beaver","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Ignacio Hwang","zip":"02492"},{"name":"McNamara Rome","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Adina Goldstein","zip":"14610"},{"name":"Andrea Keiper","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Alexander Lavrentios","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Trajan Murphy","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Jasmine Laietmark","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Bostonebikes","zip":"02445","message":"Bostonebike is here to support our community"},{"name":"Nick Neidhardt","zip":"02453","message":"Mayor Wu, please help us ensure that the city is doing everything possible to prevent more needless loss of life. We all benefit from safer streets!"},{"name":"James Devin Cole","zip":"02131","message":"Dear Mayor Wu,\n\nWe have known each other a long time. I respect the way you think and work. It is time to put aside calculation and prevent the next death on our streets. Please honor the work of your neighbor and colleague, Louisa Gag, by recommitting to street safety. It could save my life, my children's life, my neighbor's life.\n\nDevin Cole"},{"name":"Alexandra Areskog","zip":"02130","message":"I live at an intersection where another resident was killed walking in a crosswalk this"},{"name":"Rachael Lott","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Bridget Hogan","zip":"02149","message":"I commute through North Charlestown There are multiple projects for that area that have been in discussion for years, and the Rutherford Street project for about a decode. The new paint was a welcome maintainance, but that does not prevent drivers from cutting around traffic by using the bike lane, permanently drain the Alford St Lake, and fix unconnected bike pathways."},{"name":"Sabiha Miahjee","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Gideon Rabson","zip":"02135","message":"Cambridge and Somerville are right next door, but have much better cycling infrastructure. There's no reason our streets should be so much worse."},{"name":"Jonah Zukosky","zip":"02140"},{"name":"olive lewis","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Ellen Mathis","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Christine Minott","zip":"02130","message":"TBH - What happened? Your back pedaling makes zero sense and those of us who voted for you for things like safer streets are completely baffled. We need answers, now."},{"name":"Ryan Roche","zip":"02124","message":"I feel less safe as a pedestrian and cyclist today than I did 2-3 years ago. What was the point of helping you win two separate blowout elections, if you’re going to let us keep getting killed by dragging your feet on the upgrades you promised. Stop trying to appease your opponents, and try keeping the promises you made to your actual supporters when you were asking us for our votes and our money."},{"name":"Molly Tucker","zip":"02144","message":"After handily defeating Kraft who made his central platform about bike lanes removal, I was disappointed to not see your administration push forward with the safety infrastructure that saves lives. Please reconsider these measures that save lives!"},{"name":"Wyatt Waters","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Karen Osborne","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Katie Nieto","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Rolf Bekendam","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Daniel Melcer","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Abigail Cali","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Alan Gordon","zip":"02461"},{"name":"Lily Yan","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Matthew Sanctuary Meyer","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Mark Adler","zip":"01545","message":"Bicyclists shouldn't have to be careful just so drivers can be dangerous."},{"name":"Tynan Byrne","zip":"02145","message":"Girl, this can't happen. The people are in danger, help us out."},{"name":"Alina Caudle","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Averil Sahagian","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Carol Lee Rawn","zip":"02138"},{"name":"John F Dashe","zip":"02026","message":"We need safer streets for all people, especially walkers and cyclists!"},{"name":"Troy Dunton","zip":"02142"},{"name":"Lily Fernald","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Ryan Nelson","zip":"02149"},{"name":"Wiz Pierre","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Banning Day","zip":"02131","message":"I moved from across the country to make Boston my new home. The city's dedication to walkable infrastructure was a huge factor in my decision to live here. I believe that if any city can fully commit to reducing pedestrian & cyclist deaths to zero, it's Boston."},{"name":"Kim Johnson","zip":"02186"},{"name":"Kevin Johnson","zip":"02338","message":"Every death on our streets is a tragedy"},{"name":"Clark Freifeld","zip":"02130","message":"Mayor Wu: I'm a Boston resident and I've been commuting by bike daily, year-round, in Boston, since 2003. I have two young kids who need me to stay alive. I supported your original mayoral campaign based on a Green New Deal for Boston. Please take the 5 steps in this letter to improve bike infrastructure and make Boston safer for cyclists."},{"name":"Ben H","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Carrie Donovan","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Alexa Gomberg","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Peter R. Armstrong","zip":"02140","message":"I share a car w/my partner.  But there are simply too many car and truck miles/day on our streets.  So we take the train, T and bus when it makes sense.  And take bike or walk when it makes sense (TG for times when bike can be taken on the T).  Incentives like congestion pricing and higher parking fees would help transition. & better public transit, of course.  Let's make Boston walk- & bike-able!"},{"name":"David Spreen","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Halsey Hughes","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Ivan Kaplan","zip":"02118","message":"I was so proud to vote for  Mayor Wu when she first ran and contributed to her campaign because, among other reasons, I expected she'd help make Boston safer for bikes and pedestrians. I recognize incremental change is important. However, this is not incremental change; it's a regression, one which contributed to this tragedy. The most important responsibility of government is ensuring safety."},{"name":"Erica Moriconi","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Rebecca Schaffer","zip":"02110"},{"name":"Luke Kitov","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Mica Low","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Christopher Sbalbi","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Joshua Vogel","zip":"02135","message":"Every day delayed on street safety is more people injured and potentially another life lost. Letting people die of traffic violence is a choice, but you can make a different choice at any time. Mayor Wu - if you have love for our city, which I believe you do, choose to keep its pedestrians/cyclists/residents safe, and resume street-safety projects now."},{"name":"Rebekah Judson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Raina Levin","zip":"02139","message":"I learned to ride a bike as an adult on the Southwest Corridor, and it took years before I felt safe enough to take the road/unprotected bike lanes. Now, I often bike between Cambridge and Boston, and there are far too many ghost bikes along the way. These were completely preventable tragedies. We desperately need safe streets for bikers and pedestrians."},{"name":"Fred Wolflink","zip":"02130","message":"What a shame that there is no money for safe streets while the City is spending 2% of its budget to build, on public land, a stadium for a professional sports team."},{"name":"Karl Adrianza","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Belle oviedo","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Marc de Lecea","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Michelle Kornack","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Carlos CM Mazquiaran","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Aliza Shapiro","zip":"02130","message":"Take better care of us!"},{"name":"Alexander Nabavi-Noori","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Sara Liebler","zip":"02472"},{"name":"James Vorosmarti","zip":"02459"},{"name":"Abby Konkoly","zip":"60610"},{"name":"Max Schwenk","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Sean Davenport","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Michael Spicher","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Chris Covert-Bowlds, MD","zip":"98103","message":"You have the power and responsibility to make Boston safer for people on bicycles and foot."},{"name":"Alok Saldanha","zip":"02420","message":"I'm a commuter, not a resident. The improvements in the past 20 years have been significant but there is evidently still more to do."},{"name":"Jake Hanssen","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Suzanne Hinton","zip":"02130","message":"In memory of Louisa."},{"name":"Charlotte","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Kelsey Broyles","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Joseph Nevins","zip":"10591","message":"While I am no longer a permanent resident of the city, I spend a lot of time in Boston because of family, friends, and work. And when I'm there, I get around by walking, biking, and taking public transit."},{"name":"John  Lindsay","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Madeleine Chang","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Timothy H","zip":"02143"},{"name":"James Clarke","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Stephen Iovino","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Carolina Warneryd","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Collin Mason","zip":"02144","message":"As a regular, commuting cyclist, I have been hit by cars multiple times -- once directly under the watch of a crossing-guard with little concern for the collision -- and always met with irrational anger and bike-apathy of the at-fault driver. My partner refuses to bike in Boston due to the unsafe conditions. A ghost bike memorial lives 2 houses down from us.\n\nThis norm is completely unacceptable."},{"name":"Susan Margot Ecker","zip":"02148","message":"Please be proactive, stop these senseless deaths, and grieving for our family members, friends, neighbors, coworkers, and acquaintances across our city + towns who are struck down while trying to get through their day, walking + cycling in Boston."},{"name":"Colin Larsen","zip":"02145","message":"It shouldn’t take people dying for you to take street safety seriously."},{"name":"Kristen F","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Melinda Burns","zip":"02143","message":"Almost everyone I know who bikes regularly in Boston has been hit by a car at some point. I myself own a bike but don't use it at the urging of my family out of safety concerns. Enabling people to bike instead of drive will also reduce the carbon footprint and traffic of the city. This is a win-win. Please consider these actions!! Thank you!"},{"name":"Nicholas Kelly","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Thomas McHale","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Harry Margolis","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Ty Stelmach","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Christopher Hughes","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Louis-Emmanuel Martinet","zip":"02143","message":"No more fixing after someone dies!"},{"name":"Anthony Edgington","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Danny Noenickx","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Caroline Curtin","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Lucia Vilallonga","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Wyatt Curtis","zip":"02145"},{"name":"David Benman","zip":"02134","message":"I’m disappointed that safety projects require lengthy engagement, outreach, and approval processes, but stopping safety projects just requires a handful of private meetings with select individuals that air their grievances."},{"name":"Anne Lusk","zip":"20445","message":"Boston is a city of science and the first peer reviewed journal published in the U.S. about the safety and preference of protected bike lanes/cycle tracks in North America was written by authors at the Harvard T. H. Chan School of Public Health and Northeastern University.https://news.harvard.edu/gazette/story/newsplus/biking-on-cycle-tracks-safer-than-cycling-in-the-road/#:~:text=Our%20research%2"},{"name":"Cynthia Snow","zip":"02445","message":"I live in Brookline, but I frequently bike in various sections of Boston and care deeply about a safe, connected bike network throughout the region--something I have worked toward for years in my town and in collaboration with colleagues in Boston, Cambridge, Somerville and other surrounding towns."},{"name":"Stephanie T","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Logan Currie","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Miles Grant","zip":"02719"},{"name":"Jonathan Cohn","zip":"02116","message":"The City has taken so many important steps forward in bike and pedestrian safety, and we need to keep that momentum going, not let it stall due to unrepresentative voices."},{"name":"Erin Kane","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Aaron Ngo","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Aaron S","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Shameek Poddar","zip":"02119","message":"I would like to be able to cycle in Boston without thinking about estate planning for my family."},{"name":"Cameron Edgar","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Steve DeBonis","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Nikolas Lachiusa","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Angela Lou","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Kaitlin Rattray","zip":"01930"},{"name":"Vivian Donaghey","zip":"02135"},{"name":"MARINA J","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Nicole Freedman","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Dan Rowland","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Tristan Mills","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Matthew McCloskey","zip":"02131","message":"Your past support for safer streets has been one of the strongest reasons that I have supported your past campaigns. I hope it can be a reason to support you in the future."},{"name":"Casey Whittaker","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Jon McNeill","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Petar Mitrevski","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Charles Dow","zip":"02120","message":"The city of Boston needs reliable bike lanes on commuter roads like Huntington Avenue countless people have been killed, Beacon Street etc. there should be a dedicated bike path just like there is at the Minuteman through Cambridge where pedestrians can commute safely away from cars. This will help reduce pollution. Parking crunches, congestion, and save lives."},{"name":"Andrew Edmondson","zip":"01970"},{"name":"Cassandra Arruda","zip":"02130","message":"As a long time cyclist and resident of Boston, it is a pressing matter to address safety concerns that have been sidelined for too long. \nWe need safer streets for everyone to get to where they need to go. \n\nThank you."},{"name":"Cameron Nowack","zip":"02135","message":"I've had 8 close calls just in the last year and every single one was because a driver was either running a red light or entering the bike lane either accidentally or purposefully. Unfortunately, no matter how responsible the majority of drivers are, a single irresponsible one can end someone's life. Stall the safety projects is literally costing lives."},{"name":"Taylor Falk","zip":"02134","message":"Please work to keep us alive."},{"name":"Niko Kotsatos","zip":"02139","message":"We moved to Cambridge from Boston in 2024 in part because of the better cycling infrastructure. We were willing to pay more to be in a place that had better safety where we could drive less. Please entice me to come back!"},{"name":"Christopher Hunt","zip":"97201"},{"name":"Dorian Stump","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Julia Blake","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Brittany Schwartz","zip":"02461"},{"name":"Madeline Turner","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Tiffany Bonk","zip":"01776"},{"name":"Violet Caine","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Vehaan Keswani","zip":"02120","message":"Cyclists have been politely asking for safer infrastructure for years. You continue to fail not only bikers, but all Boston residents with your awful budgeting and inability to serve your constituents. Do not be surprised when Bostonians stop politely asking for better infrastructure and start demanding it."},{"name":"Gwyneth Phelps","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Kayla Goodale","zip":"02139","message":"Not one more."},{"name":"Benjamin Heo","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Heather T","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jessica PIWOWARSKI","zip":"01585","message":"As a cyclist, an advocate for safer streets, and a cycling industry professional, I urge you to unpause and fund the safer streets projects linked to Vision Zero. I worked alongside Louisa for Bike to Work week, and it was so upsetting to learn of her passing. But it’s not just because of Louisa, it’s for all of us, cycling and walking the streets of MA."},{"name":"Brian Ketterer","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Kate McCurley","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Benjamin Krewson","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Hannah Crotty","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Frank Poelwijk","zip":"03104"},{"name":"Anne Linders","zip":"02143","message":"Please make the road safe for all residents."},{"name":"Jose Rincon","zip":"02149"},{"name":"Robert McPherson","zip":"02148","message":"Mayor Wu, as a commuter all over Boston and the larger metro area we are reliant on your administration's leadership in making our city a safe place for this critical mode of transportation. Boston has an opportunity to emerge as a national leader in creating and maintaining a safe, bikeable environment. These tragic incidents highlight how far we are from that dream, please act!"},{"name":"Kay Lowden","zip":"02155","message":"I have lived in the Boston area for over a decade and have biked nearly every single day. I am so weary of the piecemeal approach to safety improvement following a needless death. We know what needs to be done. The stalling and defunding of street safety projects is unforgivable. There are no accidents: Louisa's death was predictable and preventable. She should still be here. Act now."},{"name":"Christian Cole Dicker","zip":"02143","message":"I don't remember the last time I went for a ride and didn't have to drive evasively in order to avoid a driver breaking the law."},{"name":"Hope Bastian","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Nyx Verity","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Tomás Lio Grudny","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Ian Darrell Kemp","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Conor McGinn","zip":"12208"},{"name":"Laddy DeLuca Lowell","zip":"04101"},{"name":"John DeRuff","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Lee Anderson","zip":"02130","message":"Your go-to-work-with ___ series illustrates the obvious inequities in access that people have commuting in the city of Boston. Putting a pause on new projects favors the life threatening status quo and does little to further your agenda to make Boston a livable city for ALL. We deserve better, Louisa deserved better. After they mourn, LET STREETS DO THEIR JOBS. Appoint a leader & fund their work!!"},{"name":"David Fox","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Peter Shipman","zip":"02465"},{"name":"Rilyn Szabo","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Philip vanderWilden","zip":"01742"},{"name":"Chris May","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Luke Winslow","zip":"02131","message":"Please go beyond \"hearts and minds\" here."},{"name":"Isaiah Jones","zip":"01773"},{"name":"Julianne Vaughan","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Jack McGrath","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Lauren Forbes","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Linda Morse","zip":"02445","message":"I live in neighboring Brookline but I am very familiar with the intersection where this event occurred and it is not only difficult to bike, but also to drive here. Plus I am truly tired of hearing of these accidents in Boston, Cambridge and Brookline. Not one more life should be lost. SHUT UP to the inconvenienced drivers. Get out of your cars! Please speed improvements."},{"name":"Spencer Kestrica","zip":"01887"},{"name":"Solomon Park","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Monica McNerney","zip":"02131","message":"Please don't make us choose between active lifestyles and arriving alive. Bike commuting is good for the community in so many ways -- it promotes activity, reduces traffic, improves air quality. We need safer roads and driver accountability ASAP to prevent these kind of unnecessary tragedies."},{"name":"Michelle Jiang","zip":"06443"},{"name":"Seth Pate","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Peter Violante","zip":"92103","message":"San Diego is looking to cities like yours for guidance on the path to safer, more pedestrian-/cyclist-friendly streets. Show us how it can be done, so that deaths like Louisa's are not in vain."},{"name":"Jeff Kimball","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Phillip Stern","zip":"01890"},{"name":"Cate Levey","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Jake Maynard","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Bridget Petitti","zip":"02186"},{"name":"Jason Ang","zip":"02478"},{"name":"Theresa Plante","zip":"01585"},{"name":"Nick Germany","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Erik Van Vlack","zip":"01890"},{"name":"Allison Myers","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Dylan McCann","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Zachary Lawrence","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Monika Hyatt","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Nicole L","zip":"02114","message":"I've been commuting in Boston as a pedestrian and cyclist for almost 10 years now. I cannot begin to count the amount of close calls that I have had due to a lack of/unmarked bike lanes, poor intersections, & lack of signage. My favorite thing about this city is how walkable and bike-able it is, but the streets feel increasingly unsafe & I feel as though I am putting my life at risk every day."},{"name":"Kaitlin Collins","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Lisa Hansen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Tom Rousculp","zip":"97202"},{"name":"Leah Weinstein","zip":"02145"},{"name":"MICHAEL PASCALE","zip":"02135","message":"I'm a resident bicycle commuter without a car. When you're a cyclist and the bike lanes switch sides, disappear, get blocked by doordash, drivers get real angry at you. I've been cursed at, swerved around, honked at, threatened, pushed into the margin. It's nobody's fault the infrastructure is this way: it's historical. It needs to be fixed. A modern city must support safe commutes for all."},{"name":"Alicia Green Gennaro","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Rory Millark","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Patrick Bibbins","zip":"02155","message":"As a life-long bike rider who has logged thousands of miles commuting on Boston streets, I am grateful for the progress that has been made to make them safer and accessible for all. While improvements have been made, my optimism is tempered by the fact that my regular route passes by locations of more than a half dozen fatal crashes. This is not the time to let up on safety — we can do more now."},{"name":"Nathaniel Kelley","zip":"02153","message":"Disappointed by this mayor. Her policy reversal caused this."},{"name":"Phoebe Chatfield","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Colin Horton","zip":"02840"},{"name":"Geraldine McGlynn","zip":"02467"},{"name":"Claire A","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Caitlin Parton","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Lux Trevelyan","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jeff Richards","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Sebastien Christensen","zip":"02460"},{"name":"Amy Argentar","zip":"02139","message":"We can’t bear to lose someone else."},{"name":"Ethan R. Colton","zip":"02446","message":"I hope you'll give serious consideration to the suggestions in this letter."},{"name":"Ashutosh Roy Choudhury","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Michael Burton","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ameya Harmalkar","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Marie Ghitman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Wesley Clapp","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Isabel Dayrit","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Daniel Sullivan","zip":"02481"},{"name":"Cleo Esposito","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Benjamin Bokser","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Austin Comerford","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Colomba Klenner","zip":"02119","message":"My heart is broken and we know you can do better. We need safe bike lanes and we need better traffic control. Why are people double parked on the bus lanes? Why are people speeding at crosswalks? How come there is not a single ticket given for these things everywhere we go? You can and must do better."},{"name":"Martin Middelmann","zip":"02038"},{"name":"Elle Girard","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Carly Cameron","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Brandon Stanaway","zip":"02135","message":"A friend and colleague is dead because of the Mayor's cowardice. The next person killed will be someone else's loved one. Infrastructure to protect pedestrians and non-automobile users must be implemented now. The deaths caused by auto-primacy are a decision; we can decide to eliminate them with the resolve and courage that a better way of living in Boston is desired."},{"name":"Madelaine Eulich","zip":"02130","message":"Dear Mayor Wu - I’ve been out of the country with my family for the year for a work project. We returned to Boston last week. We try to bike and walk as much as possible. By today at 1:30pm, I have been nearly struck by cars while crossing at crosswalks or traffic lights with my 3.5 year old THREE TIMES. And that’s just today.  It’s absurd, infuriating, and terrifying. Please help."},{"name":"Allie Rowe","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Neil Medin","zip":"01605","message":"Safety for cyclists needs to be addressed and enforced"},{"name":"Joel Nguherimo [C]","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Summer R Jasinski","zip":"02113"},{"name":"Benjamin Thomson","zip":"02143","message":"There has been an obvious lack of real enforcement or consequences for selfish, reckless driving. Ask anybody who lives or works in Boston about the number of cars running red lights, delivery drivers on mopeds driving in the bike lanes and sidewalks, and how many drivers are on their phone. The police clearly are not enforcing this and it shows"},{"name":"Aviva Herr-Welber","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Christine Dobie","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Brett Adcock","zip":"01760"},{"name":"Jack Leitch","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Nathan Roth","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Melanie J Brunt","zip":"02467"},{"name":"Maggie Saalman","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Riley Larkins","zip":"02155","message":"I take the T to work because biking in the city to too stressful to do on a regular basis. When I'm on my bike I feel I need to be 100% alert and focused just to stay safe, starting my day stressed and unproductive."},{"name":"Cameron Kessler","zip":"02215","message":"Mayor Wu, Boston cannot call itself a world-class city while treating cyclists and pedestrians like second-class citizens. People walking and biking deserve streets that are safe by design, not just painted lines and good intentions. Please make protected bike lanes, safer crossings, and traffic-calmed neighborhoods a real priority across the city."},{"name":"Felipe Silveira","zip":"01864"},{"name":"Parker Sutton","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Jennifer Le","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Maggie Zhang","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Justin Perline","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Alex Mantis","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Peter Bass","zip":"02144","message":"Some people's convenience versus other people's lives--why do we even have to have this conversation?"},{"name":"Gaurav T","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Dana Brown","zip":"02132"},{"name":"John Hersey","zip":"02108"},{"name":"William Webber","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Elizabeth A Davis","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Feda Eid","zip":"02169"},{"name":"Sienna Ramos","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Ted Brown","zip":"01583"},{"name":"Max Perozek","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Robert S Tumposky","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Kathleen Florentine","zip":"02135","message":"As a pedestrian, I fear for my life trying to get around this city regularly. Please, help."},{"name":"Abigail Cronin","zip":"02421","message":"I bike downtown as part of my commute and feel much safer in a protected lane"},{"name":"Lydia Malkemus","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Odessa Goudy","zip":"02138","message":"Please, Mayor Wu, we need your support and action to keep bikers, pedestrians, and drivers safe NOW."},{"name":"Nathan Beaumon","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Anna Engler","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Nicole Samios","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Melanie McDermott","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Chris Viets","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Emily Touchet","zip":"02119","message":"We deserve safe streets. Cars and scooters going fast on dangerous intersections is not safe. I myself got in a car crash at the intersection of centre and walter st at the arboretum. My partner got hit on his bike two times biking in roslindale square by cars taking right turns into his bike. This is not ok. We need and deserve better public infrastructure for our safety."},{"name":"Theo Morris","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Natalie Hill","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Alaina Pitt","zip":"01915","message":"We all deserve to be able to travel safely on our roads."},{"name":"Jeffrey Bass","zip":"02120","message":"Please fix this! Bike and pedestrian safety is more important than a fast commute by car."},{"name":"Tyler Katz","zip":"02163","message":"One life lost is one too many"},{"name":"Emma Abughattas","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Michael Pappaconstantine","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Freddy M","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Dan Yavuzkurt","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Lorraine Fryer","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Matthew Wunderlich","zip":"02130","message":"People voted for you for safer streets. Give them safer streets."},{"name":"Omar Ortiz","zip":"01880"},{"name":"Gale V Stafford","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Peter Farlow","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Banti Gheneti","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Molly Caringi","zip":"02135","message":"Enough is enough!"},{"name":"Maria Kuznetsova","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Gillian Ross","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Nicole Leon","zip":"02139","message":"How many more tragedies have to occur before you take this seriously Mayor Wu? What a disappointment."},{"name":"Elizabeth Bui","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Evelyn Aiello","zip":"01950"},{"name":"Sharon Sabin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Evita Willems","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Sasha Tekeian","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Rosie Lopolito","zip":"02134"},{"name":"George Schwartz","zip":"02025"},{"name":"Gabrielle Brewer","zip":"02218"},{"name":"David Schreiber","zip":"02434"},{"name":"Patrick Meaden","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Idelcia Rebeca","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Samuel Marder","zip":"02142"},{"name":"Julia Nunez","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Matthew Ryan Dillon","zip":"01970"},{"name":"Kyla Werlin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Colleen Russell","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kavish Gandhi","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Elaine Strunk","zip":"02131","message":"I have known too many people who have been killed either walking or biking in this city. I have two little kids and I don’t feel safe enough to bike, so I don’t, even though it would be a preferred method of transportation. \n\nPlease prioritize making our streets shared and please get input from those who live in the neighborhood and bike those streets to ensure a truly safe outcome"},{"name":"Daniel Szabo","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Andrew Nee","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Lawrence licklider","zip":"02468","message":"The way out of carelessness is for us all. There is no way out for only some. Please stand with us all. And not with some careless ‘ones’."},{"name":"Benjamin Salter","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Jennifer Parks","zip":"02131","message":"Please Mayor Wu, I know how much you have on your plate and I know how hard it is to come up with a budget that makes everyone happy. In this situation I ask you to consider what makes people stay alive. Thank you, your neighbor."},{"name":"Kate Harney","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Aaron Size","zip":"02451"},{"name":"Stephanie Galaitsi","zip":"02144","message":"No more human sacrifices. We should be better than this."},{"name":"Andrealis Martinez","zip":"02132","message":"Enough is enough!!"},{"name":"Yasmine Alu","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Danielle Williams","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Jeanne Dubeau","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Tara Espiritu","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Michael Mepham","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Karl Ide-Pech","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Rani Balakrishna","zip":"02446"},{"name":"John Plotz","zip":"02467"},{"name":"Rachel Petherbridge","zip":"02143","message":"I am worried for my fiancé everyday as she commutes from Somerville to Boston. It shouldn't be the case that every cyclist I know has been hit by a car at least once."},{"name":"HAIDEE JANAK","zip":"02131","message":"Hi Michelle, I think this letter is a little harshly worded because I know how important making the streets safe for bicycles is to you personally. But I agree with everything in it about restoring funding and renewing the push to make the streets safer now."},{"name":"Brandy Gutierrez","zip":"02144","message":"Dear Mayor Wu,\n\nI am extremely disappointed that the city has not taken swifter action in order to protect cyclist and pedestrian’s on the road. In order to honor the name of Lousia, an advocate and city employee take action to expedite street safety projects now!!\nThe City if Boston’s pedestrian’s and cyclists need you!"},{"name":"Niles Batchelder","zip":"01921"},{"name":"Vladimir Barash","zip":"02148","message":"Please do the right thing and fund better, safer transit in Boston!"},{"name":"Hayley Hansson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Felipe Quiroz","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Ilya Tsymbal","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Patrick Young","zip":"02026"},{"name":"Andrew Ko","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Tamara Grasty","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Emma Hargraves","zip":"02144","message":"I am heartbroken at the tragic loss of our community member. we need safer streets for pedestrians and cyclists now. I look forward to continue cycling especially when unsafe parts of our city are addressed."},{"name":"Howard Lanney","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Laura Pattison","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Nora Masler","zip":"02130"},{"name":"William Paquette","zip":"02114","message":"You stopped making safer streets with data-driven planning to appease your donors and NIMBYs during an election year.  You refuse to hold BPD accountable for the anarchy on the road.  People are dead because if your inaction.  You've lost my vote until this misdirection is corrected."},{"name":"Eric Otte","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Manan Dedhia","zip":"01801","message":"Mayor Wu, we are depending on you to address this issue."},{"name":"Eva Jeffers","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Don Bean esq.","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Darrell Holigan","zip":"01890"},{"name":"Brad Lassey","zip":"02445","message":"The rapid improvement of bike infrastructure in the city served o show us exactly what the benefits of these sort of project can be, which makes the back slide over the last year even more disappointing."},{"name":"Sam Chambers","zip":"01970"},{"name":"Felipe Pait","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Amin Sennour","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Casey Auch","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Mónica Elias-Orellana","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Anne Pinnell","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Ella Prabhakar","zip":"02445","message":"Boston has so much better to do with pedestrian and bicycle infrastructure! As a biker I frequently encounter unsafe conditions with lack of bike lane connectivity, cars double-parked in the bike lane causing me to need to merge into traffic, lack of bike lanes altogether and more. Boston drivers are notoriously unpredictable as well. Please fast track safe street projects to protect our bikers."},{"name":"Aries fisher","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Riley Zito","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Alison Hoi","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Rosalie Cohen","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Ben Crowther","zip":"02131","message":"Mayor Wu--Boston residents have lost a lot of trust in the City, that it wants to keep people safe however they get around. Strong action of safe streets is a way to regain out trust. I was hit by a car in Roslindale while on a run. Every time I go for a run now, my wife tells me 'stay safe, I love you'. It's not right that people have to fear for their loved ones when they go out on foot or bike."},{"name":"Jeff Wachter","zip":"02446","message":"Bike commuting to my downtown Boston job is the best and scariest part of my day. We shouldn't fear for our lives at every intersection, have to guess if the car is going to take a surprise turn across the bike lane, or swerve out of bike lanes to avoid cars stopped in the tiny space allocated for bikes. We can have safe streets if we make the choice to have them. Please make that choice."},{"name":"Michael Mahoney","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Ben Spevack","zip":"02446","message":"I work for Boston Healthcare for the Homeless and bike to the Southampton Street Shelter to care for shelter guests. I don't want to get injured on the way to work, nor do I want to fear death on my commute. We need decisive action!"},{"name":"Michelle Chavez","zip":"02135","message":"All deaths are preventable."},{"name":"Raylen Dziengelewski","zip":"02189"},{"name":"Ethan Yu","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Alex Montana","zip":"02053"},{"name":"Sevi Ettinger","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Faith Nguyen","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Hiya Gada","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Bob Nesson","zip":"02143","message":"These deaths are inexcusable and preventable with safer streets and more monitoring of drivers impaired by distractions -- and stronger penalties."},{"name":"Kathleen McDermott","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Rabbi Lev Friedman","zip":"02468"},{"name":"Cynthia Zabin","zip":"02131","message":"02131"},{"name":"Anna Nagy","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Sage Gilbert-Diamond","zip":"02481"},{"name":"Corinne P","zip":"02453"},{"name":"Eric Colantonio","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jaimie DeScioli","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Tyler Wood","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Felicia Belostecinic","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Daniel J Moss","zip":"02130","message":"I love traveling by bicycle in my beloved Boston. It reduces traffic and climate change and is a healthy alternative .Please keep us safe, Mayor Wu. Now!"},{"name":"Alexander Nguyen","zip":"02149"},{"name":"Jan Santo","zip":"02026"},{"name":"Allie Durak","zip":"02148","message":"We needed help yesterday, but we can build a better world now. Please be a part of that Mayor Wu."},{"name":"Milo Kron","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Jocelyn Greer","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Sam Champion","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Sarah O'Connor","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Abby Feyrer","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Michael Currie","zip":"01742","message":"My spouse commutes by bike to Boston. I want her to come home alive at the end of each day."},{"name":"Carlos Cipollitti","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Ryan Ho","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Gracie Brett","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Henrique Carneiro Zhu","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Samuel Crum","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Christian Strassberger","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Levi Chen","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Ethan Richenberg","zip":"01464"},{"name":"Dionysis Milesis","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Janie Kayz-Christy","zip":"02140","message":"PLEASE. We loved your strong and inspiringbsupport in the past, and cannot understand why you changed direction despite winning the primary race against an anti-bike and bus lane agenda."},{"name":"Daniel Lloyd-Miller","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Swami Venkatesan","zip":"01742"},{"name":"Adrish Dey","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Stephen Winslow","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Angela Sun","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Yashar Hadi","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Bebe Nixon","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Tali Smookler","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Gavin Pitt","zip":"02144","message":"I ride my bicycle just about everywhere around Somerville, Cambridge, and Boston. The streets of Boston are noticeable more dangerous than Somerville and Cambridge, and honestly Cambridge and Somerville has a long way to go too. I would love to see some real action on making the city more bikeable, like this administration campaigned on"},{"name":"Carlos Villamil","zip":"02150"},{"name":"David Wean","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Dianna Pozdniakov","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Daniel Dempsey","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Maggie Scott","zip":"02120","message":"We deserve safe streets. Cities should be accessible to EVERYONE. People living in areas that need safe, reliable transportation the MOST have the LEAST safe, reliable access. Everyone deserves to be mobile and be safe while they are at it."},{"name":"Hunter Hsiu","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Elissa Yanover","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Tyler Rocca","zip":"02138"},{"name":"mary larosee","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Meg Daly","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Lauren Sanchez","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Naomi Miller","zip":"01742"},{"name":"Todd Consentino","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Andrea Yakovakis","zip":"02140","message":"Please do the right thing. I was one of your cheerleaders but right now my pom poms are on the floor."},{"name":"Armie Erban","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Mehana Nagarur","zip":"06074"},{"name":"Mattéo Couplet","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Alexander Aman","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Erika Shira","zip":"02119","message":"I am a cyclist living in Roxbury and parent of a disabled young adult who cannot \"just go around\" when a bike lane or crosswalk is blocked. I have made hundreds of 311 reports about massively unsafe infrastructure and e-mailed the city videos of drivers including city employees endangering cyclists and pedestrians, and you do nothing. This tragedy was entirely preventable. When will we get action?"},{"name":"Jason Freirich","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Gabby Romm","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Katlynn Schmick","zip":"02152"},{"name":"Robert Ainslie","zip":"02130","message":"Keep adding infrastructure to keep pedestrians safe! Drive enforcement of bike lane violations! I bike this section regularly and you shouldn't need to take your life in your hands to GET to the corridor!"},{"name":"Anuradha Desai","zip":"02131","message":"We know you are grieving Louisa's loss, as we all are. Time to pay urgent attention to bicycle safety. Thanks."},{"name":"Lauren Posklensky","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Aubrey O'Dell","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ahir Verma","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Kneide Nascimento","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Stephanie Xiao","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Emily Pitt","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Cicia Lee","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Aria Wong","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Megan Hyde","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Mackinley Morgan","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Michael Rosenbaum","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Caleb Meredith","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Henry Finch","zip":"02468","message":"My mid 30s son lives in Brighton and has biked to work downtown for the last 6 years. Not owning a car might make it possible to actually buy a house in the future. When I go into Boston I either bike or take the T. I love the improvements to Boston's biking infrastructure but it is only a beginning. We need so much more for general safety of pedestrians and bikers."},{"name":"Liew Min","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Chad Fisher","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emily Maez","zip":"02120","message":"I’ve gotten hit by two cars cycling and i’ve only biked in boston for a year"},{"name":"Michael Elliott","zip":"01562"},{"name":"Jessica Loftus","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Zachary Jicha","zip":"02143","message":"I left Boston for Somerville because it does not show the same care for people outside of cars as its neighbors. It has been extremely disappointing to see the mayor give up not only their ambition for new safety projects but also the ones already planned and funded."},{"name":"Jacob Isom","zip":"02215","message":"In my time living at Boston I have worked at a preschool and as a tutor in an after school site, both of which I usually biked to. Anytime I had a frightening moment or a close call while biking to work, I thought to myself, what would those kids think if, when they expected me to come in, I had been killed on the road? People shouldn't have to die before safe infrastructure is built."},{"name":"Renee Kasinsky","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Bettina Stoetzer","zip":"02130","message":"I frequently feel unsafe as a pedestrian and cyclist in Boston; I have lived in several other US cities in the past and Boston is by far the city in which I have felt the least safe; please protect the safety of pedestrians and cyclists in this city in a more comprehensive way to prevent future deaths and injuries"},{"name":"CHRISTOPHER GORDON SCHERBEL","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Joshua Blouwolff","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Yunus Baran Kok","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Ellen I Israel","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Glenda Yoder","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Susan Naimark","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Maya Faulstich","zip":"01063"},{"name":"Lauren Mock","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Julie Gibbons","zip":"02130"},{"name":"cathy greenspan","zip":"02467"},{"name":"Richard Williams","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Aaron Daigle","zip":"01571"},{"name":"Chloe Toutain","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Madeline Liberman","zip":"01867"},{"name":"Nancy Marks","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Ellie Stonecipher","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Celia Drury","zip":"10516"},{"name":"Holly Clayton","zip":"02145","message":"I commute into Boston from Somerville, most days by bicycle. I have safe routes to get to the border of Boston. Once I'm in Boston, those safe routes disappear, and it's a stark difference. Lack of separation means cars WILL park in the bike lanes (where the bike lanes even exist), forcing us into traffic. Un-stall the stalled complete streets projects already."},{"name":"Claire-Solene Becka","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Rob Cant","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Kenneth Ho","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Max Jackson","zip":"02472","message":"I'm sobbing over lost friends while alcoholic road-ragers run City Hall, pretending to care. Boston is the #1 US city primed for the Amsterdam treatment. Instead, you desecrate Storrow’s legacy, proving driver convenience surpasses human life in priority. THIS – this is my only priority as a constituent. Stop this criminal neglect. Stop being an accessory to vehicular homicide."},{"name":"Ravienne Hodgson","zip":"02134","message":"Cyclists deserve better. Please prevent these tragedies from hurting our community more!"},{"name":"Max Fan","zip":"01810","message":"I frequently cycle into the Boston metropolitan area. I avoid Boston because it is particularly dangerous for cyclists, especially compared to Cambridge. Improving Boston's cycling infrastructure would encourage me to come into Boston more and spend more of my money in the City. It is also a more humane policy to pursue. These deaths are preventable!"},{"name":"Elisabeth Leake","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Aidan Sweeney","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Ray Fisher","zip":"21209","message":"My son rides his bike several times a week to his city Parks and Rec job. He was side swiped by a car a few months ago on his way to work. Something needs to be done asap! May Louisa’s name be a blessing and help change the direction of road safety."},{"name":"Philip Omohundro","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Jody Adams","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Audrey Kollett","zip":"02131"},{"name":"James Yeagle","zip":"02460"},{"name":"Matt Green","zip":"02118","message":"Separated bike lanes protect drivers, cyclists, and pedestrians. The roads are packed with people double parked or loitering, creating a dangerous environment that I'm impressed doesn't have more casualties."},{"name":"Steve Meacham","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Una Gogstetter","zip":"02026"},{"name":"Ajay Sequeira","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Isabella Dobson","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Liam Hafter","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Alicia Ridenour","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Naomi Carrigg","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Alex Sheahan","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Lea Carrigg","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Yiru Zhou","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Gregory Loden","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Riyana Roy","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Andrew Starr","zip":"02115","message":"You promised us better than you've been delivering, Mayor Wu. Louisa could have still been with us if you hadn't backed down from your promises"},{"name":"Robert Triest","zip":"02132"},{"name":"John O'Connell","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Charles Jessup Franklin","zip":"02139","message":"I remember last year when you testified before Congress. You did a such great job representing the city. Since then you've betrayed your voters. They gave you a decisive victory against Kraft, then you promptly picked up his platform.\n\nWestern Avenue was safe. Now I have regular near misses. I even got hit on the 6th. See it for yourself https://youtu.be/8eShP2Yql20"},{"name":"Esther Rosi-Kessel","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Louise Treitman","zip":"02421"},{"name":"Madeleine McKee","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Sarah reed","zip":"02445","message":"I cycle to work every day. Hardly a day goes by that I don’t have a close call. I am a 62 year old resident of Brookline and cycle to the Back Bay."},{"name":"Jeff Geisinger","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Gabrielle C.","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Ava Cheloff","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Allison Perna","zip":"02144","message":"I do not feel safe navigating in such a car-centric city. The infrastructure not only enables but encourages unsafe car maneuvers and aggression. Our lives are literally at stake."},{"name":"KW","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Gabriella Lipsitch","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Tatiana Boria","zip":"01701"},{"name":"Henri Wielandy","zip":"07940"},{"name":"Srusti Sain","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Rutu Tatke","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Ezra Weintroub","zip":"02467"},{"name":"Miles Schwartz Sax","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jonah K Chiarenza","zip":"02176","message":"Politics is hard. Saving lives with proven safety countermeasures shouldn't be. Let's get back to where you started - working for the people, not special interests."},{"name":"Katherine Vinter","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Susan Bresney","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Ian Kinstlinger","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Sophie Choong","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Tristán Gramsch","zip":"02134","message":"As cyclists we are exposed. We pay for the mistakes of motorists. Who are careless and not impacted by such accidents. It is an unfair game. We have a saying in Spanish, “Pagan justos por pecadores”, the innocent pay the price."},{"name":"Joey Zeldin","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Roz Freeman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sharryn Ross","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Trevor Stenson","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Susan Hansen","zip":"02131","message":"Since 1994  I have lived in Kenmore Square across from ‘The Rat’ and changed apartments in 1995 due to a Rat Infestation. Paiid $355 in tent with BFF $355. Discovered we had a Rat problem we contacted the necessary authorities. We were moved two floors above the Taj in Kenmore. We had NO bike lanes. I rode my bike occasionally and felt safer on Public Transport u til I came back from Britainr."},{"name":"Katherine Kinnaird","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Tizzy Torres Zamarripa","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Abigail Hoy","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Alexander Bertoloni Meli","zip":"02119"},{"name":"THOMAS BIELENDA","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Brielle Shea","zip":"02170"},{"name":"Collen Mahoney","zip":"02119","message":"I’ve nearly been struck by a car countless times in this city. Blue Hill Ave and Columbus Ave/Tremont St north of Jackson Square are absolute nightmares. There are already plans to significantly improve both of these corridors. It’s time to move NOW."},{"name":"Elizabeth Langan","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Megan Lim","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Matt Poulsen","zip":"02115","message":"Please act fast to stop these unnecessary deaths!"},{"name":"Enrico Grillo","zip":"01027"},{"name":"Janie Akers","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Rachel Eve Young","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Anvi Fenn","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Saoirse Beare","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Daniella Herman","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Seth Tenenbaum","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Ellen B","zip":"02120","message":"Let’s advance boldly the work Luisa left unfinished, in her honor."},{"name":"Mary Bovenzi","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sheila B Magee","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Emma Powers","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Lara Merullo","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Suzanne Parmar","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Alice Kessler","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Adric Mueller","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Shilpa Taneja-Mannetta","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Hannah Gibson","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Johan Tingsvall","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Judy Kanter","zip":"02131","message":"I know the heartache you must be feeling. Please turn that into action."},{"name":"Nate Deshmukh Towery","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Eugenio Menegon","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Bridget Lee","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kayla Ormiston","zip":"01773"},{"name":"Elizabeth Cantor","zip":"02130","message":"Dear Mayor Wu,\n\nI often bike my kids to school from JP to Roslindale. My 7-year-old can’t wait to get on their own bike, but I am scared to allow them because the infrastructure just isn’t there. In truth, I am fooling myself to believe we are safe if I am “driving”. If we want our city to be the best and safest version of itself, we need to move these projects forward. Please take action now."},{"name":"Alexandra Turner","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Sarah Lisuzzo","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Adam Reeve","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Krzysztof Gajos","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Emily Summit","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Kathleen Fitch","zip":"02130","message":"Dear Mayor Wu,\nI have been cyclist in Boston for about 15 years. Cycling is empowering, it’s exercise, good for the environment, takes unsafe cars off the street, and is less impactful on the city’s infrastructure, the list goes on. Boston should be a the best city to bike in, in this country, if not world, but it’s not and while I support you as mayor the biking infrastructure has fallen apart."},{"name":"Brendan Tschuy","zip":"02130","message":"All I'm asking is to please do the easy things which your constituents want. Add the flex posts BACK to where they once were. Follow through with approved — by the feds and by locals — transit projects like the BH Avenue Busway."},{"name":"Noah Wolfe","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Marybeth Noonan","zip":"02459","message":"Hi I lived in Boston for 33 years before retiring and moving to an independent senior living community in Newton. I rode my bike to work from WestRoxbury to the Fenway area. I was hit by a car in a bike to work day in 2012. Luckily I survived with only a broken wrist & several fingers. We need to do more to stop distracted drivers , trucks not yielding at intersections &register all scooters"},{"name":"Scott Sharpe","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Joseph Wardwell","zip":"02130","message":"As a cyclist I can no longer support a mayor that has abandoned the policies that she herself started.   Striving for consensus on safety issues equals fatalities of our own citizens.  I don’t understand how someone so obviously bright doesn’t understand or can tolerate the trade off."},{"name":"kara doherty","zip":"02118"},{"name":"James Furnival","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Susan Murphy","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Izabella Agasino","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Mitchell Chernick","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Elise Aultman","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Liz Baldo","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Wiseness Tatienou","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Anoushka Abroal","zip":"02120"},{"name":"scott wyman neagle","zip":"02462","message":"enforcement of traffic laws in Boston is totally inadequate. I don't believe that BPD is incapable of enforcing traffic laws, they choose not to enforce the traffic laws. when the best street design can be destroyed by negligent drivers with impunity, we have a deeper problem. I submit multiple 311 requests for parking and traffic enforcement every week, and the problem only seems to get worse."},{"name":"Nick Wang","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Sean Riley","zip":"02043"},{"name":"Deborah Danzig Brodie","zip":"02467"},{"name":"Hugh P McCrory","zip":"01742","message":"Please Be Decisive on making roads safer."},{"name":"Daniel Hudon","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Paula Rodriguez-Diaz","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Ada Okun","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Suzanne Mrozak","zip":"02131","message":"And as a friend of Louisa's grieving parents, I urge you to take action now. Thank you!"},{"name":"Morgane Treanton","zip":"02127","message":"We take our kids to a BPS school by bike and try to bike as much as we can.  We want safer streets everywhere but especially south boston. Vehicles drive too fast."},{"name":"chris heaton","zip":"02131","message":"More must be done to provide for cyclists' safety, and you can do it! More cars is not the answer."},{"name":"Jim Kimball","zip":"02113"},{"name":"Samantha LeBlanc","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Larry Rogel","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Annalisa Heppner","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Nathan Klima","zip":"60640"},{"name":"Jordan Rabinowitz","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Lara Patricio","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Emma Boland","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Jess Ten Eyck","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Lizzie Lofye","zip":"02115"},{"name":"John Ellersick","zip":"02140","message":"We ask you to honor the memory of Louisa and so many others, with recommitment to making our streets safer for our whole community.\n\nJohn Ellersick - Cambridge Bike Committee 2016 - present"},{"name":"Linda Cohen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Tatiana Ediger","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Cesar Garcia","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Tai Lam","zip":"02148","message":"I hope this will create the much needed urgency to bring back the City's support for cycling infrastructure.  It saddened me when the bike counter at Lowell Square wasn't working anymore for Boston's Bike to Work Day this year.  I hope this is a wake up call for Boston."},{"name":"Calvin Pomerantz","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Lydia Harrington","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Perry Thomson","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Austin Paul","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Trevor N Powell","zip":"02135","message":"Enough. You have the opportunity to do the right thing and keep us safe. Boston should be a leader in mobility options and you are failing us. Please!"},{"name":"Robert J Fitzpatrick","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Daniel McMasters","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Jules Lousberg","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Abigail Tyler","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Carolyn Riley","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Shruthi S","zip":"02135"},{"name":"John O’Vonnell","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Luke Henry McCarthy","zip":"02445","message":"Dear Mayor Wu,\n\nIt is deeply disappointing seeing you slip on cycling infrastructure of the years in office. You came out strong with 10 miles built in the first year or so. Then you just... stopped. You gave up. You thought it would cost too much political will to improve to safety of a small percentage of voters.\n\nThis is what apathy costs.\n\nLuke"},{"name":"Caimren Wagner","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Gustavo Marquez Lainez","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Zoe Nugent","zip":"02171"},{"name":"Bernadette Chirokas","zip":"02026","message":"I work within the city of Boston and generally commute to work from Dedham by cycling if the weather is amenable. I  also use many of the recreational ways around Boston cycling but it is often dangerous to connect from any northern routes I have been on the southern routes I’m taking to get home."},{"name":"Merika Sanders","zip":"02478"},{"name":"Samuel Warren","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Leslie Homa","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Shachie Garcia","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Alina Watson","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Georgia Ryan","zip":"02210"},{"name":"Cheng Wu Li","zip":"02459"},{"name":"Penelope Hernandez","zip":"02148","message":"Cities are the one place for people scale movement. Without cars Boston can be pollution and noise free and full of life. Please make Boston a world class city and not just good enough because the rest of America is so much worse."},{"name":"Nate Reddi","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Liz Carver","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Willow Choi","zip":"02466"},{"name":"Benjamin Stinson","zip":"02131","message":"Our dangerous streets are a top hindrance to your goal of making Boston the best place to raise a family. Safe street practices are well documented, and you have the power to implement most of them today. Full consensus is impossible. We urgently need courage and leadership to protect our families, as you did with Centre St. in West Roxbury. Don’t delay, our lives are at stake."},{"name":"Nicholas Brown","zip":"02121"},{"name":"Gregory A. Robben","zip":"02135","message":"Boston and its neighbors are one of the few areas in the US I can live without a car. This improves my physical and mental health while allowing me to afford living in this great yet HCOL area. \n\nEnabling safer streets in combination with better public transit improves traffic, congestion, and enables Boston’s residents to STAY in Boston rather than move away to the suburbs."},{"name":"Jenna Celestin","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Robin Ttitta","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Arieh Zimmerman","zip":"02135","message":"You beat him by a landslide. The issue was never actually hurting you, he was grasping at straws. Now someone has died."},{"name":"Katerina Petridou","zip":"02155","message":"I commute daily to work and have to use the bike lanes, sometime these bike lanes are blocked by cars or other vehicles. This increases the risk of an accident when a driver may not expect a cyclist on the road. Please make bike lanes safer by preventing cars or other vehicles to be able to stand by! Thank you for your attention in this matter!"},{"name":"Scott Istvan","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Shervin Riahi","zip":"02472","message":"Our roads are very difficult and costly to improve, I understand that.\nWhat is not difficult is actually enforcing traffic laws and requirin our seemingly apathetic and lazy police forces do their job. A protected bike lane only goes so far when cars are blowing through red lights on a whim, driving/commuting behavior is aggressive and reckless, and obnoxious cyclists ignore safe riding processes."},{"name":"Orla Kennedy","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Katelyn Howerton","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Sarah Horowitz","zip":"02026"},{"name":"Sarah Hanifin","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Toni armstrong","zip":"02143","message":"In 2023, I was hit by a car as a pedestrian while in a marked sidewalk. This accident put me in the hospital away from family and friends and has left me with a TBI that will impact me for life. Though this accident didn't occur in my Boston hometown, it highlighted how critical safety infrastructures are in the places I spend the most of my time. I urge you to act now to build a safer city."},{"name":"Sarah Grimes","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Dan Nelson","zip":"02136","message":"I was very happy the Mayor was so supportive in adding bike lanes and improving general road safety during her first term, but it seems that this priority has taken a back seat during her second term. Maybe Krafts criticisms changed things. I voted for Mayor Wu because of her strong support for bike lanes and street safety.  Please return to the person who stood for safe streets for all! Thank you"},{"name":"Ana Maria Reyes","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Ojas Thakur","zip":"01720"},{"name":"Mel Wilde","zip":"02215","message":"Since COVID lock down we've seen an increase in reckless driving. The cause is unclear and probably complex but what is clear is that Boston has not risen to meet this moment. Moving here I was told Boston was a walkable city yet my experience as a pedestrian has not shown that reputation to be earned anymore. Time to earn that reputation back and make our city safer for all"},{"name":"Andrew Padilla","zip":"02132","message":"I believe in my heart that you support street safety. You've pushed things through, like the critical WRox Centre St. redesign and citywide speed humps, when others wavered. I know that the opposition is loud, fearful of change, and rejects data. But there can be no compromise when lives are at stake: cyclists, pedestrians, drivers... everyone. Please do the right thing. We will have your back."},{"name":"Lean Solis","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Mokhsira Kurbonova","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Julia Beal","zip":"02081"},{"name":"Austin Smith","zip":"02114","message":"Issue a public apology for the u-turn on your original campaign platform for street safety and transit priority without clear or transparent justification to either the public or your own staff. Fire Nick Gove immediately, and issue a public apology that he and other senior members of your cabinet directly lied to and gaslight the City Council and the public present during hearings this year."},{"name":"Sasha Nifontova","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Jonah Novack","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Maura Shira","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Eric Fishman","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Annie Hoy","zip":"22201","message":"My younger sister lives in boston and i would do anything to ensure her safety, please protect her and her friends and the millions of other people under your care"},{"name":"Webber Sloan","zip":"10002"},{"name":"Aiperi Garcia","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Karen Baldassare","zip":"02136","message":"As a Hyde Park resident I dare not use my bike anywhere near Hyde Park Ave. The last time I did, 2 years ago, I was almost hit by a car with a driver who yelled at me even though I was using signals and obeying traffic laws as a cyclist. Clearly, I was just an obstacle in the road to him, not a fellow commuter."},{"name":"Lorenzo Gatti","zip":"02052"},{"name":"Sofia ulloa","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Samantha Casey","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Robert Repaci","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Zachary Beaupre","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Hannah Knight","zip":"02130","message":"We all have a duty to work together to fight climate change, and bike commuters & pedestrians are doing our part. Please help us stay safe and invest in infrastructure that prioritizes alternative modes of transportation."},{"name":"Gavin Rohrer","zip":"02478","message":"Every day when I bike home I chose between a fast route and a safe route. I am reminded through violence that Boston (and MA as a whole) cares more about the convenience of drivers than the lives of its people."},{"name":"Colleen Foran","zip":"02135"},{"name":"bella gauthier","zip":"02081"},{"name":"Kami Kaz","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Mars Maloney","zip":"02130","message":"Part of the Mayor’s job is to ensure a safer city for its residents. I noticed I didn’t see a plan to ensure this doesn't keep happening in response to the passing of your colleague. It is especially poignant that she was working on improving the safety of that area. I would deeply appreciate a commitment to bettering the infrastructure for our safety and seeing real action taken in her honor."},{"name":"Finnegan Gabriel Doherty","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Haeyeon Hong","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kevin Keane","zip":"01760","message":"Please look up the \"Complete Street Philosophy\" that is the best practice the world over in urban street scape planning.  It simply says that there are three user groups on all urban roadways: autos, cyclist, and pedestrians.  Each user group has their own specific needs and limitations.  A Complete Street has three dedicated lanes for each user, emphasizing safety over speed.  Period."},{"name":"Wyatt Sluga","zip":"02109"},{"name":"Jose Diaz","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Ethan","zip":"02140","message":"no one has ever died because they couldn't find a parking spot; when you choose parking over safety, you kill. know this: going back on your plans at parker and tremont is a statement about who you are. if you want to change public perception of yourself and your leadership, start doing the work."},{"name":"Maureen French","zip":"02140","message":"I am a year-round bike commuter from Cambridge into Boston as well as a physician and mom to two cyclists in training who currently enjoy experiencing our wonderful city on the back of my cargo bike. Do not take my life, or theirs, for granted. Anybody (in medicine or otherwise) knows that the cyclist or pedestrian doesn’t stand a chance vs cars and trucks. We need infrastructure to keep us safe!"},{"name":"Eduardo Puerta","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Andriel Fenner","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Mikheil Petrosyan","zip":"01970","message":"I am tired feeling like i am risking my life just to commute to work. Paint on the pavement is not a bike infrastructure. Just in case you didn't know, drivers here are absolutely the worst, and they will run a bike committer over, given the slightest of chances. Please, protect us"},{"name":"V Wong","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Melanie Morris","zip":"02134","message":"Too many cyclists have been killed in Boston. We can fix this before another life is taken senselessly."},{"name":"Claire Cocroft","zip":"02145","message":"I commute on bike to Roxbury Crossing every day, and experience the stress and fear that the intersections in this area pose. The bike (and pedestrian!) infrastructure in this area is significantly worse than in whiter and richer areas of Boston. This is a clear safety issue for residents and commuters, but also a racial and social justice issue. Safe streets should be available to all in Boston."},{"name":"Nisarga Ramesh","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Gahelle Galette","zip":"02072"},{"name":"Charla Whitley","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Robert Guptill","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Anita Johnson","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Megan Ramey","zip":"97031","message":"I was a board member of LivableStreets from '08-16, the \"Renaissance years\". I led the family ride for our annual Tour de Streets fundraiser and Louisa helped me organize it. We filled the streets with biking kids and families to raise awareness about safety, yes, but also showcase the opportunity for joy.\n\nMayor Wu, when you see joyful families biking in the streets, you will honor Louisa's work."},{"name":"Neheet Trivedi","zip":"02140","message":"Thank you for looking into this and being a leader on bike safety."},{"name":"Andrew Martens","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Craig Evans","zip":"02170"},{"name":"Stephanie Adams","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jack Meyers","zip":"02445","message":"I've been bicycling in and around Boston for three decades, and commuted for years. Biking conditions in Boston have improved a bit in 30 years, and the number of bikers has gone up as a result. But the environment and infrastructure for bicyclists and pedestrians needs to get much better much faster. Safety is a priority for everyone."},{"name":"Melissa Markstein","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Diana Lounsbury","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Kiera Alventosa","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Angie Alberto Escobar","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Hazen Peters Emerson","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Jacob Evangelista","zip":"02180"},{"name":"Jason Schuster","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Josh Lown","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Djoulissa Louis-Jean","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Christina Schlegel","zip":"02131"},{"name":"robert rossetti","zip":"02138","message":"Roads are for people, not just cars."},{"name":"Dylan Callahan","zip":"02145","message":"We support you, Mayor. Please have the courage to carry through on your promises."},{"name":"Khanh Nguyen","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Wendy Schwartz","zip":"02134","message":"Mayor Wu, I knew Louisa from having ridden the Livable Streets fundraising ride since its inception, which honored the life and cycling death of community leader Bob Zeeb. \nAction is needed now, not after more studies or discussions. Please get these and other safety improvements in place. Safety is the number one responsibility of government. Please do this."},{"name":"Emma Chadwick","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Roi Orzach","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Jacob Stephens","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Meghan McCoy","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Tricia Lemon","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Harold Zhu","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Grace Whitney","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Yash Tulsiani","zip":"02116","message":"I've had several close calls as a pedestrian in Back Bay, and I'm deeply concerned that the city has not taken meaningful action to improve street safety. It's disheartening to feel that vulnerable road users are no longer a priority. Mayor Wu, I was once a strong supporter, but I believe it's time for new leadership on this issue. Enough is enough."},{"name":"Swathi Srinivasan","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Elizabeth Hanlon","zip":"02143","message":"No one should have to worry about getting killed by a car on their way to work."},{"name":"Resa Blatman","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Orr Ashenberg","zip":"02138","message":"Dear Mayor Wu,\nYou can save lives by acting on bike safety and infrastructure. Do not allow more bike deaths and harm to families and community. Thank you."},{"name":"Amy Plovnick","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Emily Carol","zip":"02474","message":"I urge you to take action and take these specific steps so that lives can be saved. I want to feel safe on our streets with my kids."},{"name":"Ivan Gonzalez","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Brendan Coffey","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Matthew Greene","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Alexandra Wilson","zip":"02141","message":"We've all had our own experience with a dangerous road situation. But how a road is constructed is also a policy decision, and changes that make our streets safer will lead to real reductions in deaths. You can help us save more people and let people get where they need to go safely. Thank you for your time."},{"name":"Annie Moriondo","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Bryce Martin","zip":"02138","message":"Every traffic death is a choice. A preventable failure. It’s time to stop apathetically choosing death."},{"name":"Clayton Spivey","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Joshua Rand","zip":"02130","message":"Mayor Wu, \nDecades of research has shown how the police do significant harm to Boston communities, and yet your recent budget increases funding to the BPD while stalling and cutting safe transportation funding. Fund the safe streets programs that actually save lives, and protect Boston communities."},{"name":"Marie Keil","zip":"02140","message":"Mayor Wu, every time I get on my bike to go grocery shopping, meet a friend, or go to work in Boston, I think to myself “don’t die today”. It doesn’t have to be like this. It is worth sacrificing “convenience” of drivers for the safety of all of us, pedestrians and cyclists and drivers and passengers. Inaction is a choice. Please act."},{"name":"Noah Walsh","zip":"02114","message":"You were elected with the promise of change, change that would make our streets safer than they have ever been. But you’ve sadly wavered over the last few years.  You destroyed your opponent in the last election. You should not be afraid to use your  political power, your power saves lives. Your silence speaks volumes and hurts us all"},{"name":"Ferah Kahyaoglu","zip":"02238","message":"The streets don't belong only to cars.\nEvery cyclist is a human being. A vehicle is not a tool for intimidation or aggression.\nSlow down. Leave space. Be patient. One careless decision can change lives forever.\nShare the road. Respect every life. \n#BikeSafety #ShareTheRoad #VisionZero"},{"name":"Jordan Korgood","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Lakshman Swamy","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Andrea Williams","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Kiersten Kerby-Patel","zip":"02138","message":"I am proud to work at UMass Boston. Students, staff, and faculty at our city's public university need safe ways to get there."},{"name":"Katherine Moon","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Juliana Castedo","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Sarah Whitaker","zip":"02155","message":"It's been too little for too long. We know how to solve these problems, and you have the political backing to do so. There is no excuse."},{"name":"Deborah Galef","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Amara Regehr","zip":"02145","message":"There is no excuse for pedestrian and cyclist deaths. These are entirely preventable by implementing safe street practices. It is critical to uphold Louisa’s legacy and promote proactive safety measure implementation. This includes not reactively removing bike infrastructure when there is political opposition ( ie in response to the Kraft campaign challenge)."},{"name":"Grady Stoodt","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Eric Levine","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Charu Swamy","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Ian Woodhouse","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Annie Shapiro","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Thomas M. Hinkle","zip":"01886"},{"name":"Joseph Bicycles","zip":"97232","message":"When I visit Boston, I bring my folding Brompton bicycle. Please make the city safer for people who walk. bike and ride transit. Cars are coffins and driving is a privilege, not a right."},{"name":"Blake A Sessions","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Andrea Chen","zip":"02135","message":"Safe streets for all. This should not and cannot be an issue of political debate or \"budgeting constraints\". We all deserve to enjoy Boston's communities safely. Please don't let the advocacy of Louisa Gag and all of us fall on deaf ears."},{"name":"Cam McCartin","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Ryan Kiracofe","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Michelle Jones","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Ben Tyler","zip":"02142"},{"name":"Matthew Malone","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Aparna Paul","zip":"02139","message":"I've been hit by two cars this year (once in Cambridge as a pedestrian and once in Somerville as a cyclist). This is an egregious mishandling of priorities—our streets are designed to prioritize cars over people, capital over lives. Let this be a signal that across the city and greater Boston area, we have had enough of being shut out, put on pause, and literally run over again and again."},{"name":"Chris Herlich","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Despina Moutsouris","zip":"02368"},{"name":"Lauren Clark","zip":"02472"},{"name":"David M Fenchel","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Andrew Whitaker","zip":"02155","message":"I myself was hit in a bike lane by a distracted driver in a pickup truck, in a gap between barriers. It is horrifying that even the most experienced, careful transportation advocates are still at risk on the streets in Boston. The victim-blaming needs to stop and the infrastructure needs to be improved ASAP."},{"name":"Catherine Brewster","zip":"02474","message":"I lived on Beacon Hill for 12 years, then moved to Arlington and now commute by bike, mostly through Cambridge, which has gotten steadily safer. When I come off the Longfellow Bridge onto Charles Street, I'm kind of embarrassed by the contrast. I don't see why Boston should be so far behind its smaller neighbor."},{"name":"Michael Sokolov","zip":"02210","message":"you didn't need to worry about the electoral fallout, but you did anyway. Use your political capital to do what's right. Everyone can understand the need for prioritization due to budget constraints, but not caving to political expediency. We can't prevent every traffic death, but we can do much more by addressing the worst intersections now"},{"name":"Betty Mac","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Robert Cowherd","zip":"02115","message":"Zero traffic deaths. If not in Boston, then where?"},{"name":"Troy Smith","zip":"02215","message":"The lack of progress and also of enforcement of traffic violations has lead to a free-for-all in the streets. People are blowing through red lights, stopping wherever they please, commandeering sidewalks and bike lanes whenever convenient. It makes all forms of transportation through the city, including driving, far more dangerous."},{"name":"Christian Tatu","zip":"02139","message":"As a federal city planner, incredibly disappointed by this administration’s (in)action."},{"name":"Kitty Ascrizzi","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Jeremy Koo","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Johnathon D Birs","zip":"02809","message":"Please do something now to address this!"},{"name":"Bob Wolf","zip":"01773"},{"name":"John Baillieul","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Bette Kisner","zip":"02492"},{"name":"liz zobel","zip":"02130","message":"Pedestrians & bikes first"},{"name":"Andrey Fedorov","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Damon Ball","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Morgan Griffiths","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Nova Gregory","zip":"02339"},{"name":"Zeke Kramer","zip":"02421"},{"name":"Julia Mettler-Grove","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Lisa S","zip":"02445","message":"please please please do not let another death happen!!"},{"name":"Peter Sousounis","zip":"01720"},{"name":"Ava Fedorov","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Keegan Dougherty","zip":"02130","message":"Please act on street safety for cyclists, pedestrians and drivers — slower streets are safer for everyone."},{"name":"Anna Wang-Holtzen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Louise Fanchon","zip":"02446","message":"Please please please do better ! I know it’s not easy but we need you to be brave and make the right decisions to protect the most vulnerable - cyclists and pedestrians"},{"name":"Kathryn Sullivan","zip":"02134"},{"name":"David Saakyan","zip":"02131","message":"Mayor Wu, I'm signing to honor Louisa Gag, but reject \"build fast, fix later\" approach in this letter.  We need transparency and urgency on stalled projects and to stop reinventing the wheel with designs – implement proven best practices from other cities! Combined with the lack of both automated (camera-based) and police traffic enforcement,  MA and Boston are grossly neglecting public safety."},{"name":"Philippe Daniel","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Daniel Jeffs","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Carly Buchanan","zip":"02135","message":"We are a single car family. I rely on my bike to take our child to daycare and soon school. While individuals may need to use a car, they have no need to wantonly ignore speed limits, red lights, stop signs, and yield signs. Everyone in this city deserves to be safe. We need more safety infrastructure now."},{"name":"Alec Barrett","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Alyssa Kruithof","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Connor O'Brien","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Paul Kafasis","zip":"02109","message":"Enough is much, much more than enough. People are dying in the streets. Now, a member of your own administration has been killed. Josh Kraft is no longer a threat, but unsafe streets sure are. Stop stalling, and start fixing it."},{"name":"Bethany Mills","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Nicole Neville","zip":"02139","message":"Please recommit to safer streets. It's been extremely disappointing to see the administration's retreat in recent months, particularly for projects that have already been planned/budgeted/approved. It's clear you are listening to a few powerful and wealthy voices rather than the majority of Bostonians and your constituents. I know you can do better because you have in the past"},{"name":"Curt Newton","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Bijan Ghaffari","zip":"80026","message":"Former resident of Boston and year-round bike Commuter. Feared getting hit at unsafe crossings and intersections every day."},{"name":"Rebecca Richman Cohen","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Barry Nelson","zip":"02496"},{"name":"Matthew Nadan-Buresh","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Magdalena Steciuk","zip":"02109"},{"name":"Melinda Szabo","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Franklin Soults","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Preston Buehrer","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Georgia Bowder-Newton","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Yina Turchetti","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Isa Gold","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Robin Chase","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Amy Schoenbaum","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Molly Ryan","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Jiayu Liang","zip":"02144","message":"I met you years ago, when you were a city councilor, at a press conference about Chinatown's inequitable exposure to emissions. Cleaning the air, protecting the health of our communities, and safe bike infrastructure are all connected issues. There is no reason our streets should be this deadly and hostile to bikes. Your people need you to resume these street safety projects."},{"name":"Vivek Sikri","zip":"02139","message":"There is no perfect. We need now not eventually. Louisa's death was entirely preventable and your administration is responsible."},{"name":"Liz Tan","zip":"02148","message":"Please use BTD to enforce no double parking in the bike lanes/bus lanes. Public transit and cyclists depend on these cleared routes.  Fine the cars that double park. Install pick up 15 min parking zones for the workers who are picking up for Ride Share or food pickup. Demand ride share apps and their corporations pay to use the city lanes for stalling and congesting the streets for profit"},{"name":"Jacob Lazarus","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Aila Ikuse","zip":"02143","message":"Not having a call to action in your statement is reprehensible. The time to act was yesterday, the next best time is now."},{"name":"Virginia Donnelly","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Risa L Mednick","zip":"02139","message":"Please make street safety a reality. The humans who live in, commute to, and visit Boston are depending on you!"},{"name":"Allen Veldwisch","zip":"01880"},{"name":"Yixin Hu","zip":"02138","message":"People shouldn't have to choose between death and the financial burden of car-ownership in a city that is already prohibitively expensive for so many"},{"name":"Raul Mojica Soto-Albors","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Alexandra Wong","zip":"02113"},{"name":"Amelia Weber Hall","zip":"01760","message":"Please help this city be the place it can be for cycling and walking as transit.  We are lightyears behind our peers and we need to get safer streets done."},{"name":"Ben Stamas","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Evgenia Diakonenko","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Emma Kirkman-Davis","zip":"02130"},{"name":"James Ridzon","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Dana Boisvert","zip":"03063"},{"name":"Kathryn Badami","zip":"02459"},{"name":"farid","zip":"02145"},{"name":"REBECA POAL","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Chitres Guria","zip":"02139","message":"Let's also fix the roads in the same vein. The road conditions are absolutely attrocious."},{"name":"Jahnavi Bulusu","zip":"02120"},{"name":"E Holland","zip":"02108"},{"name":"Hannah Gold","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Sydney MacDonald","zip":"02142"},{"name":"Michelle W","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Max Gladstone","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Harish Bhandari","zip":"02446","message":"We believe in your Mayor Wu. Please help make Boston a safe city for Bicyclists and Pedestrians."},{"name":"Benjamin Olken","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Joanne Loomer","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Courtney Pong","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Madeline A","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Emma McDougal","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Victoria Arnold","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Jamie Schafer","zip":"02130","message":"Hoping for a better future in Boston for bikes and pedestrians. You know where the problems are, please fix them before we lose another neighbor."},{"name":"Christopher Knight","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Pat Alvarez","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Awad Abdelhalim","zip":"02139"},{"name":"John Fulton","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Miles Hilton","zip":"02145","message":"This violence is not abstract. The policies you make - or rather, fail to make - are written on our bodies, in broken limbs, burst organs, torn skin, and  bloodied asphalt. What we demand is nothing more or less than the human right to free and safe movement in our own streets, among our own communities. A right too long deferred, with a body count rising by the day."},{"name":"Daniel Sprague","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Harrison Simon","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Ethan S Sokol","zip":"02210","message":"I meticulously plan my cycling route to work in Boston. Basic transportation shouldn't need hyper vigilance. We need safe infrastructure for all (said as someone who bikes, takes the train, and drives)."},{"name":"James J Collins","zip":"02127","message":"As I have indicated in letters to the Mayor directly, I find it completely unacceptable and reprehensible that the city has paused or backtracked on its commitment to safer streets for pedestrians and cyclists.\nAs a resident of this city, I *demand* that projects which had been planned and funded for the purposes of making streets safer for pedestrians & cyclists move forward with greatest haste!"},{"name":"Piper Ullmann","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Seren Benoit","zip":"02148","message":"It was only after I was hit by a car in 2022 that the roads in my neighborhood implemented safer crossings for pedestrians. I live to tell the tale of what happens when unsafe conditions go unchanged, but many others in my place have been killed due to reckless driving and unsafe intersections. No more deaths. Please."},{"name":"Matthew Montgomery","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Linden Huhmann","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Michael Kavala","zip":"02125","message":"Her death is on your hands."},{"name":"Steve Cheseborough","zip":"97232"},{"name":"Frieda Nace","zip":"01890","message":"I have two sons living in Mission Hill who bike to school at Northeastern and soon to work at Liberty Mutual in Back Bay.  It terrifies me to think of them biking on these unprotected bike lanes in and around the city.  Please act now.  Be bold and make Boston a proud example of safe bicycle infrastructure."},{"name":"Gabi Drummond","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Judy Friedman","zip":"02459"},{"name":"William","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Younes Abesi","zip":"02149"},{"name":"Alice Wu","zip":"02453"},{"name":"Jay Arthur Gleiner","zip":"01720","message":"PLEASE!"},{"name":"thomas goemaat","zip":"02481"},{"name":"Fynn Schmitt-Ulms","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Jacynda Espenshade","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Beth Griffith","zip":"02026"},{"name":"Norton Pang","zip":"02452"},{"name":"Clovis Jaillet","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Jessie Lan","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Laura Foner","zip":"02130"},{"name":"sair goetz","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Kendall Chase","zip":"02139","message":"Please help make our unruly city streets safe for cyclists."},{"name":"Eli Duggan","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Nicholas Fine","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Benson Christalin","zip":"02121"},{"name":"John Morgan Adams","zip":"02139","message":"I know this is hard. I don’t know the right order to tackle these problems in. You have my sympathy for this problem being on your plate. I’m signing because I just want us moving towards safer streets that will bring more bikers to this city."},{"name":"Thom Cleland","zip":"02142"},{"name":"Mike H","zip":"10023"},{"name":"MaryEllen Roy","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Michele Ross","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Noah Risley","zip":"02130","message":"You should strongly consider resigning, in my personal opinion. The inexcusable inaction of your administration directly caused that woman's death; you have abdicated your duty to protect the residents of Boston."},{"name":"Meilin Garfinkel","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Andrew Guttell","zip":"02448"},{"name":"Sophie Abo","zip":"02144","message":"Please seriously consider these demands. As a transportation worker myself, I am horrified and shaken by this loss of life. This is why I do the work that I do. Please support us in doing the work."},{"name":"Derek McLeod","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Cyrus Rhode Jr","zip":"02141","message":"Please safe streets for everyone NOW."},{"name":"Anna Gishin","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Brian Goodell","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Luis M","zip":"02125","message":"I drive a lot in Boston.  A lot.  Like 15-25k miles per year.  It’s past time for safer streets. Car and truck drivers should not be priority."},{"name":"Joshua Morrison","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Courtney Howard","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Aleksey Kliger","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Samson King","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Jeff Tian","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Scott Andrews","zip":"02111"},{"name":"Daniel Salas","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Justin Suarez","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Andrew Armagost","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Michael deMello","zip":"02144","message":"Please prioritize safe streets for all. Actions over words. 😢"},{"name":"Kristine Acevedo","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Chris Murphy","zip":"01773"},{"name":"Prerana Shrestha","zip":"98109"},{"name":"Dan McKinley","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Cynthia Gillan","zip":"02026","message":"This story is heartbreaking. And preventable.  I implore you to take these demands seriously.  I commute by bike to MGH from Dedham 2-3 times a week and appreciate the bike lanes & SW Corridor immensely.  There are obviously still areas that need safety improvements.  You can do it.  Please!"},{"name":"Paolo Testolina","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Shawdee Eshghi","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Jimena Codina","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Ian Wickersham","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Dan Jaffe","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Graham Oxman","zip":"01027"},{"name":"David Mitri","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Ryan Murray","zip":"02139"},{"name":"JPat Brown","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Karen Buck-Gilbert","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Annie Glodek","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Katherine Dobson","zip":"91403"},{"name":"Thomas Tenzin","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Clara Woods","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Elizabeth Tchantouridze","zip":"02134","message":"When I first moved to Boston years ago, I proudly registered to vote immediately so I could vote for Michelle Wu. I wanted to stay proud. I was excited to live in a city I could freely explore, whether on foot or bike. I wanted to stay excited. But the administration has reneged on campaign promises for safe streets, and so now I am disappointed, afraid, and grieving."},{"name":"Juniper Rivera","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Benjamin Finander","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Nico Brizuela","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Christine Liu","zip":"02143","message":"Lives depend on you."},{"name":"Aliya Norton","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Sharron Sawyer","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Alessandro Mendola","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Teresa M. Eliot Roberts","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Susan Racine","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Robert Carney","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Adam Bullock","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Hannah Rajput","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Dina Pru","zip":"10023"},{"name":"Emily Flynn","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Leah Grossman","zip":"02130","message":"Biking in this city can be a true joy. More people should be able to experience this \n without a constant fear of death or injury. We need to rebalance our streets to prioritize safety for all users."},{"name":"Tim Williams","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Maya Colón Hayes","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Dillon Scott","zip":"02134","message":"Every cyclist I know has regular close calls due to inattentive drivers, illegal parking, and poor street design. Nobody should have to wonder whether today is the day they don’t make it home from work. Please take action to protect cyclists and prevent further unnecessary death and injury to your constituents."},{"name":"Abbey Cahill","zip":"02026","message":"I live in Dedham and work in Dorchester. I don’t have access to a car most days,  so I bike commute to and from work. These streets are built for cars, not people, and it breaks my heart that we have been fighting against that reality since the 60s!! This fall, my family will be biking my daughter to and from preschool in Brookline. I’m anxious about this with the recent cyclist deaths."},{"name":"Scot Osterweil","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Sara Elsa-Beech","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Andrew Swanson","zip":"02170"},{"name":"Asa Reed","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Cathy Smith","zip":"02186"},{"name":"Sam Morrison","zip":"02131","message":"I live in Roslindale and I love biking, it allows me to experience the beauty of this city, but I hesitate to share it with my friends and family because of how unnecessarily dangerous Boston streets are.\n\nWe deserve to ride and get groceries or ride to see friends and not worry about car doors opening or distracted drivers. \n\nLet's build a Boston Louisa would be proud of."},{"name":"Brooke Melody","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Nathaniel Parker","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Patrick Buzza","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Randy Barahona","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Madeleine Hines","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Dale Hollingsworth","zip":"02368"},{"name":"Charlotte Dobbs","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Maytal Bach","zip":"02139","message":"It's hard to stomach that people (my colleagues) are dying despite knowing exactly what saves people and coding to not invest in it. Reducing the planning and transportation departments' funding is not the solution. Targeted interventions are needed... years ago"},{"name":"Joelle Resnik","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Emily Kinsler","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Matthew Liebman","zip":"28801"},{"name":"Charles Homer","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Ronald R Beland","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Ethan Winters","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Kevin M","zip":"02136"},{"name":"Angel Muse","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Bob Oei-Clark","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Caitlin Stier","zip":"02131"},{"name":"andy gao","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Pat Reeve","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Dylan Marshall","zip":"12025"},{"name":"Tong Tong","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Martha Matlaw","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Aditya Nochur","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Amanda Wolfgang","zip":"02478"},{"name":"Ian Goentzel","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Sophan Phin","zip":"02169"},{"name":"Henry Lieberman","zip":"02138","message":"Particularly, Charles St. in Beacon Hill has needed a two-way bike lane; there are few other good routes from the Common to Cambridge. \n\nIn Cambridge, NIMBYs challenged a recently-installed bike lane on Garden St, and gotten the City to \"reconsider\" reverting to a less-safe design to get more parking. But the citizens were outraged, and the City wound up holding fast. Follow their example!"},{"name":"Ritesh Kanchi","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Amiah Ames","zip":"02135","message":"Traffic law enforcement& bike lane maintenance is extinct. Everyday after 4PM, the bike/bus only lanes on Comm Ave morph into Uber Eats driver parking lanes. The protected bike lanes down Mass Ave between Melnea Cass Blvd & Columbia Rd double as parking lanes for cop cars and utility trucks. Motorcycle/mopeds speed thru bike lanes. What exactly are safety officials & cops doing with their time?"},{"name":"Suzanne McGlone","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Danny Chen","zip":"92880"},{"name":"Bryce Andrew Springfield","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Anna Verlander","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Aidan Mundy","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Nikki Laird","zip":"02144","message":"Quick-builds NOW, not yesterday. Refine as you go. Getting to unanimous approval & “perfect design” is at the expense of Boston-area residents’ livelihoods. Prioritize human lives over cars. These deaths & injuries are preventable. We are all just trying to get home at the end of the day.\n\nI am a ‘dot’ on your Vision Zero crash map.  I’m so saddened and tired of seeing more dots added to that map."},{"name":"Brendan Pierce","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Jane Newbold","zip":"02131","message":"I got to meet Louisa for the first time a few weeks ago at a BlueBikes public meeting in Roslindale, and am devastated we will never be able to follow up on our mutual plans to meet again (our parents are good friends). She had so much more to do with her life, and so much passion for the critical work she was doing - please see it through. No more delays; Louisa could still be alive today if only"},{"name":"Julian Rossello Cornier","zip":"02124","message":"Keep us safe!"},{"name":"Yoni Papic","zip":"02137"},{"name":"Dot CV","zip":"02143","message":"We all deserve better"},{"name":"Jarred Graber","zip":"02155","message":"Enough is enough."},{"name":"Neil Boyle","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Lauren Rifas","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Allison Roche","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Janeway Granche","zip":"02135","message":"Every traffic death is a failure to address well documented safety issues.  We know how to make Boston's streets safer for pedestrians, cyclists and drivers. The time to act is now."},{"name":"Julien Tailleur","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Marissa Reese","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Brandon Motes","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Andreas Aeppli","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Catherine Lennartz","zip":"01606"},{"name":"Alana Rusin","zip":"02210"},{"name":"Kenneth Kruckemeyer","zip":"02116","message":"Evaluating each implementation is how to improve the design."},{"name":"Christine Rose","zip":"02126"},{"name":"Marybeth Caldwell","zip":"02191"},{"name":"Erin Wallace","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jesse Henry","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Shannon Bewley","zip":"02446","message":"Mayor Wu, do not back down on your promises to expand safe bike infrastructure. Enough is enough. It is time to prioritize the travel and saftey of local environmentally friendly commuters."},{"name":"Martha Karchere","zip":"02130","message":"Dear Mayor Wu,\nJosh Kraft allied himself with the anti-bike forces in his campaign against you. It's time to push back and continue city efforts to make our streets safer and more welcoming to people in movement without cars."},{"name":"Dave Wood","zip":"02452"},{"name":"Cesar Fuentes","zip":"01702"},{"name":"Ghulam khan","zip":"02467"},{"name":"Radu Nan","zip":"02130","message":"Please raise the level of professionalism and care of the city hall staff to the level of passion and care Louisa brought to her job. The current approach to implementing changes and maintaining our streets is dated, subjective, and dangerous."},{"name":"Robert Cormack","zip":"02186","message":"While I live outside Boston, I cycle to work and many businesses in Boston."},{"name":"Owen Pittet","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Elizabeth Self","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Stefanie D Rich","zip":"02472","message":"I feel less safe biking in this city than I did 10 years ago."},{"name":"Kevine Arne Poulsen","zip":"02472","message":"Perfection is the enemy of action."},{"name":"Adam Rogoff","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Mark Pasnik","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Rachel Jacobe","zip":"02144"},{"name":"KATELYN LEMAIRE","zip":"02151"},{"name":"Samuel Polk","zip":"02476","message":"As a decade-long bike commuter in Greater Boston, including Boston, I’ve been hit by cars twice due to poor bike infrastructure. I’m alarmed by the removal of bike-lane protections and the pause on new safety projects, including near where Louisa Gag was killed. Please restore protections, restart projects, and work towards Boston's stated Vision Zero goals."},{"name":"Eileen Haggerty","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Dylan Keane","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Samantha Laney","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Stephanie Wasiuk","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Ava Danieu","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Nuha Shaikh","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Cindy-jo Gross","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Matthieu Dora","zip":"02476","message":"Boston should be a world leading city in pedestrian facilities with its historic charm and yet cities such as Paris and London have taken more action in the last few years than Boston has in the last 3 decades."},{"name":"Kevin Leppmann","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Yevy Spivak","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Mary Yacovone","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Mandy Ferguson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jorden van Emmerik","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Shaye Jones","zip":"02144","message":"How many people have to die for your administration to take any action, Ms. Wu?"},{"name":"Jehan Sinclair","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Sofia Horan","zip":"02130"},{"name":"ajay sharma","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Martin Staadecker","zip":"02139","message":"Please."},{"name":"Anna Leslie","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Alexa Torres","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Emily Mathay","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Bill Kessler","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Matthew J Quinn","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Bitsy Perlman","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Nathan Collett","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Mary Ellis","zip":"02144","message":"Nearly every day, I commute on my bike to Government Center from Davis Square in Somerville. On my ride, I notice how, immediately after I cross over the river at Charles River Dam Rd., the quality of the bike infrastructure plummets. This is not the reputation that a world class city like Boston should have. We do not deserve it. Louisa did not deserve it. And we can do more. I urge you to Act."},{"name":"Zach Woods","zip":"01773"},{"name":"Ethan Frank","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Simon Kangoun","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Jim Morgan","zip":"02446","message":"Please do what you can to make this the last such tragedy..."},{"name":"Jeremy Rossen","zip":"02472","message":"ACTION NOW!\n(ALWAYS TOO LITTLE TOO LATE WITH POLITICIANS)"},{"name":"Andrew Thomas","zip":"02492"},{"name":"Kyle Parker","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Kerry Bradley","zip":"02118","message":"Bring back the Hub on Wheels ride to being more awareness to cyclists in the city."},{"name":"Gary Williams","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Harper Mills","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Lisa M. LeBlanc","zip":"02109"},{"name":"Lexie Gross","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Jenny Hochstadt","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Haydee M Casellas","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Harry Chung","zip":"03101"},{"name":"Samuel Finston","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Zella Pirello","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Trevor Marchhart","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Adin Bialkin","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Zach Neuwirth","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Christina English","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Yustra Gomez","zip":"02485","message":"‼️‼️‼️‼️HELP  US  PLEASE ‼️‼️‼️"},{"name":"Mary Sharon Kaminski","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Nicolas Schurmann Vignaga","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Rebecca Locke","zip":"02445","message":"As a pediatrician, I support safe street projects to protect my patients."},{"name":"Brandi Hall","zip":"02108"},{"name":"Candace Hodge","zip":"02143","message":"I frequently cycle to work in Gov. Center from Somerville and always feel less safe on a bike as I cross the city limit into Boston.  Please make cyclist safety a priority, especially as it impacts low income households who cannot afford a vehicle."},{"name":"Ann Poulsen","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Bhavin Patel","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Allison Godfrey","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Susann Wilkinson","zip":"02144"},{"name":"McKenna Allred","zip":"02135","message":"It’s been so disappointing as a cyclist and passionate Boston resident to see your quick walk back of creating safe pedestrian and cycling infrastructure in Boston. I no longer feel safe in Boston as a cyclist with you as the mayor."},{"name":"Dana Nguyen","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Theodore Campbell","zip":"02445","message":"Boston deserves safer streets, and a leader with the commitment  to follow through on what's right."},{"name":"Hana Lee","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Jane Matlaw","zip":"02460","message":"Please please please make this a priority. My son and daughter in law use their bikes every day as their primary means of transportation. I worry constantly. Why do we make it so easy for cars and so hard for those who want to help the environment and do the right thing?"},{"name":"Azariah Boyd","zip":"02210"},{"name":"David J Harris","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Franklin Peralta","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Michael Almond","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Marty Dang","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Sophia Orr","zip":"02215","message":"The time is now to fix the bike infrastructure in the city. We’ve already lost so many people due to biking accidents. More and more people - especially young people are biking and we should feel safe and protected while we commute. We should not continue to prioritize cars, when bikers are not safe"},{"name":"Audrey Ng","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Donald Yacovone, Ph. D.","zip":"02155","message":"How many must die before you act?"},{"name":"Mary Alexandra Agner","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Molly Zeff","zip":"02143","message":"I have been hit by a car 3 times just in Cambridge"},{"name":"Emily Reckard-Mota","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Dagmar Sternad","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Kaitlin Kelly-Thompson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Andrew Lewine","zip":"01810","message":"Enough is enough. Vision zero isn't just a catch phrase. Your constituents are *dying* due to traffic violence. It's time to act with vision, expediency, and decisiveness."},{"name":"Christopher Kabacinski","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Alexandra Fortune","zip":"02135","message":"Safer streets save lives and no action is actively killing people."},{"name":"Clay Napurano","zip":"02446","message":"do the right thing"},{"name":"Jason Rundle","zip":"02108"},{"name":"Ryan Miniot","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Safi Chalfin-Smith","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Jolie Frazer","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Elena Milius","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Megan Lam","zip":"02134","message":"As a resident of Boston, Tufts alum, and fellow cyclist, I am infuriated that we continue to see poor cycling infrastructure throughout the city. We voted for you because you campaigned on safer streets. You reneged on this commitment and people are suffering. What will it take for you to honor your promise when you first took office?"},{"name":"Hesper Khong","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Emilie Heilig","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Winston Vaughan","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Sebastian Key","zip":"02129"},{"name":"Brian gannon","zip":"02128","message":"Mayor Wu,\nWe've made great progress on street safety, but the recent election saw pushback that paused some ambitious bike projects. You earned our votes and valuable political capital. Let's use that capital now to make our streets safer in the name of Lousia Gag, your friend and mine. The time is now to push forward on these initiatives."},{"name":"Kate Gearing","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Matthew Mitcheltree","zip":"02130"},{"name":"MATTHEW BONSER JOHNSON","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Cheyenne Mason","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Caroline Tornquist","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Julie Lugten","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Aidan Q.","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Rebecca Stamp","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Lauren Sullivan","zip":"02125"},{"name":"Christopher Wyllie","zip":"02139","message":"Dear Mayor Wu,\n\nAs a resident of Cambridge, I am not a direct constituent of yours, but I have in the past been a supporter of yours. \n\nStreet safety is not optional, and it does not harm local businesses. I rarely cross the river to shop because it is unsafe to do so as soon as I get to the Boston side of the Longfellow bridge. My dollars will stay in Cambridge until safety improves."},{"name":"Maria V. Sanchez Mico","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Emile Hamwey","zip":"02144","message":"How many more Bostonians have to be murdered by cars on our streets before we treat this like the urgent crisis it is?"},{"name":"Elana Schwam","zip":"02155","message":"We need to make our streets safer for everyone"},{"name":"Lola Ibanez","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Erin Bartus","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Brianne Skywall","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Estefany Benitez","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Polina Ermoshkina","zip":"02144","message":"I cycle to work everyday. The most dangerous behavior I see from car drivers happens all the time and goes unpunished. Enforce the laws and give more tickets/suspensions for unsafe driving around cyclists. The infrastructure is needed to minimize car driver/cyclist interactions, but this doesn’t mean treating cyclists as second class commuters. Incentivize cycling and save your city."},{"name":"Max Evans","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Nicholas Walsh","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Jeremy Phillips","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Becky Malinowski","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Sara Rudolph","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Scott Ehrmann","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Trevor Clark","zip":"02144","message":"I've just returned from a visit to Portland Oregon and the stark contrast in bicycle and pedestrian safety infrastructure is astounding. I am appalled that the city of Boston has delayed projects time and again. This directly endangers the lives of the most vulnerable road users. Change now and prevent unnecessary death."},{"name":"Mark Gavin","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Nicolas Fernandez","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Erika Silva","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Diane Grant","zip":"02120"},{"name":"G C","zip":"02130","message":"Please improve street safety for cyclists, and save lives!"},{"name":"Christopher Wink","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Gerard Baquer Gomez","zip":"02138","message":"please"},{"name":"Tara Patel","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Trevor Silva","zip":"02143"},{"name":"James Angstman","zip":"02215","message":"For a walking city Boston is pretty damn hostile to pedestrians. Fix it."},{"name":"Roger Forcada Margarit","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Nick Schwartz","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Kristen Halbert","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Niels Vanderloo","zip":"02139","message":"Make our streets safe! Now!!"},{"name":"Lorenzo Van Munoz","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Jordyn Goldson","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Binit Shrestha","zip":"02120","message":"C'mon, Mayor Wu."},{"name":"Berta Escude","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Gemma Ibanez","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Nathaniel Borders","zip":"02135","message":"Please wake up to the important message this letter is giving you."},{"name":"Jonathan Fertig","zip":"80206","message":"Longtime 02130/02122 now residing in Colorado, and looking back on my old home with deep sadness, both for the loss of Louisa, who was a bright star in the city, and for the abandonment of an idea and a community by a mayor who we thought we knew so well and trusted thoroughly."},{"name":"Lewis Black","zip":"02135"},{"name":"John Craver","zip":"11225"},{"name":"Yolunda Silva","zip":"11206","message":"Make the streets safe for all."},{"name":"Andrew Lee","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Megan Jones","zip":"02115"},{"name":"B. July","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Federico Mancini","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Kyle Matthew Flores","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Abigail Starr","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Tom Body","zip":"02140"},{"name":"BARBARA A SEIDL","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Niki Kuchipudi","zip":"02134"},{"name":"miso w","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Jonathan Wilson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Christopher R. Vaughan","zip":"55408","message":"Though I now live in Minneapolis, I used to work steps from where Louisa was killed: At ABCD Parker Hill Fenway, yards from the intersection of Tremont and Parker, an intersection I biked through countless times on my way to work to teach Englisht to adult immigrants. It is well past time for to unpause, restart, fully fund, and prioritize the implementation of safety measures for all Bostonians."},{"name":"Catherine Porter","zip":"02144","message":"i am appalled that the only way to make our streets safer is political pressure after the horror of a preventable death."},{"name":"Sophie Staii","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Priyanka Rangadass","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Andrew Troska","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Katherine Asselin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Gandharvika Gopal","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Colleen McGuire","zip":"02134","message":"I avoid many of the main streets in Boston as part of my bike commute because they are fast and dangerous. Infrastructure for car traffic is prioritized over cycling, pedestrian and multimodal public transportation.  Stop prioritizing in this way. Shift this focus and really change the way the people move through our city. Protect the folks not in cars."},{"name":"Mabel Pence","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Jonathan Berz","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Michelle Weinatein","zip":"02132"},{"name":"Josh McCorkle","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Neal Tilhou","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Mike Blackwell","zip":"02379","message":"I have bike commuted to my job in Boston for over two decades. It really seemed like the city was making good progress in making things safer for pedestrians and cyclists, but that all seemed to stall over a year ago. Please re-prioritize safety improvements in Boston!"},{"name":"Leyre","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Hazem Algendy","zip":"02467"},{"name":"Nico Smith","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Carlota","zip":"02141"},{"name":"Martin Plovnick","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Juan Taborda","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Michael DiDomizio","zip":"02134","message":"Louisa was a wonderful person and her loss is a complete tragedy. It was preventable. Please make greater efforts to support safe streets so losses like hers stop becoming such a common occurrence in Boston."},{"name":"Brenna Dunn","zip":"01810","message":"Do better, Major Wu. One more death due to you serving big corporations and not the people of Boston. Make your streets safer and act now."},{"name":"Rani Schloss","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Peter Gallagher","zip":"01742"},{"name":"Martin Richard","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Valerie Enriquez","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Amy Wipfler","zip":"02138"},{"name":"John Callerame","zip":"02144","message":"I live in Somerville, but I work in Boston (Back Bay), and I ride my bike to work about once a week -- so I hope to see Boston resume the street safety improvements we saw in your first three years as Mayor."},{"name":"Nick Brennan","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Michelle J","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Maisy Rohrer","zip":"02114"},{"name":"David Kramer","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kevin Smith","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Bryan Bigelow","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Kate Sullivan","zip":"02760"},{"name":"Sarah A. Levy","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Paul Maschhoff","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Graham Turk","zip":"02119","message":"It's been almost a year since Boston residents soundly rejected a mayoral candidate who made tearing out bike lanes the focal point of his campaign. Now that it's clear you will not lose a primary by supporting safe streets, what are you waiting for? I knocked doors for you last year but wouldn't even consider volunteering if these projects are not resumed soon."},{"name":"Ernest Jackson","zip":"01923","message":"Please stop acting like Josh Kraft was right. I know you know better than that. Don't let this death be in vain."},{"name":"Theresa Cutter","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Amanda Leinbaugh","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Kyle Yuan","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Jeffrey Orlin","zip":"02458","message":"I'm just curious how many more lives must be lost before we do something. Other places have proved that it doesn't have to be this way and there are many facets to the solution but infrastructure and motor vehicle operator behavior and attitude could use a lot of attention right now."},{"name":"Susan Huang","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Noah Leavitt","zip":"01923"},{"name":"Kenny Arana Fennell","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Sarah G. Jackson","zip":"02130"},{"name":"CHRISTOPHER KUNGIE","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Ashley Enochs","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Joshua Gorman","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Olivia James","zip":"02459"},{"name":"Matthew Terrill","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Alex Mattern","zip":"02127","message":"The number one killer of children in Massachusetts is motorists. As the elected mayor you have the power to change this statistic. You can do it."},{"name":"Carolina Abuelo","zip":"02445","message":"I’ve been hit as a cyclist in a poorly designed cross walk near museum of science. I would be so grateful to you for implementing these recommendations now so I don’t become Louisa Gag."},{"name":"Kathryn Skeldon","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Brett Woodvine","zip":"02215"},{"name":"JR Moock","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Philipp Tkachev","zip":"02062","message":"I truly believe that period of half-measures is over. I have been in accidents myself. We need a revolutionary approach to road safety. We should build tunnels and close streets for car traffic. We need to be able to ticket people without police. Simple photo report via 311 app should be enough to give violator a ticket. We need traffic cameras, especially red light ones."},{"name":"Cathy Ellis","zip":"01985"},{"name":"Carol Marton","zip":"02130","message":"Mayor Wu, I've been grateful every day for the increased safety and actual  quality of life the speed bumps in Boston have made.  Please prioritize saving lives in our city.  More and more folks are riding bicycles, which is a good thing for the city.  Make that and public transportation the BEST OPTIONS for travel in the city."},{"name":"EMily Hewitt","zip":"02130","message":"In addition to these safety measures it seems that education and reeducation of drivers need to occur . Many of us drove for years on roads that did not include bicycle lanes . In addition bike riders MUST also follow the laws and rules - this needs to be a\nFull community effort .\nlet’s prevent any further bicyclists’ deaths - one is already to many ."},{"name":"Alex Skeldon","zip":"01880"},{"name":"Denise OMalley","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Jean Dunoyer","zip":"02472","message":"I love your policies in general, so I am hoping the bicycle ones will catch up."},{"name":"Michael Zank","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Jennifer Martinelli","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Adam Beerman","zip":"02118","message":"I moved to Boston specifically because I knew I wouldn’t need a car. Let’s keep it safe for bikers 🙏"},{"name":"Jeremi Mountjoy","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Terry Mason","zip":"02130","message":"My message will simply reiterate those of so many others--and you yourself know that makes our streets safer for people on bicycles, pedestrians and even those in cars is more than urgent.  I understand that there is a lot on your plate and that priorities change but bicycling in this city, walking in this city and driving in this city are universal experiences for residents and visitors."},{"name":"Lauren Butler","zip":"02210","message":"Please help. I know you care."},{"name":"Todd Abrams","zip":"02142"},{"name":"Henry Hutcheson","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Alan Walker","zip":"01778","message":"Hi Mayor Wu, \nAll major roads should have bike lanes built like the new ones on State and Congress. Not only would it save the lives of bikers but it would make the streets more sane for vehicle drivers and help remind pedestrians that there are bikes to watch out for too. \nThank you, Al"},{"name":"Carlos Morales","zip":"02130","message":"Please, please, we don't want more neighbors, family, friends, colleagues to continue dying. \nPor favor, por favor, no queremos que más vecinos, familiares, amigos y colegas continúen muriendo."},{"name":"Camilla Cox","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Eli Pollock","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Charlotte Burger Troy","zip":"94973","message":"How many more?"},{"name":"Michael Giovanniello","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Deepak kumar","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Kelly Cartagena Rusch","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Karl Alexander","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Bao-Minh Hoang","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Johnattan Ontiveros","zip":"02119","message":"Biking has been my primary form of transportation for 8 years. I bike conservatively and always use caution, but there have been several times where a driver who is truly not paying attention has nearly seriously injured me. Much of this can be solved with cyclist protections across the main paths of the city."},{"name":"Jason Livingston","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Alicia Williams","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Annastasia MacKenzie","zip":"02493"},{"name":"Rosa Hayes","zip":"02129","message":"Designing streets to maximize pedestrian and cyclist safety improves neighborhood livability and overall environmental  quality. It’s also a necessary intervention to mitigate some of the environmental harms that will otherwise occur due to climate change. It’s inexcusable that your administration has paused safe streets projects for so long. Louisa should still be here."},{"name":"Anna Hermann","zip":"02474"},{"name":"Eileen Hutchins","zip":"02122","message":"Dear Mayor Wu, My husband commutes by bike to work from Dorchester to Brighton. I worry for his safety. Please end these senseless killings; educate drivers and bikers about road rules; prosecute violators; bring Boston into safety compliance with other states; align with countries that protect bikers and pedestrians through road design and traffic enforcement -like  the Netherlands. Thank you"},{"name":"James Gumpper","zip":"02131","message":"You were supposed to be the option for Mayor who would protect us, but you are moving backwards on safe transit! Do better, please!"},{"name":"Timothy Bulger","zip":"02492"},{"name":"Guy Mendilow","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Aaron Kraemer","zip":"02150"},{"name":"Liz Hughes","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Adriana Santiago","zip":"02111"},{"name":"Ashley Pratt","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Richard Voos","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Natalia Ortega Herrero","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jane Kungie","zip":"02122"},{"name":"Margie Bell","zip":"02476"},{"name":"Mark Eisenberg","zip":"02138"},{"name":"Allison Richardson","zip":"01754"},{"name":"Carly J Gavant","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Daniel Flannery","zip":"02052"},{"name":"Rebecca Harris","zip":"02474","message":"Other cities like Helsinki have achieved zero traffic deaths over the course of a year. Boston ought to be leading the U.S. to prove it’s possible to keep pedestrians and cyclists safe here too."},{"name":"Marc Rosenbaum","zip":"02575"},{"name":"Alan Euston","zip":"02139","message":"Fix this now"},{"name":"Matt Casey","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Kevin Fitzgerald","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Anne Hjortshoj","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Valerie Oorthuys","zip":"01721"},{"name":"Tibrine da Fonseca","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Susan Chang","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Micah Sachs","zip":"02130"},{"name":"SC Pierce","zip":"02130","message":"We voted for your pro-cyclist stance. What happened?"},{"name":"Paul S Foster-Moore","zip":"01062","message":"My son, his wife and 2 yr old daughter frequently bike the Roslindale streets - your home town- but worry about their safety. We are concerned parents and grandparents and urge you to get the bike safety program back on track. Please and thank you in advance.\nPaul & Laurel Foster-Moore\nNorthampton MA"},{"name":"Christine Casalini","zip":"02134","message":"Restart and fully fund traffic calming and bike and pedestrian safety programs"},{"name":"Rob Colonna","zip":"02116"},{"name":"Erik Hjortshoj","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Will Bogardus","zip":"02129"},{"name":"William Kyler Psenka","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Fiona Land","zip":"01984","message":"Both my 13 year old son and I have been hit by cars while riding our bikes within 2 miles of our home in the greater Boston area within the past 9 months. My son was hit in a crosswalk on the way to school. I was hit in a marked bike lane. Instead of picking up my daughter, I was in an ambulance with concussion. We're both ok now, but could have been Louisa. Do better."},{"name":"Mardge H Cohen","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Michael Eskin","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Sally Bigelow","zip":"02129","message":"Dear Mayor, the crosswalks at Austin Street and Rutherford Avenue in Charlestown are horrible and also the do not turn right on red at the intersections at these stoplight are totally ignored by the vehicles pedestrians are at risk daily"},{"name":"Evelyn Syed-Molin","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Kelsey Haugh","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Paul Nicknish","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Carlotta Barone","zip":"02139"},{"name":"David Weinstein","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Kristen Sunter","zip":"02139","message":"I was hit by a car while biking to work in 2016 in Somerville, and in the weeks following, two cyclists were killed in Cambridge. Given how popular cycling is even with the current levels of danger, how environmentally friendly bikes are, and how much bike commuting could reduce traffic, there's no reason not to prioritize bike infrastructure."},{"name":"Beatriz Moreira","zip":"02124"},{"name":"David Veloz","zip":"02466"},{"name":"Daniel Gelbtuch","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Catherine O’Keefe","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Ilya Sytchev","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Julia Nash","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Gordon Schiff","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jana Scholten","zip":"02120","message":"Enough is enough! How many more death's will it take to get back to protecting our streets so we can safely ride our bikes in Boston? Please consider making this a priority again. Jana Scholten"},{"name":"Jocelyn Marshall","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Daniel B Shugrue","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Dr. Jennifer Brody","zip":"02124"},{"name":"Mara Voukydis","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Tony Dutzik","zip":"02122","message":"I am a cyclist in Boston and the father and husband of people who ride bikes to get to work and school. The thought of losing a loved one in a crash that could have been prevented, or the risk of it minimized, with better street design and traffic enforcement is unfathomable. We have the tools to keep people safe. It is time to use them."},{"name":"kelle griffon","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Sean O'Neall","zip":"02472","message":"Safer streets for cylists and pedestrians! Safer bike lanes and bike lanes that cannot be used for parking! Ticketing enforcement for illegally parked vehicles!"},{"name":"Susan Jackson","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Julia Ramon Mateu","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Phoenix Boulay","zip":"02169","message":"As a  former 20 year resident of Jamaica Plain, one of the most bike friendly communities in Boston, I'm saddened to see that the cyclist and pedestrian carnage continues. Beloved Mayor Menino worked closely with various organizations to plan/make our streets safer for members of our community, which you have stalled. Worry less about illegal aliens, more about citizens who matter and pay taxes."},{"name":"Corie Scibelli","zip":"02131","message":"The exact area where Louisa was killed is and has been deadly and dangerous for far too long. I myself was clipped by a driver on my bicycle on my way to class at Northeastern over 15 years ago. In 2010, my classmate, Andy Prior, was also killed there on his moped. How many lives, especially young ones, need to be damaged or lost? One is far too many and we are too late. PLEASE, do something."},{"name":"Maria Christina Blanco","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Henry Shugrue","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Kevin McCaffrey","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Jason Mogel","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Daniel Junkins","zip":"02120","message":"Please make our streets safer now!"},{"name":"Nate Stell","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Nathan Aronow","zip":"02460"},{"name":"Phil Gunderson","zip":"01040","message":"I am signing as a former Mission Hill resident and friend of a friend of Louisa. I biked through the intersection that Louisa was killed at hundreds of times when I lived on Mission Hill, and know how dangerous it is. It is unconscionable that your administration paused work to make this street safer absolutely no reason. Louisa paid for that decision with her life. The time for action is now."},{"name":"Julia St George","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Liane D","zip":"02118","message":"Overall, the city also needs to drastically improve enforcement of basic rules of the road — there isn’t an intersection in Boston where cars don’t go through red lights at every opportunity."},{"name":"Matthew Vincenty","zip":"02148"},{"name":"Mick Timony","zip":"02130","message":"I have supported the current Mayor and wonder why initiatives like changes to Ukrainian way which is likely one of the most dangerous intersections in the city for pedestrians have not yet occurred. Many intersections that are dangerous to pedestrians and cyclists and other users of our roads have not seen changes to minimize danger to non-automobile users."},{"name":"Ivory King","zip":"02130","message":"My partner always worries when I set out to cycle to work. Please fix the streets so I can tell her I'll be ok!"},{"name":"Ross MacFadyen","zip":"02215"},{"name":"Katherine McDaniel","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Eileen Botti","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Andrea Wells","zip":"02126","message":"I was told years ago that a light for pedestrians was ABOUT to be added to Morton Street. Still no light for pedestrians. Cars fly down Morton. My neighbors on Clearwater have been asking for speed bumps for years. Cars use Clearwater as a cut through and go too fast. No speed bumps. When do we get taken seriously?\nI'm not sure about \"building fast,\" but we certainly can't wait for perfection."},{"name":"Paolo De Guzman","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Jon Rudzinski","zip":"02131"},{"name":"Roderick MacNeil","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Matthew Ritter","zip":"02128"},{"name":"Rei Watanabe","zip":"02134","message":"I was very optimistic about the bike infras improvements"},{"name":"Cameron Lawless","zip":"02143"},{"name":"Eric Cao","zip":"02140"},{"name":"Annabelle Nolan","zip":"02120"},{"name":"Philip M Roberts","zip":"02115","message":"Please restart safe streets program. Thank you."},{"name":"Sam Marchesi","zip":"02144"},{"name":"Wes Mars","zip":"02472","message":"#DemandMore"},{"name":"Tom Lamar","zip":"02145"},{"name":"Gregory Savageau","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Sarah D W Nagle","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Matthew Goldstein","zip":"02445"},{"name":"Philip Brink","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Julia Eskew","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Ben Lewis","zip":"02115"},{"name":"Susanne Schindler","zip":"02139","message":"Dear Mayor Wu, I'm a Cambridge resident, so can't vote for you, but woild if I could. But street safety is a core, core issue for me, and cities must work together. I urge you to stand up for what you know is right and take the long view--safer streets will allow kids to become independent, elders to accomplish their errands, workers to get to work and save on commuting costs. Thank you."},{"name":"Jorge Alvarez","zip":"02130"},{"name":"Avery burdette","zip":"02135"},{"name":"Sara Colón","zip":"02131","message":"My partner, child and I commute on personal bikes, Bluebikes and public transit 6 days a week in all kinds of weather - I want to raise my daughter and my students in a city where being a cyclist and pedestrian is sustainable and safe."},{"name":"Lily Hayes","zip":"02118","message":"Please make bike lanes safer so I don’t have to worry about my sister ending up in the trauma bay just because she is commuting to work"},{"name":"madeleine c","zip":"02472"},{"name":"Daniel Phipps","zip":"02139"},{"name":"Dean Eckles","zip":"02139"},{"name":"kristin guyot","zip":"02138","message":"As a public health issue, we need to ensure bike safety so that more people cycle. Beyond being fatal machinery, cars are quiet killers as polluters. With our dirty air and rising heat, we can't wait. Bike deaths are not \"accidents.\" They're substantially avoidable."},{"name":"Barbara Zack","zip":"02118","message":"Please add a new protocol as suggested in the Boston Globe to have a road evaluation after every bike accident to make our cities safer!!"},{"name":"jason d bowers","zip":"02445","message":"i've been bike commuting in boston since 2004...so much has improved since then.  Please keep up this important work.  We frequently go down town to green way and esplanade on the weekends and we don't have a consistent safe way for my wife, 8 yr old son and i to safely explore all the great things boston has to offer"},{"name":"Lily Ko","zip":"02170"},{"name":"Patrick Bonner","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Meghan R Metivier","zip":"02119"},{"name":"Gurol Tuncman","zip":"02467"},{"name":"Ana Maria Camargo","zip":"02114"},{"name":"Barbara Callaghan","zip":"02155"},{"name":"Sandy Hoehl","zip":"02127"},{"name":"Samantha Garwin","zip":"02472","message":"Boston area residents shouldn't have to risk our lives every time we get on a bike.  You have the power to change this. Use it."},{"name":"Beyer Bullard","zip":"02134"},{"name":"Leigh Heyman","zip":"02446"},{"name":"Coryn Maher","zip":"02118"},{"name":"Stephanie KHOURY","zip":"02452"},{"name":"Rachel Loischild","zip":"02131"},{"name":"David McGaffin","zip":"02130","message":"Mayor Wu, it is time to reprioritize improvements to cycling and pedestrian infrastructure throughout the city. These tragic deaths can be prevented. Your administration has already made large improvements to traffic safety but there is much more work to do. Please pursue this. Please make the changes that make us safer on the streets. I am tired of seeing new ghost bikes around the city."},{"name":"Anna Sangree","zip":"02155","message":"Biking into Boston is one of the most fun, fastest and healthy ways to commute. I work in downtown and love being a part of the city life. Since this crash happened, I've been really scared to bike in and that makes me really sad because it is something I love, and something I know Louisa loved too. Boston lanes need protection. Please prioritize safety on Boston roads."}];
